Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.21,0:00:40.64,Default,,0,0,0,,下一条消息\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Issue:
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.64,0:00:44.62,Default,,0,0,0,,苏联继续进行其最近的一系列军事演习\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}The Soviet Union continued its recent series of military exercises...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.62,0:00:48.04,Default,,0,0,0,,今天在白令海进行了一次爆炸试验\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}... conducting a bomb test today in the Bering Sea...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.04,0:00:52.20,Default,,0,0,0,,离阿拉斯加南海岸仅1500英里\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}... just 1500 miles off the southern coast of Alaska.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.20,0:00:56.67,Default,,0,0,0,,总统理查德·尼克松对苏联发布如下警告\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}President Richard Nixon issued this warning to the Soviets:
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.67,0:01:00.34,Default,,0,0,0,,美国从不主动挑起冲突\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}The United States does not start fights.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.34,0:01:02.16,Default,,0,0,0,,我必须强调\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Let it be clear
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.16,0:01:04.35,Default,,0,0,0,,我们维持自己的实力\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Let it be clear we maintain our strength...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.35,0:01:07.32,Default,,0,0,0,,是为了维护和平\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...in order to maintain peace...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.32,0:01:11.22,Default,,0,0,0,,所以任何对手 都应问问自己\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...so any adversary should ask themselves:
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.22,0:01:14.46,Default,,0,0,0,,攻击美国带来的后果\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}"Do the consequences of attacking America...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.46,0:01:17.11,Default,,0,0,0,,是否高于可能带来的好处\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...outweigh the potential benefits?"
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.11,0:01:20.07,Default,,0,0,0,,苏联的行动导致了一个结果\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}As a result of the Soviet activity...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.07,0:01:22.86,Default,,0,0,0,,核能科学家监察小组\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...the watchdog group of nuclear scientists...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.86,0:01:27.90,Default,,0,0,0,,将"末日时钟"的指针拨到了午夜前5分钟\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}... moved the Doomsday Clock up to five minutes until midnight:
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.45,0:01:32.93,Default,,0,0,0,,午夜代表核战带来的毁灭\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Destruction by nuclear war.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.57,0:01:35.03,Default,,0,0,0,,问题\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Question:
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.60,0:01:38.08,Default,,0,0,0,,用0到10来衡量 0代表不可能…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}On a scale of zero to 10, zero meaning impossibility...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.08,0:01:40.63,Default,,0,0,0,,10代表理论上完全的确信\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...10 meaning complete metaphysical certitude...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.63,0:01:45.37,Default,,0,0,0,,俄罗斯人实际进攻美国的机会到底有多大?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...what are the chances the Russians will actually attack the United States?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.37,0:01:46.93,Default,,0,0,0,,帕特·布坎南\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Pat Buchanan.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.93,0:01:48.43,Default,,0,0,0,,零\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Zero.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.43,0:01:51.24,Default,,0,0,0,,苏联人绝不会冒险发起战争\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}The Soviets would never risk going to war...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.24,0:01:55.06,Default,,0,0,0,,只要我们这边还有一件行走的核威慑\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...when we have a walking nuclear deterrent on our side.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.06,0:01:57.69,Default,,0,0,0,,你说的当然是曼哈顿博士\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You're referring, of course, to Dr. Manhattan...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.69,0:02:01.04,Default,,0,0,0,,但是曼哈顿博士的存在一定能保证世界和平吗\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}... but does Dr. Manhattan's existence guarantee world peace?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.04,0:02:02.14,Default,,0,0,0,,艾琳娜·克里夫特\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Eleanor Clift.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.14,0:02:05.04,Default,,0,0,0,,然而这并没有阻止苏联继续\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Well, it hasn't stopped the Soviet Union...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.04,0:02:09.70,Default,,0,0,0,,囤积破纪录数量的核武器\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}... from stockpiling record amounts of nuclear weapons.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.70,0:02:11.58,Default,,0,0,0,,你不觉得那只是摆摆样子吗\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You don't think it's just posturing?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.58,0:02:13.52,Default,,0,0,0,,也许苏联人之所以…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Maybe the reason why the Soviets...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.52,0:02:16.22,Default,,0,0,0,,搞这些炸弹试验…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...are doing these bomb tests...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.22,0:02:19.86,Default,,0,0,0,,就是因为害怕曼哈顿博士\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...is because they feel threatened by Dr. Manhattan.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.86,0:02:24.31,Default,,0,0,0,,或许全世界都有这样的感觉\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Of course. Maybe the whole world feels like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.32,0:02:28.76,Default,,0,0,0,,苏联的船只已经侵犯了领海\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Soviet ships have violated the territorial waters...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.59,0:03:07.85,Default,,0,0,0,,该来的早晚都会来\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Just a matter of time, I suppose.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.48,0:04:39.79,Default,,0,0,0,,这就是个笑话\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}It's a joke.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.79,0:04:41.79,Default,,0,0,0,,全都是笑话\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}It's all a joke.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.79,0:04:44.72,Default,,0,0,0,,母亲 原谅我\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Mother, forgive me.
