Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.64,0:11:10.80,Default,,0,0,0,,不\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}No!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.77,0:11:43.90,Default,,0,0,0,,爱德华·布雷克 67岁 6尺2寸 重225磅\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}GALLAGHER: Edward Blake. Sixty-seven years old. Six-two, a solid 225.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.41,0:11:46.42,Default,,0,0,0,,这家伙结实得像个橄榄球后卫\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Guy was built like a linebacker.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.42,0:11:48.49,Default,,0,0,0,,对 我看过尸体了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}FINE: Yeah, I saw the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.49,0:11:50.73,Default,,0,0,0,,按他这年纪的人来说 他身形极佳\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}For a guy his age, he was in terrific shape.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.73,0:11:53.41,Default,,0,0,0,,你是说 除了他死了这一点?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}GALLAGHER: You mean apart from being dead?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.65,0:11:56.30,Default,,0,0,0,,那是厚玻璃板\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}That's plate glass.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.30,0:11:59.37,Default,,0,0,0,,你得踩油门才能撞出条裂缝来\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You'd have to step on the gas just to put a crack in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.37,0:12:01.61,Default,,0,0,0,,一定是被扔出去的\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Had to have been thrown.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.61,0:12:02.97,Default,,0,0,0,,检查过卧室了吗?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Check the bedroom?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.97,0:12:06.08,Default,,0,0,0,,是的 抽屉都被打开了 翻了个底朝天\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Yeah. Drawers opened, tossed through.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.08,0:12:09.31,Default,,0,0,0,,床垫被翻过。大概是入室抢劫\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Mattress flipped. Probably robbery.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.31,0:12:10.95,Default,,0,0,0,,或者做成入室抢劫一样\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Or made to look like one.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.95,0:12:12.73,Default,,0,0,0,,看看这个\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}See this?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.04,0:12:16.42,Default,,0,0,0,,- 和总统握手 - 哇\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}- Shaking hands with the president. FINE: Whoa.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.42,0:12:18.82,Default,,0,0,0,,觉得布雷克是密探?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Think Blake was a spook?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.82,0:12:22.78,Default,,0,0,0,,政府的还是地下组织的?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Government or black ops?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.78,0:12:24.71,Default,,0,0,0,,我觉得…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}GALLAGHER: I think...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.02,0:12:28.32,Default,,0,0,0,,这件事远远大过你我\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...this is way bigger than both of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.42,0:12:36.87,Default,,0,0,0,,罗夏日记 10月12日 1985年\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}RORSCHACH: Rorschach's journal, October 12th, 1985.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.87,0:12:42.24,Default,,0,0,0,,今早巷子里有狗尸 车轮碾爆它肚皮\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Dog carcass in alley this morning. Tire tread on burst stomach.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.24,0:12:44.65,Default,,0,0,0,,这座城市害怕我\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}This city's afraid of me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.65,0:12:48.61,Default,,0,0,0,,我见过它的真面目 这些街道就是无尽的臭水沟…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I've seen its true face. The streets are extended gutters...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.27,0:12:51.82,Default,,0,0,0,,充满鲜血的臭水沟\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}... and the gutters are full of blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.82,0:12:54.31,Default,,0,0,0,,当这些污垢终于结痂时…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}And when the drains finally scab over...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.38,0:12:57.61,Default,,0,0,0,,所有的害虫都会淹溺\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}... all the vermin will drown.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.25,0:13:00.80,Default,,0,0,0,,他们的色情和谋杀所沉积的污秽…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}The accumulated filth of all their sex and murder...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.80,0:13:03.27,Default,,0,0,0,,会在他们的腰部泛起泡沫…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}... will foam up around their waists...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.27,0:13:08.75,Default,,0,0,0,,这时所有的婊子和政客们就会抬头哭喊： "救救我们！"\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}... and all the whores and politicians will look up and shout, "Save us."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.73,0:13:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,而我轻声说："不"\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}And I'll whisper, "No."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.87,0:13:17.70,Default,,0,0,0,,现在整个世界立于边缘…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Now the whole world stands on the brink...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.70,0:13:20.55,Default,,0,0,0,,向下盯着血腥的地狱\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}... staring down into bloody hell.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.55,0:13:24.26,Default,,0,0,0,,那些自由主义者、知识分子…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}All those liberals and intellectuals...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.26,0:13:26.42,Default,,0,0,0,,还有只会说好话的人…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}... and smooth talkers...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.42,0:13:29.88,Default,,0,0,0,,突然之间 没人能想出一句话来说\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}... and all of a sudden, nobody can think of anything to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.88,0:13:33.40,Default,,0,0,0,,在我脚下 这座可怕的城市…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Beneath me, this awful city.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.40,0:13:37.18,Default,,0,0,0,,它惨叫连连 如同满是弱智儿童的屠宰场\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}It screams like an abattoir full of retarded children...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.18,0:13:41.98,Default,,0,0,0,,夜晚散发出通奸和丧良心的臭气\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}... and the night reeks of fornication and bad consciences.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.29,0:14:39.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}(剪报：凶残的暴行被制止)
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.61,0:14:47.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}(笑匠笑到了最后：罪犯头目摩罗神 在戏剧性的决斗中受到了正义的制裁)
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.10,0:14:55.03,Default,,0,0,0,,哈\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.21,0:15:01.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}(民兵)
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.57,0:15:06.86,Default,,0,0,0,,今晚 一位笑匠死在了纽约\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Tonight, a comedian died in New York.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.86,0:15:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,某人知道原因\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Somebody knows why.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.18,0:15:10.81,Default,,0,0,0,,某人知道\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Somebody knows.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.09,0:15:18.58,Default,,0,0,0,,不 我肯定听到了些动静\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}No, I definitely heard something.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.93,0:15:23.22,Default,,0,0,0,,看住门\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Watch the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.52,0:15:50.08,Default,,0,0,0,,嘘\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Shh.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.06,0:15:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,一定是风吹的 下次你…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Must've been the wind. Next time you...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.04,0:16:09.70,Default,,0,0,0,,全都是从那些帮派团伙开始的\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}MAN: It all started with the gangs.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.29,0:16:13.27,Default,,0,0,0,,你知道 大家往往忘记这点\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You know, people tend to forget that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.94,0:16:17.19,Default,,0,0,0,,海盗装扮、鬼魂\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Pirate outfits, ghosts.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.19,0:16:19.81,Default,,0,0,0,,他们以为那样好玩：装扮起来去打劫\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}They thought it was funny: Dress up and pull heists.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.32,0:16:24.37,Default,,0,0,0,,等我们逮捕了他们 他们即刻又回到街头\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}As soon as we'd arrest them, they'd be back on the street.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.37,0:16:28.37,Default,,0,0,0,,没人能指认出他们 因为有那些该死的面具\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Nobody could pick them out of a lineup because of the damn masks.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.37,0:16:30.81,Default,,0,0,0,,所以我们几个警察 聚在一起…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}So a few of us cops, we get together...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.81,0:16:34.35,Default,,0,0,0,,然后我们合计：见他的鬼吧 我们也蒙面\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...and we figure, what the heck, we'll mask up, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.35,0:16:37.06,Default,,0,0,0,,我们来了结法律无能为力的事情\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}We'll finish what the law couldn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.87,0:16:42.05,Default,,0,0,0,,很快 报纸也收到风声 他们跟风…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Pretty soon, the papers get wind of it. They ran with it...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.05,0:16:45.89,Default,,0,0,0,,噢 老天 我们是全民娱乐啊\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...and oh, boy, we're a national pastime.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.89,0:16:49.56,Default,,0,0,0,,那时有我、美钞、飞蛾侠…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}It was me, Dollar Bill, Mothman...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.56,0:16:53.10,Default,,0,0,0,,都会队长、兜帽判官…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...Captain Metropolis, Hooded Justice...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.10,0:16:56.47,Default,,0,0,0,,丝灵还有笑匠\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...Silk Spectre and the Comedian.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.47,0:17:00.01,Default,,0,0,0,,噢 别让我提到他\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Oh, don't get me started on him.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.16,0:17:06.38,Default,,0,0,0,,我一定喝醉了 又向你说起这件伤心事\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I must be drunk already, telling you this sob story again.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.38,0:17:08.22,Default,,0,0,0,,我想你是要表达一个观点\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I think you were trying to make a point.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.17,0:17:13.55,Default,,0,0,0,,好吧 我的观点是 我们起头太容易了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Well, my point is that we had it too easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.55,0:17:15.31,Default,,0,0,0,,发生在你们身上的事情不公平\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}It wasn't fair what happened to you guys...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.31,0:17:17.57,Default,,0,0,0,,你们接手的是我们留下的烂摊子\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You guys who picked up where we left off.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.57,0:17:19.61,Default,,0,0,0,,还有尼克松强迫你们引退\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}With Nixon forcing you out.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.68,0:17:22.44,Default,,0,0,0,,尼克松 噢 那个烂人\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Nixon, oh, that prick.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.08,0:17:25.12,Default,,0,0,0,,想想我五次投票给这烂人\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}To think I voted for that prick five times.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.12,0:17:28.05,Default,,0,0,0,,嘿 不选他就只有共产党了 对吧?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Hey, it was him or the commies, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.85,0:17:34.65,Default,,0,0,0,,噢 差不多到午夜了 该走了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Oh, wow, it's almost midnight. Gotta go.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.19,0:17:37.82,Default,,0,0,0,,要真话吗?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Truth?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.50,0:17:42.38,Default,,0,0,0,,你当夜枭比我当得更好 丹尼小子\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You were a better Nite Owl than I ever was, Danny boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.38,0:17:46.10,Default,,0,0,0,,- 霍利斯 我们都知道这是屁话 - 嘿！\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}- Hollis, we both know that's bullshit. - Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.10,0:17:47.72,Default,,0,0,0,,说这话注意点\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Watch it with the language.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.72,0:17:50.52,Default,,0,0,0,,这左勾拳曾打趴艾克西斯队长 记得吗?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}This is the left hook that floored Captain Axis, remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.52,0:17:52.08,Default,,0,0,0,,- 对啊 - 最新报道\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}- Yeah. WOMAN [ON TV]: This just in:
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.08,0:17:54.13,Default,,0,0,0,,那位被称作"罗夏"的蒙面义警…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}The masked vigilante known as Rorschach...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.13,0:17:57.01,Default,,0,0,0,,在凌晨时分袭击了一位警官\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}... has assaulted a police officer in the early-morning hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.88,0:18:00.72,Default,,0,0,0,,罗夏在联邦调查局的前十名统计名单上…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Rorschach is on the FBI's Ten Most Wanted list...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.72,0:18:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,因他违反6年前取缔蒙面英雄的"基恩法案"\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}... for violation of the Keene Act, which banned masked heroes six years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.00,0:18:07.29,Default,,0,0,0,,据报道罗夏不断地使…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Rorschach reportedly incapacitated...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.83,0:18:10.37,Default,,0,0,0,,强迫每个人退出却留下他\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Forced everyone out except him.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.37,0:18:12.08,Default,,0,0,0,,噢 他会退出的\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Oh, he'll quit.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.08,0:18:13.43,Default,,0,0,0,,在他死的时候\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}When he's dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.06,0:18:16.31,Default,,0,0,0,,- 下周见?  - 其实…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}DAN: Next week? HOLLIS: Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.31,0:18:20.53,Default,,0,0,0,,你看 你没必要一直这样陪我\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...you know, you don't have to keep humoring me like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.97,0:18:23.42,Default,,0,0,0,,如果你有个热辣的约会对象之类的…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}If you got a hot date or something...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.42,0:18:26.22,Default,,0,0,0,,嘿 我们退休人员应该常聚 对吧?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Hey, us retired guys have to stick together, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.01,0:18:29.85,Default,,0,0,0,,你怀念过那些日子吗?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You ever miss it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.08,0:18:33.14,Default,,0,0,0,,没 你呢?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}No. You?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.75,0:18:35.52,Default,,0,0,0,,噢 去它的 没\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Oh, heck, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.85,0:18:38.62,Default,,0,0,0,,回见了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Be seeing you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.98,0:18:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}(梅森汽修)
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.48,0:18:50.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}(专修老车)
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.08,0:18:57.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}(乡愁：由维特公司献上)
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.40,0:19:53.69,Default,,0,0,0,,你好 丹尼尔\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Hello, Daniel.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.43,0:19:55.52,Default,,0,0,0,,罗夏\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Rorschach.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.60,0:20:01.05,Default,,0,0,0,,给自己弄了些豆子 希望你别介意\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Helped myself to some beans. Hope you don't mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.05,0:20:03.51,Default,,0,0,0,,不 不 当然不介意\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}No, no. Course not.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.11,0:20:07.83,Default,,0,0,0,,你要我给你热热吗?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You want me to heat those up for you?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.83,0:20:09.37,Default,,0,0,0,,这样就好\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Fine like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.95,0:20:12.14,Default,,0,0,0,,最近在忙些什么?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}How have you been keeping?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.52,0:20:18.25,Default,,0,0,0,,不坐牢\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}RORSCHACH: Out of prison.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.02,0:20:22.25,Default,,0,0,0,,在新闻里听到你了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Heard about you on the news.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.86,0:20:25.24,Default,,0,0,0,,说你袭击了一个警察\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Say you attacked a cop.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.24,0:20:28.01,Default,,0,0,0,,轻伤 都不用住院治疗\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}RORSCHACH: Minor wound. Won't need hospitalization.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.90,0:20:30.05,Default,,0,0,0,,丹尼尔…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Daniel...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.05,0:20:31.53,Default,,0,0,0,,看看这个\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...Iook at this.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.31,0:20:39.94,Default,,0,0,0,,- 这是豆汁吗?  - 这是"人汁"\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}DAN: Is this bean juice? RORSCHACH: Human bean juice.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.64,0:20:45.14,Default,,0,0,0,,徽章是笑匠的 血也是 他死了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Badge belonged to the Comedian. Blood too. He's dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.15,0:20:48.62,Default,,0,0,0,,我们到下面谈吧\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Let's talk downstairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.53,0:20:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,可能是入室行窃\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}DAN: It could have been a burglary.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.44,0:21:02.31,Default,,0,0,0,,或许凶手不知道笑匠是谁\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Maybe the killer didn't know who the Comedian was.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.31,0:21:06.92,Default,,0,0,0,,一个普通入室窃贼? 杀了笑匠? 荒谬\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}RORSCHACH: An ordinary burglar? Kill the Comedian? Ridiculous.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.64,0:21:12.22,Default,,0,0,0,,我听说他从1977年一直为政府做事…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I heard he'd been working for the government since '77...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.22,0:21:15.56,Default,,0,0,0,,推翻南美洲的马克思主义共和国\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...knocking over Marxist republics in South America.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.56,0:21:18.66,Default,,0,0,0,,或许这是一起政治谋杀什么的\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Maybe it was a political killing or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.66,0:21:20.10,Default,,0,0,0,,或许\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Maybe.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.10,0:21:23.53,Default,,0,0,0,,或许有人正在除掉变装英雄\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Maybe someone's picking off costumed heroes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.53,0:21:25.80,Default,,0,0,0,,你不觉得有点被害妄想吗\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}DAN: You don't think that's a little paranoid?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.80,0:21:28.61,Default,,0,0,0,,他们是这样说我的吗\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}That what they say about me now?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.61,0:21:30.04,Default,,0,0,0,,被害妄想症\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Paranoid?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.04,0:21:33.04,Default,,0,0,0,,听着 笑匠在那些日子里树敌很多…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}DAN: Look, Comedian made a lot of enemies over the years...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.04,0:21:34.71,Default,,0,0,0,,甚至得罪了些朋友\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...even among his friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.71,0:21:36.87,Default,,0,0,0,,说起朋友 霍利斯·梅森还好吗?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}RORSCHACH: Speaking of friends, how's Hollis Mason?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.77,0:21:41.71,Default,,0,0,0,,他写了那本书 里面说了些笑匠的坏话\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}He wrote that book. Said some bad things about the Comedian in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.71,0:21:43.67,Default,,0,0,0,,我不喜欢你暗示的东西\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I don't like what you're implying,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.11,0:21:45.97,Default,,0,0,0,,另外我喜欢少被人跟踪\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}and I like being followed even less.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.51,0:21:48.99,Default,,0,0,0,,也许我是在照看着你\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Maybe I was keeping an eye on you
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.99,0:21:51.13,Default,,0,0,0,,以防万一有人在捕杀面具英雄\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}in case someone's gunning for masks.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.13,0:21:52.45,Default,,0,0,0,,你以前没这么感情用事\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You were never that sentimental.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.45,0:21:55.81,Default,,0,0,0,,袭击一个 就是袭击我们全部\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Attack on one is attack on all of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.25,0:21:58.69,Default,,0,0,0,,那你建议我们该干些什么?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}What do you suggest we do about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.59,0:22:00.72,Default,,0,0,0,,报复\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Retribution.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.16,0:22:03.72,Default,,0,0,0,,守望者已经完了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Watchmen are over.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.72,0:22:05.44,Default,,0,0,0,,狡猾的尼克松说的\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Says Tricky Dick.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.44,0:22:07.39,Default,,0,0,0,,我说的\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Says me.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.00,0:22:11.61,Default,,0,0,0,,没人知道你是谁\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Nobody knows who you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.61,0:22:14.92,Default,,0,0,0,,你可以放弃 试试过正常生活\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You can give it up, try and have a normal life.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.92,0:22:18.84,Default,,0,0,0,,就像你过的生活? 正常生活?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}That what you have now? A normal life?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.84,0:22:23.21,Default,,0,0,0,,当你走在狂犬病中垂死的城市街道上…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}When you walk down the street in a city dying of rabies...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.21,0:22:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,走过那些人形蟑螂…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...past the human cockroaches...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.00,0:22:27.93,Default,,0,0,0,,他们谈论着海洛因和儿童色情…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...talking about their heroin and child pornography...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.93,0:22:29.48,Default,,0,0,0,,你真觉得很正常吗?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...do you really feel normal?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.62,0:22:33.39,Default,,0,0,0,,至少我没有继续躲在面具后面\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Least I'm not the one still hiding behind a mask.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.26,0:22:36.52,Default,,0,0,0,,不\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}No.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.20,0:22:40.32,Default,,0,0,0,,你躲在大众这副面具后面\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You're hiding in plain sight.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.70,0:22:43.86,Default,,0,0,0,,回头见 丹\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Be seeing you, Dan.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.37,0:22:46.98,Default,,0,0,0,,有个维修竖井能出去 到北边两个街区外\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}A maintenance hatch will let you out two blocks north.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.98,0:22:48.89,Default,,0,0,0,,对 我还记得\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Yeah, I remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.89,0:22:50.82,Default,,0,0,0,,以前常来这里\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Came here often,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.82,0:22:53.12,Default,,0,0,0,,那时候我们还是搭档\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Came here often, when we were partners.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.12,0:22:55.04,Default,,0,0,0,,那的确是段好时光 罗夏\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Those were great times, huh, Rorschach?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.55,0:22:56.83,Default,,0,0,0,,后来怎么了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.83,0:22:58.78,Default,,0,0,0,,你退出了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You quit.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.71,0:23:23.59,Default,,0,0,0,,罗夏日记\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Rorschach's journal.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.59,0:23:26.09,Default,,0,0,0,,第一次访友无功而返\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}First visit of evening fruitless.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.09,0:23:28.23,Default,,0,0,0,,感觉有点低落\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Feel slightly depressed.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.75,0:23:30.79,Default,,0,0,0,,很快就会有战争\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Soon there will be war.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.79,0:23:34.53,Default,,0,0,0,,上百万的人会在疾病和痛苦中惨死\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Millions will perish in sickness and misery.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.53,0:23:37.11,Default,,0,0,0,,为什么一个人的死还比这么多人重要?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Why does one death matter against so many?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.82,0:23:42.77,Default,,0,0,0,,因为有好人有坏人 而坏人必须受到惩罚\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Because there is good and evil, and evil must be punished.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.77,0:23:45.78,Default,,0,0,0,,即使面对世界末日…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Even in the face of armageddon...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.78,0:23:48.79,Default,,0,0,0,,在这点上我也不会妥协\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}... I will not compromise in this.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.79,0:23:48.79,Default,,0,0,0,,[片段1插入点][0:23:48.79]
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.79,0:23:52.85,Default,,0,0,0,,但是有太多人还没得到报应\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}But there are so many deserving of retribution...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.85,0:23:55.13,Default,,0,0,0,,时间却太少\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}... and so little time.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.64,0:24:30.45,Default,,0,0,0,,船长\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}MAN: Captain.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.45,0:24:32.92,Default,,0,0,0,,- 船长 - 瑞德里\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}- Captain. - Ridley.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.92,0:24:36.09,Default,,0,0,0,,瑞德里 你看到其他的生还者了吗?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Ridley, have you seen any other survivors?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.09,0:24:37.46,Default,,0,0,0,,没有 长官\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}No, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.46,0:24:42.10,Default,,0,0,0,,船长 我的脚被些残骸卡住了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Captain, my foot is caught in some of the wreckage.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.10,0:24:45.49,Default,,0,0,0,,- 正在把我拽下去 - 撑住\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}- It's pulling me under. - Hold on.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.86,0:24:49.69,Default,,0,0,0,,瑞德里\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Ridley.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.77,0:25:03.24,Default,,0,0,0,,瑞德里\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Ridley. Ridley.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.87,0:25:05.16,Default,,0,0,0,,不\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}No.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.16,0:25:06.83,Default,,0,0,0,,不\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}No.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.21,0:25:09.63,Default,,0,0,0,,更多血 更多血 更多血\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}VOICES [CHANTING]: More blood, more blood, more blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.63,0:25:12.14,Default,,0,0,0,,在几乎溺亡的迷乱中 我看见了它\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}MARINER: Delirious from nearly drowning, I saw it.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.72,0:25:15.69,Default,,0,0,0,,黑货船\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}The Black Freighter.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.02,0:25:21.29,Default,,0,0,0,,这驶向地狱的船的黑色船帆 正对着东印度群岛那片黄色的天空\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}The hell-bound ship's black sails against the yellow Indies sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.86,0:25:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,我再次见识了火药、人脑浆和战争的恶臭\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I knew again the stench of powder and men's brains and war.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.53,0:25:32.70,Default,,0,0,0,,更多血 更多血 更多血\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}VOICES [CHANTING]: More blood, more blood, more blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.58,0:25:42.84,Default,,0,0,0,,更多血 更多血 更多血\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}More blood, more blood, more blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.02,0:25:50.75,Default,,0,0,0,,我身边的海浪是血红的…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}MARINER: The waves about me were scarlet...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.75,0:25:54.10,Default,,0,0,0,,…冒着泡沫 在黑货船号的航迹里透着可怕的温暖\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}... foaming, horribly warm in the Freighter's wake.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.10,0:25:57.44,Default,,0,0,0,,绝望中 我将自己风化的灵魂供给全能的上帝…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}In despair, I offered my weathered soul to almighty God...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.44,0:26:01.21,Default,,0,0,0,,…他的慈爱和他的审判\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}... his mercy and his judgment.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.21,0:26:02.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}(黑货船传奇)
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.50,0:26:04.25,Default,,0,0,0,,嗨 你觉得如何 小子?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}MAN: Heh. What do you think, kid?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.25,0:26:07.52,Default,,0,0,0,,我们应该核攻击苏联 让上帝去清理\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}We ought to nuke Russia and let God sort it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.52,0:26:10.75,Default,,0,0,0,,或者最低限度 让曼哈顿博士过去走一遭\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Or at the very least, send Dr. Manhattan over for a visit.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.75,0:26:12.42,Default,,0,0,0,,知道我的意思吗?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.42,0:26:15.49,Default,,0,0,0,,我是说 我不是想做一个混球之类的 但是他们…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I mean, I ain't trying to be an asshole or anything, but they're the ones...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.49,0:26:18.16,Default,,0,0,0,,…先打搅我们的 这只是我的个人意见\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...who are agitating us. Now this is just my opinion.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.16,0:26:21.62,Default,,0,0,0,,但我是一个卖报纸的 你知道 所以我了解信息\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}But I'm a news vendor, you know, so I am informed.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.39,0:26:25.90,Default,,0,0,0,,对 我知道 新边疆人报 呃 还没送到\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Yeah, I know. The New Frontiersman. Well, it's not here yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.90,0:26:27.90,Default,,0,0,0,,如果你不站在这瞎等的话 我会很感激的…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I'd appreciate if you didn't stand around waiting...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.90,0:26:30.67,Default,,0,0,0,,…因为我不知道什么时候会送到\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...because I don't know when it's going to be here.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.67,0:26:32.63,Default,,0,0,0,,我想你刚刚才说你了解信息的\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I thought you said you was informed.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.76,0:26:37.73,Default,,0,0,0,,- 你打算买下这个吗?  - 不\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}- Are you gonna buy that? - No.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.64,0:26:43.47,Default,,0,0,0,,噢 上帝 明天再来试试 好吗?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Oh, Jesus. Just try again tomorrow, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.30,0:26:53.30,Default,,0,0,0,,[片段1结束点][]
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.87,0:26:55.07,Default,,0,0,0,,维特先生\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}MAN: Mr. Veidt...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.07,0:26:57.37,Default,,0,0,0,,迄今为止 你是守望者当中唯一两位…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...to date, you're one of only two Watchmen...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.37,0:26:59.97,Default,,0,0,0,,向大众公开真实身份的成员之一\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...ever to reveal their true identity to the world...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.97,0:27:01.94,Default,,0,0,0,,第一位是霍利斯·梅森 (一代夜枭 写过关于守望者的书 前面那老人)\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...the first being Hollis Mason.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.94,0:27:05.11,Default,,0,0,0,,将自己超级英雄"法老王"的一面…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}And you've certainly profited greatly by it...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.11,0:27:10.55,Default,,0,0,0,,转变成亿万产业 你一定从中获益良多\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...turning your superhero alter ego, Ozymandias, into a billion-dollar industry:
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.55,0:27:13.62,Default,,0,0,0,,玩具、午餐盒 基因工程\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Toys, lunchboxes, genetic engineering.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.62,0:27:15.87,Default,,0,0,0,,我了解甚至有一部电影正在制作中\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I understand there's a movie in the works.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.87,0:27:18.12,Default,,0,0,0,,我没听到问问题 罗斯先生\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I'm not hearing a question, Mr. Roth.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.12,0:27:20.39,Default,,0,0,0,,抱歉 你是否想过…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}ROTH: I'm sorry. Do you think...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.39,0:27:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,守望者会因我贱卖他们的奋斗而憎恨我?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}The Watchmen resent me for prostituting their struggle?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.96,0:27:25.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\a6}(时事杂志：超人们为和平而联手)
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.96,0:27:25.88,Default,,0,0,0,,这是个合理的问题 是的 我曾这样想过\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}It's a fair question. Yes, it's crossed my mind...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.88,0:27:29.23,Default,,0,0,0,,某些过往的同事或许会这样看待我\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...some of my old colleagues might see it that way...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.23,0:27:32.42,Default,,0,0,0,,正如你也很清楚 有偏向的新闻报道…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...just as you're clearly aware that biased journalism...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.42,0:27:35.02,Default,,0,0,0,,让杂志更好卖\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...sells more magazines.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:35.53,0:27:40.44,Default,,0,0,0,,维特产业的销售正在资助我们跟曼哈顿博士合作的研究工作\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}The merchandising arm of Veidt Industries is funding our work with Dr. Manhattan.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.44,0:27:43.40,Default,,0,0,0,,最近我们扩大了在南极洲的研究设施\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}We recently expanded our research facility in Antarctica...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.40,0:27:46.95,Default,,0,0,0,,希望研发出便宜、可再生的能源\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...in the hope of developing cheap, renewable sources of energy...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.95,0:27:50.14,Default,,0,0,0,,这样我们可能结束全球对于石化燃料的依赖\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...that we might eliminate the world's reliance on fossil fuels.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.14,0:27:52.73,Default,,0,0,0,,好了 我们并不需要借助政治学者…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Now, it doesn't take a political scientist...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.73,0:27:56.31,Default,,0,0,0,,就能看到 我们与苏联的冷战并非意识形态\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...to see that our Cold War with the Russians isn't ideological...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.31,0:27:59.81,Default,,0,0,0,,而是基于惧怕 惧怕自己有的不够多\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...it's based upon fear. Fear of not having enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.18,0:28:04.03,Default,,0,0,0,,但如果我们让能源无限…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}But if we make resources infinite...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.03,0:28:06.30,Default,,0,0,0,,啊…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...ah...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.30,0:28:08.38,Default,,0,0,0,,我们就废掉了战争\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...we make war obsolete.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.26,0:28:13.09,Default,,0,0,0,,我希望其他的守望者们能明白这点\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I would hope the other Watchmen understand that...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.30,0:28:15.96,Default,,0,0,0,,不管他们现在身处何方\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...wherever they may be.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.07,0:28:19.43,Default,,0,0,0,,感谢你们抽空到来\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Thanks for your time.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.68,0:28:28.49,Default,,0,0,0,,- 你样子不错 阿德里安 - 丹\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}- You look good, Adrian. - Dan.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.49,0:28:30.74,Default,,0,0,0,,好久不见了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}It's been too long.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.74,0:28:32.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}(纽约公报："末日时钟" 指向午夜前5分钟)
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.22,0:28:36.54,Default,,0,0,0,,所以 罗夏认为有人在捕杀守望者 是吧?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}ADRIAN: So Rorschach thinks someone's hunting the Watchmen, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.22,0:28:39.08,Default,,0,0,0,,你认为可能吗?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You think it's possible?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.08,0:28:41.99,Default,,0,0,0,,统计学来讲 一桩谋杀并不等于一个趋势\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Statistically, one murder doesn't equal a trend.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.13,0:28:45.09,Default,,0,0,0,,罗夏是个反社会的人 丹\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Rorschach's a sociopath, Dan.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.73,0:28:49.10,Default,,0,0,0,,笑匠也是 他简直就是个纳粹\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}And so was the Comedian. He was practically a Nazi.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.93,0:28:52.12,Default,,0,0,0,,你比任何人都清楚这点\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You know that better than anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.12,0:28:54.48,Default,,0,0,0,,我来这里并不是因为我怀念他\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I'm not here because I miss him.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.48,0:28:55.99,Default,,0,0,0,,这件事让罗夏想到…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}It's occurred to Rorschach...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.99,0:28:58.98,Default,,0,0,0,,只有我们几个人知道彼此的身份\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...that we're the only ones who know each other's identities.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.48,0:29:01.57,Default,,0,0,0,,而实际上 全世界的人都知道你的\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Actually, the whole world knows yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.35,0:29:04.81,Default,,0,0,0,,所以我第一个要提醒你\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}That's why I'm warning you first.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.42,0:29:10.41,Default,,0,0,0,,谢谢你 丹\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Thank you, Dan...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.02,0:29:15.97,Default,,0,0,0,,但现在我害怕有更现实的东西需要担心…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...but I fear there's something much more real to worry about...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.97,0:29:18.59,Default,,0,0,0,,比罗夏的蒙面英雄杀手更可怕\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...than Rorschach's mask killer.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:20.10,0:29:24.63,Default,,0,0,0,,如果苏联人果然发射了核弹 乔恩真的可以阻止它们吗?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}If the Russians do launch their nukes, can Jon really stop them?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.63,0:29:28.59,Default,,0,0,0,,苏联人有5万1千枚核弹头储备\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}The Soviets have 51,000 warheads stockpiled.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.59,0:29:31.96,Default,,0,0,0,,就算乔恩拦截了其中的99%…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Even if Jon stops 99 percent of them...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.96,0:29:36.17,Default,,0,0,0,,那漏网的1%也还是能杀死地球上每一个活物\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...the 1 percent that get through could still kill every living thing on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.92,0:29:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,就算是曼哈顿博士也不能同时身处各方\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Even Dr. Manhattan can't be everywhere at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.95,0:29:52.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}(美国陆军洛克菲勒军事研究中心)
Dialogue: 0,0:29:55.53,0:30:01.32,Default,,0,0,0,,罗夏日记 10月13日 1985年\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Rorschach's journal, October 13th, 1985...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.32,0:30:03.67,Default,,0,0,0,,晚上8:30\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}... 8:30 p.m.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.21,0:30:08.46,Default,,0,0,0,,与德雷伯格(夜枭)会面之后 嘴里残留着不好的味道\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Meeting with Dreiberg left bad taste in mouth.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.46,0:30:12.54,Default,,0,0,0,,一个在自己地下室啜泣的软弱失败者\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}A flabby failure who sits whimpering in his basement.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.72,0:30:16.83,Default,,0,0,0,,为什么我们中只有几个人还在活跃…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Why are so few of us left active...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.83,0:30:21.87,Default,,0,0,0,,健康 没有人格缺陷?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}... healthy and without personality disorders?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.87,0:30:25.28,Default,,0,0,0,,第一任夜枭在经营一家汽修店\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}The first Nite Owl runs an auto-repair shop.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.28,0:30:28.85,Default,,0,0,0,,丝灵一世则成了一个臃肿的老妓女\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}The first Silk Spectre is a bloated, aging whore...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.85,0:30:31.88,Default,,0,0,0,,在加州的一处疗养胜地等死\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}... dying in a California rest resort.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.88,0:30:34.65,Default,,0,0,0,,美钞被一座旋转门夹住了斗篷…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Dollar Bill got his cape stuck in a revolving door...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.65,0:30:36.20,Default,,0,0,0,,然后在那里被枪杀了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}... where he got gunned down.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.81,0:30:39.24,Default,,0,0,0,,侧影 被害…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Silhouette, murdered...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.58,0:30:42.51,Default,,0,0,0,,成了她自己不检点生活方式的受害者\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}... a victim of her own indecent lifestyle.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.08,0:30:46.07,Default,,0,0,0,,飞蛾侠在缅因州的一所精神病院里\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Mothman's in an asylum in Maine.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.09,0:30:52.26,Default,,0,0,0,,还有阿德里安·维特\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Even Adrian Veidt,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.26,0:30:54.44,Default,,0,0,0,,可能是个同性恋\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}possible homosexual.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.44,0:30:57.11,Default,,0,0,0,,还需进一步调查\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Must investigate further.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.11,0:30:59.89,Default,,0,0,0,,我的名单里就剩两个人了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Only two names remain on my list.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.43,0:31:01.82,Default,,0,0,0,,俩人合住在洛克菲勒\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Both share private quarters
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.82,0:31:04.43,Default,,0,0,0,,军事研究中心的私人宿舍里\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}at Rockefeller Military Research Center.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.68,0:31:07.50,Default,,0,0,0,,我要去找他们\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I shall go to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.37,0:31:10.66,Default,,0,0,0,,我要去告诉那个坚不可摧的人\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I shall go tell the indestructible man
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.66,0:31:13.74,Default,,0,0,0,,有人要谋杀他\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}that someone plans to murder him.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.54,0:31:16.49,Default,,0,0,0,,晚上好 罗夏\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}JON: Good evening, Rorschach.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:16.49,0:31:18.53,Default,,0,0,0,,曼哈顿博士\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Dr. Manhattan,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.53,0:31:20.16,Default,,0,0,0,,你知道我为什么来\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}you know why I'm here.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.16,0:31:21.78,Default,,0,0,0,,是的…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}JON: Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.89,0:31:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,但你会失望地离开\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...but you're going to leave disappointed.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.00,0:31:26.14,Default,,0,0,0,,罗夏\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Rorschach.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.14,0:31:28.91,Default,,0,0,0,,你不该来这里 你是个通缉犯\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You shouldn't be here. You're a wanted man.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.91,0:31:31.27,Default,,0,0,0,,我也很高兴见到你 丝灵\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Nice to see you too, Silk Spectre.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.27,0:31:33.51,Default,,0,0,0,,我有个一直在用的真名\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I have a real name I've been using.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.51,0:31:34.71,Default,,0,0,0,,说说看\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Try it.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.71,0:31:36.98,Default,,0,0,0,,你说了算 劳瑞\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Whatever you say, Laurie.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.98,0:31:38.38,Default,,0,0,0,,你来这做什么?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}What are you doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.38,0:31:40.88,Default,,0,0,0,,笑匠死了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}JON: The Comedian is dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.88,0:31:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,罗夏希望我观察我的未来…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Rorschach wants me to look into my future...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.34,0:31:45.96,Default,,0,0,0,,去看看那杀手会不会被公开指认\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...see if the killer is ever publicly identified.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.96,0:31:49.07,Default,,0,0,0,,我已经警告过德雷伯格了 现在来警告你\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Already warned Dreiberg. Came to warn you too.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.78,0:31:54.15,Default,,0,0,0,,就算我愿意帮忙…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Even if I wanted to help...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.75,0:31:58.65,Default,,0,0,0,,我的未来已经被某种时空干扰遮住了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...my future is blocked by some kind of temporal interference.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:59.06,0:32:00.70,Default,,0,0,0,,我无法看清\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I cannot see it clearly.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.70,0:32:03.27,Default,,0,0,0,,干扰? 什么引起的?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Interference? Caused by what?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.27,0:32:06.69,Default,,0,0,0,,最有可能是因为核灾难\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}In all likelihood, nuclear holocaust.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.43,0:32:11.68,Default,,0,0,0,,如果美国和苏联全面开战…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}If the United States and Soviet Union engage in all-out war...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.68,0:32:15.85,Default,,0,0,0,,引发的冲击波 会产生超光速粒子\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...the resulting blast wave would produce a sudden burst of tachyons...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.85,0:32:20.83,Default,,0,0,0,,这些粒子能沿着你们眼中的时间逆向运动\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...particles which travel backward through what you perceive as time...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.48,0:32:24.81,Default,,0,0,0,,从而模糊了我现在的视觉影像\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...therefore obscuring my vision of the present.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.62,0:32:27.16,Default,,0,0,0,,我必须回去工作了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I must return to my work.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:27.16,0:32:28.46,Default,,0,0,0,,等一等\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}RORSCHACH: Wait a minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.46,0:32:31.13,Default,,0,0,0,,万一正是这个原因有人要清除我们呢?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}What if that's why someone wants us out of the way?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.13,0:32:33.54,Default,,0,0,0,,这样我们就不能做什么来阻止他了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}So we can't do anything to stop it?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.54,0:32:35.54,Default,,0,0,0,,再见 罗夏\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Goodbye, Rorschach.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.54,0:32:37.82,Default,,0,0,0,,费了好大工夫进来见你们…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}RORSCHACH: Took a lot of effort to get in here to see you.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:37.82,0:32:39.15,Default,,0,0,0,,我是不会走的…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I'm not leaving...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.60,0:32:42.93,Default,,0,0,0,,要把话说完才行\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}- till I've had my say.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.44,0:32:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,看起来这些日子有很多事情你没有告诉我\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Seems like there's a lot of things you don't tell me these days.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.52,0:32:56.24,Default,,0,0,0,,我不想过早让你担心\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I didn't wanna worry you prematurely.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.71,0:33:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,如果阿德里安和我能解决这场能源危机 战争也许能避免\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}If Adrian and I can solve the energy crisis, war may be averted.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.00,0:33:03.08,Default,,0,0,0,,但你总是说时间是同步的\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}LAURIE: But you always say time is simultaneous.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.79,0:33:06.80,Default,,0,0,0,,如果是这样 那你如何改变未来?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}If that's true, then how can you change the future?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.80,0:33:11.98,Default,,0,0,0,,但愿你能和我一样感知时间\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}If only you could perceive time as I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.98,0:33:13.10,Default,,0,0,0,,请允许我向你展示\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Please let me show you.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.24,0:33:22.24,Default,,0,0,0,,魔法 梦想 那就是我以前拥有的\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Magic. Dreams. That is what I had before.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.24,0:33:24.59,Default,,0,0,0,,我曾经是个英雄 该死的\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I was a hero, goddamn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.59,0:33:26.40,Default,,0,0,0,,你变老又不是我的错\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}It's not my fault you got old.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.40,0:33:27.50,Default,,0,0,0,,你有什么可抱怨的?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}What do you have to complain about?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.50,0:33:29.77,Default,,0,0,0,,是我在供养你和你的小孩\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I'm putting food on the table for you and your child.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.77,0:33:31.18,Default,,0,0,0,,你怎么不打电话给你的朋友艾迪\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Why don't you call your friend Eddie.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.18,0:33:32.65,Default,,0,0,0,,也许他能给你更好的生活\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Maybe he can give you a better life.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.65,0:33:36.12,Default,,0,0,0,,那是个错误 就那一次\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}It was a mistake. One time.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.12,0:33:37.25,Default,,0,0,0,,那个想要强奸你的男人…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Man tries to rape you...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.25,0:33:38.45,Default,,0,0,0,,停止\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.72,0:33:41.34,Default,,0,0,0,,你的思绪总是走向黑暗的地方…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Your mind goes to dark places...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.34,0:33:43.69,Default,,0,0,0,,而你还好奇我为什么把坏事瞒着你\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...and you wonder why I keep the worst from you.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.63,0:33:49.27,Default,,0,0,0,,替我向丹问好\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Say hello to Dan for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.63,0:33:50.70,Default,,0,0,0,,什么?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}What?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:52.84,0:33:55.63,Default,,0,0,0,,你想要求我和你去吃晚餐…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You wanna ask me to go to dinner with you...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.34,0:33:59.50,Default,,0,0,0,,就像我们以前一样…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...like we used to...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.11,0:34:02.07,Default,,0,0,0,,但你不会\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...but you won't.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.85,0:34:05.11,Default,,0,0,0,,你知道我不能去的\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You know I can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.75,0:34:10.01,Default,,0,0,0,,所以你给丹打电话…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}So you'll call Dan...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:10.45,0:34:12.65,Default,,0,0,0,,这样是最自然的\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...which is only natural.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:12.99,0:34:15.58,Default,,0,0,0,,你应该得到一位老朋友的慰籍\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You deserve the comfort of an old friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.89,0:34:51.42,Default,,0,0,0,,丹·德雷伯格的桌位\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}LAURIE: Dan Dreiberg's table.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.58,0:35:16.35,Default,,0,0,0,,- 你知道他和H·J是… - 我完全不知道\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}DAN: Did you know that he and H.J. Were...? I had no idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.85,0:35:20.07,Default,,0,0,0,,你还记得那个疯子吗? 他怎么称呼自己来着?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You remember that crazy guy? What'd he call himself?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.07,0:35:21.74,Default,,0,0,0,,屠杀队长\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Captain Carnage.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.74,0:35:24.94,Default,,0,0,0,,他总是假装是个超级恶棍 好让自己被暴打一顿\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Used to pretend he was a supervillain just so he could get beat up?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:24.94,0:35:27.53,Default,,0,0,0,,是啊 他找过我一次 我没理他\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Yeah, he tried that on me once. I just walked away.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:27.53,0:35:30.88,Default,,0,0,0,,于是他光天化日跟着我走了整条街…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}He starts following me down the street in broad daylight...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:30.88,0:35:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,喊着："惩罚我吧！惩罚我吧！"\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...yelling, "Punish me! Punish me!"
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.92,0:35:36.46,Default,,0,0,0,,我只说道："不 滚开。"\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I'm just saying, "No, get lost."
Dialogue: 0,0:35:37.61,0:35:40.04,Default,,0,0,0,,天啊 后来他怎么了?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}God, whatever happened to him?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.04,0:35:42.56,Default,,0,0,0,,噢 嗯 后来他去惹罗夏了…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Oh. Um... He pulled that on Rorschach...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:42.56,0:35:44.98,Default,,0,0,0,,罗夏就把他扔下了电梯井\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...and Rorschach dropped him down an elevator shaft.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.45,0:35:53.85,Default,,0,0,0,,哦 天啊 这可就不好笑了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Oh, my God. That's not even funny.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.56,0:35:57.05,Default,,0,0,0,,- 还是有点好笑的 - 嗯\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}- It's a little funny. - Yep.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.96,0:36:01.08,Default,,0,0,0,,很庆幸我点了四腿鸡\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}WOMAN: I'm glad I ordered the four-legged chicken.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.08,0:36:03.07,Default,,0,0,0,,能再见到你真的很好\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}It's really good to see you again.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.30,0:36:05.82,Default,,0,0,0,,见到你也很高兴\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}It's great seeing you too.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.64,0:36:09.16,Default,,0,0,0,,我们为什么会那样做 丹? 像那样子的变装\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Why'd we do it, Dan? Dress up like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.31,0:36:13.79,Default,,0,0,0,,- 没有别人会那样 - 是啊 你还记得我的装束吗?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}- No one else would. - Yeah, but do you remember my costume?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.79,0:36:17.06,Default,,0,0,0,,全身的束身橡胶 我说 那真糟糕\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}All that tight latex? I mean, it was awful.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.06,0:36:20.04,Default,,0,0,0,,啊 是啊 糟糕\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Uh... Yeah, yeah, awful.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.04,0:36:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,但我那时不想让妈妈失望\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}But didn't wanna disappoint Mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.80,0:36:26.81,Default,,0,0,0,,她想我成为像她一样的人 打击坏人\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Wanted her little girl to be just like her and fight bad guys.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.49,0:36:31.09,Default,,0,0,0,,我想 "基恩法案"是发生在我们身上最好的事情了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I think the Keene Act was the best thing that ever happened to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.16,0:36:34.53,Default,,0,0,0,,哦 反正这样我们会活得长久些\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Well, we'll live longer anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:37.83,0:36:38.90,Default,,0,0,0,,怎么了?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}What?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:40.34,0:36:44.83,Default,,0,0,0,,乔恩认为 如果他做点什么的话…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Jon thinks, unless he can do something about it, that...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.68,0:36:47.70,Default,,0,0,0,,就会有一场核战争\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...there's gonna be nuclear war.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.18,0:36:49.67,Default,,0,0,0,,很快\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.55,0:36:54.03,Default,,0,0,0,,但我不知道该怎么想 我是说…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}But I don't know what to think. I mean, it's all...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.03,0:36:57.27,Default,,0,0,0,,他的世界都是量子力学、平行现实之类的\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...quantum mechanics and parallel realities with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.27,0:37:00.05,Default,,0,0,0,,我从不了解他实际看到的宇宙\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I never even know what universe he's actually seeing.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.36,0:37:04.49,Default,,0,0,0,,他不停地离我远去…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}He just keeps getting further away from me.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.19,0:37:06.86,Default,,0,0,0,,和其他人也一样\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:07.80,0:37:10.55,Default,,0,0,0,,我甚至不能确定他是否还在乎我…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I can't even tell if he actually cares about me anymore...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.55,0:37:12.53,Default,,0,0,0,,或者他只是在假装\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...or if he's just pretending.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.54,0:37:16.47,Default,,0,0,0,,如果他假装的话 那说明他还在乎\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}If he's pretending, it means he cares.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:21.21,0:37:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,等等 我给你开门\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Hold on, I'll get the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.55,0:37:26.34,Default,,0,0,0,,谢谢 丹\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Thanks, Dan.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.72,0:37:28.74,Default,,0,0,0,,- 坐好了?  - 对\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}- Got it? - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.16,0:37:36.90,Default,,0,0,0,,你吃晚餐总是有政府护卫吗?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You always get a government escort to dinner?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:37.86,0:37:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,他们是要确定我不会做什么事情 让本国最强大的武器烦心\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}They're making sure I don't do anything to upset the country's most powerful weapon.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:43.70,0:37:44.92,Default,,0,0,0,,我很抱歉\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.92,0:37:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,我约你出来吃饭 叙旧 说笑…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I invite you out to dinner to catch up and have a few laughs...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.37,0:37:52.89,Default,,0,0,0,,但看起来这些日子并没有多少可谈笑的事\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...but there don't seem to be many laughs around these days.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:52.89,0:37:56.71,Default,,0,0,0,,还能期待些什么呢? 笑匠都死了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}What do you expect? The Comedian's dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.32,0:38:02.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an9}(BGM: The Sound Of Silence)
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.08,0:39:40.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}(棕榈泉报：苏联提高核弹头产量)
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.25,0:39:43.81,Default,,0,0,0,,劳瑞 是你吗?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Laurie? Is that you?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.52,0:39:49.49,Default,,0,0,0,,还以为你现在已经习惯这种旅行方式了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Thought you'd be used to traveling that way by now.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:50.16,0:39:54.17,Default,,0,0,0,,我不习惯 我讨厌乔恩传送我\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Well, I'm not. I hate it when Jon teleports me.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.17,0:39:57.20,Default,,0,0,0,,那也比经济舱强\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Well, it beats flying coach.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:57.57,0:39:59.78,Default,,0,0,0,,来点玛格丽塔?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Margarita?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:59.78,0:40:01.96,Default,,0,0,0,,母亲 现在是下午2点\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Mother, it's 2:00 in the afternoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.67,0:40:06.14,Default,,0,0,0,,嗯\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Mm.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:06.81,0:40:09.11,Default,,0,0,0,,还记得那个一直给我写信的家伙吗?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Remember that guy that writes me letters?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.48,0:40:12.77,Default,,0,0,0,,他寄给我一件纪念品 是一本提华纳圣经\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}He sent me an item of memorabilia. It's a Tijuana bible.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.77,0:40:17.27,Default,,0,0,0,,三四十年年代流行的8页色情漫画\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}This little eight-page porno comic they did in the '30s and '40s.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.27,0:40:18.45,Default,,0,0,0,,他寄给你这个?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}He sent you this?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.45,0:40:21.31,Default,,0,0,0,,是啊 这很值钱的 算是古董了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Sure. They're very valuable, like antiques.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.12,0:40:23.83,Default,,0,0,0,,母亲 这东西太恶心了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Mother, this is gross.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.83,0:40:26.41,Default,,0,0,0,,我倒觉得这是某种恭维\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I think it's kind of flattering.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:26.41,0:40:28.69,Default,,0,0,0,,为什么你生气的时候总是叫我"母亲"\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Why do you always call me Mother when you're mad?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.07,0:40:34.13,Default,,0,0,0,,我知道你为什么来 我还能认字 知道吗?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I know why you're here. I can still read, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:34.90,0:40:37.13,Default,,0,0,0,,我在报纸看到了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I saw it in the paper.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:37.81,0:40:40.71,Default,,0,0,0,,艾迪·布雷克的葬礼就在今天\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Eddie Blake's funeral is today.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:42.51,0:40:45.50,Default,,0,0,0,,他终于说出了点睛妙语 我猜想\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Finally got his punchline, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:45.98,0:40:47.25,Default,,0,0,0,,可怜的艾迪\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Poor Eddie.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:47.25,0:40:48.81,Default,,0,0,0,,可怜的艾迪? 他都那样对你了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Poor Eddie? After what he did to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:49.52,0:40:51.06,Default,,0,0,0,,噢 劳瑞 你还年轻\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Oh, Laurie, you're still young.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:51.82,0:40:53.90,Default,,0,0,0,,你不了解\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:53.90,0:40:55.69,Default,,0,0,0,,世事无常\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Things change.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.53,0:40:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,无论发生了什么 都是40年前的事了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}What happened happened 40 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.44,0:41:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,我已经67岁了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I'm 67 years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:02.88,0:41:07.10,Default,,0,0,0,,每一天 未来都变得暗淡\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Every day, the future looks a little bit darker.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:07.94,0:41:10.10,Default,,0,0,0,,但是过去…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}But the past...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:10.61,0:41:13.60,Default,,0,0,0,,即使是最肮脏的部分…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...even the grimy parts of it...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.14,0:41:16.77,Default,,0,0,0,,却越来越明亮\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...keep on getting brighter.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:22.28,0:41:25.12,Default,,0,0,0,,我眼睛被闪到了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I've got spots in my eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.59,0:41:30.95,Default,,0,0,0,,别这样 艾迪\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Stop it, Eddie.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:32.23,0:41:35.60,Default,,0,0,0,,- 谢谢了 维基 - 谢谢 夜枭先生\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}- Thank you, Weegee. - Thank you, Mr. Owl.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:36.80,0:41:40.15,Default,,0,0,0,,明天 3点 我的工作室\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Tomorrow, 3:00, my studio.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:40.15,0:41:43.03,Default,,0,0,0,,- 在第21街的一个小地方 - 听起来不错\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}- Little place on 21 st. - Sounds good.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:43.51,0:41:48.10,Default,,0,0,0,,哇 我们的合影 不知道我的头发上镜不\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}SALLY: Wow, a real photo session. Wonder how my hair will look?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:50.41,0:41:53.61,Default,,0,0,0,,噢 你先走吧 我5分钟就好\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Oh, go ahead. I'll be there in five.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:10.10,0:42:11.14,Default,,0,0,0,,艾迪\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Eddie.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:12.20,0:42:16.42,Default,,0,0,0,,你在这里干什么? 你知道我在换衣服\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}What the hell are you doing here? You knew I was changing.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.42,0:42:18.03,Default,,0,0,0,,我当然知道\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Sure I did.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:19.68,0:42:21.27,Default,,0,0,0,,来吧 宝贝\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Come on, baby.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:21.71,0:42:23.70,Default,,0,0,0,,我知道你需要什么\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I know what you need.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:23.70,0:42:27.95,Default,,0,0,0,,你穿这么一套衣服 肯定有某些原因的\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You gotta have some kind of reason for dressing in an outfit like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.95,0:42:30.42,Default,,0,0,0,,我说不要 艾迪\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I said no, Eddie.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:31.05,0:42:32.74,Default,,0,0,0,,不要就是要\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}No spelled Y-E-S.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:32.74,0:42:35.96,Default,,0,0,0,,不要就是不要\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}No spelled N-O.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.35,0:42:37.12,Default,,0,0,0,,别这样\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}All right?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.12,0:42:38.69,Default,,0,0,0,,来吧 宝贝\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Come on, sweetheart.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:43.34,0:42:45.09,Default,,0,0,0,,艾迪…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Eddie...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:25.94,0:43:28.67,Default,,0,0,0,,你个小畜生\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You little bastard.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:35.28,0:43:36.47,Default,,0,0,0,,这就是你喜欢的?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}This is what you like?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.47,0:43:38.94,Default,,0,0,0,,- 这样让你显得性感?  - 什么?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}- This what makes you hot? - What?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.47,0:43:52.82,Default,,0,0,0,,世事处处维艰 甜心\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Things are tough all over, cupcake.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:52.82,0:43:57.09,Default,,0,0,0,,正义不正义 雨点照样落下\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}It rains on the just and the unjust alike.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:57.09,0:44:00.94,Default,,0,0,0,,笑匠有点正邪均沾\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}The Comedian was a little bit of both.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:02.41,0:44:05.97,Default,,0,0,0,,而他一向认为自己是笑到最后的人\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}And he always thought he'd get the last laugh.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:06.32,0:44:09.38,Default,,0,0,0,,全知的主啊 我们内心的秘密\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}MAN: Thou knowest, Lord, the secrets of our hearts.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:09.99,0:44:13.47,Default,,0,0,0,,请用你那慈爱的耳 聆听我们的祷告…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Shut not thy merciful ears to our prayers...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:13.47,0:44:18.10,Default,,0,0,0,,宽恕我们吧 至圣之主 全能之主…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...but spare us, Lord most holy, O God most mighty...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:18.10,0:44:21.32,Default,,0,0,0,,噢 神圣而仁慈的主\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...O holy and merciful savior.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:22.00,0:44:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,你那最可畏惧的永恒审判\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Thou most worthy judge eternal.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:24.88,0:44:28.11,Default,,0,0,0,,在我们生命的最后时刻 请不要让痛苦降临\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Suffer us not at our last hour for any...
Dialogue: 0,0:45:55.19,0:45:57.93,Default,,0,0,0,,烟花 你跟我逗乐呢\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}EDDIE: Fireworks. You gotta be kidding me.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:57.93,0:46:02.53,Default,,0,0,0,,你看 本以为这该死的国家已经受够了烟火\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You know, you'd think this goddamn country had had enough fireworks.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:03.43,0:46:06.18,Default,,0,0,0,,知道吗 如果我们在越南输了…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You know, if we'd lost here in Vietnam...
Dialogue: 0,0:46:06.18,0:46:11.16,Default,,0,0,0,,我想我们会被逼疯的 你懂的 我们这个国家\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...I think it might have driven us crazy. You know, as a country.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:11.94,0:46:15.64,Default,,0,0,0,,但我们没有输 多亏了你\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}But we didn't, thanks to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:17.61,0:46:19.70,Default,,0,0,0,,你话说得苦涩\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You sound bitter.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:19.70,0:46:21.39,Default,,0,0,0,,我? 苦涩?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Me? Bitter?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:21.39,0:46:24.77,Default,,0,0,0,,操 并不 我认为是搞笑\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Fuck, no. I think it's hilarious.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:30.78,0:46:32.94,Default,,0,0,0,,噢 老天爷\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Oh, Jesus Christ.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:32.94,0:46:36.11,Default,,0,0,0,,- 艾迪先生  - 来得真他妈是时候\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}- Mr. Eddie? - Just what I fucking needed.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:36.11,0:46:41.19,Default,,0,0,0,,战争结束了 我们必须谈谈这个孩子\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}The war is over now. We must talk about this baby.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:41.97,0:46:45.65,Default,,0,0,0,,没什么可谈的 瞧 我要离开了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}There's nothing to talk about. See, I'm leaving.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:45.65,0:46:47.16,Default,,0,0,0,,我会把你忘掉的…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I'm gonna forget about you...
Dialogue: 0,0:46:47.16,0:46:50.01,Default,,0,0,0,,连同你这令人讨厌、湿热、一坨烂屎样的国家\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...and your horrible, sweaty, little piece-of-shit country.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:50.58,0:46:51.74,Default,,0,0,0,,他妈的滚出去\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Get the fuck out of here.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:53.48,0:46:55.50,Default,,0,0,0,,- 不  - 给我滚开\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}- No. - Get the fuck out of here.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:55.50,0:46:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,你会记得的\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You will remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:58.47,0:47:01.38,Default,,0,0,0,,你会记得我和我的国家…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You will remember me and my country...
Dialogue: 0,0:47:02.26,0:47:03.88,Default,,0,0,0,,永远！\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...forever!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:06.50,0:47:08.36,Default,,0,0,0,,我的脸！\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}My face!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:10.40,0:47:11.73,Default,,0,0,0,,布雷克 不！\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Blake. Don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:12.53,0:47:13.83,Default,,0,0,0,,布雷克！\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Blake!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:20.53,0:47:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,她怀着孩子…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}She was pregnant...
Dialogue: 0,0:47:24.48,0:47:26.36,Default,,0,0,0,,但你却枪杀了她\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...and you gunned her down.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:26.36,0:47:27.80,Default,,0,0,0,,没错\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}That's right...
Dialogue: 0,0:47:27.80,0:47:29.90,Default,,0,0,0,,你知道吗? 你看着我干的\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...and you know what? You watched me.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:29.90,0:47:33.07,Default,,0,0,0,,你本可以把我的枪变成蒸汽 子弹化成水银…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You could have turned the gun to steam, the bullets to mercury...
Dialogue: 0,0:47:33.07,0:47:36.68,Default,,0,0,0,,把那酒瓶变成该死的雪花片 但你没有这么做 不是吗?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...the bottle into goddamn snowflakes, but you didn't, did you?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:38.63,0:47:41.46,Default,,0,0,0,,你真正半点不关心人类\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You really don't give a damn about human beings.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:42.63,0:47:45.46,Default,,0,0,0,,你正在飞升到世人不可触及 博士\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You're drifting out of touch, doc.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:47.04,0:47:49.23,Default,,0,0,0,,愿上帝救助我们\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}God help us all.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:51.24,0:47:52.54,Default,,0,0,0,,医务兵！\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Medic!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:59.38,0:48:02.54,Default,,0,0,0,,至圣至仁之主啊\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}MAN: Most holy and merciful savior.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:03.49,0:48:08.54,Default,,0,0,0,,他来了又去 如同花开花谢\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}He cometh up and is cut down, like a flower.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:08.54,0:48:12.91,Default,,0,0,0,,在生命之中途 我们遭遇死亡\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}In the midst of life, we are in death.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:12.91,0:48:17.23,Default,,0,0,0,,除了你 我们还能往何处寻求援助 我的主啊\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Of whom may we seek succor, but of thee, O Lord?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:21.64,0:48:24.85,Default,,0,0,0,,欢迎 我们很快开始\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Welcome. We'll be starting shortly.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:24.85,0:48:26.97,Default,,0,0,0,,我们还在等一个人\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}We're waiting for one more.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:37.75,0:48:41.09,Default,,0,0,0,,我说过 你不是这里唯一精心装扮的人\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I told you, you wouldn't be the only one dressed up.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:42.72,0:48:44.12,Default,,0,0,0,,欢迎你 博士\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Welcome, doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:44.56,0:48:46.20,Default,,0,0,0,,现在可以开始了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Now we can start.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:46.20,0:48:47.65,Default,,0,0,0,,感谢你们今天到来\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Thank you for coming today.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:47.65,0:48:50.47,Default,,0,0,0,,我要求过你们 要让自己熟知这张罪案高发区地图\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I asked you to acquaint yourselves with this map of high-crime areas.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:50.47,0:48:51.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}(苏联称曼哈顿博士为"帝国主义者的武器")
Dialogue: 0,0:48:51.56,0:48:52.69,Default,,0,0,0,,这全是胡扯\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}This is all bullshit.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:53.14,0:48:55.71,Default,,0,0,0,,你看 对于一个称自己为笑匠的人\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You know, for a guy who calls himself the Comedian
Dialogue: 0,0:48:56.20,0:48:57.88,Default,,0,0,0,,我从来区分不出你开玩笑的时候\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I can never tell when you're joking.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:57.88,0:49:01.47,Default,,0,0,0,,守望者 真正是一个笑话\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Watchmen. That's the real joke.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:01.47,0:49:04.56,Default,,0,0,0,,15年前它就没有作用 现在也不会有作用…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}It didn't work 15 years ago, and it ain't gonna work now...
Dialogue: 0,0:49:04.56,0:49:06.72,Default,,0,0,0,,因为你们想玩牛仔和印第安人的游戏\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...because you wanna play cowboys and Indians.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:06.72,0:49:09.25,Default,,0,0,0,,或许我们应该同意开会时不能喝酒\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Maybe we should agree on no drinking at meetings.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:10.89,0:49:14.54,Default,,0,0,0,,罗夏和我联手 已经在黑帮问题上取得进展\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Rorschach and I have made headway on the gang problem by working together.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:14.54,0:49:17.35,Default,,0,0,0,,这么大规模的团队 看来像是要作秀\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}A group this size seems like a publicity stunt.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:17.87,0:49:19.32,Default,,0,0,0,,我加入可不是为了宣传\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I'm not in it for the ink.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:19.32,0:49:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,,我们能做的有很多\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}ADRIAN: We can do so much more.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:21.28,0:49:23.63,Default,,0,0,0,,我们可以拯救这个世界…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}We can save this world...
Dialogue: 0,0:49:25.23,0:49:28.40,Default,,0,0,0,,- 如果有正确的领导层  - 是啊\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...with the right leadership. - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:30.77,0:49:32.69,Default,,0,0,0,,那就是你喽 对吧 奥兹(法老王)?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}And that'd be you, right, Ozzy?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:32.69,0:49:35.70,Default,,0,0,0,,我是说 见鬼 你是地球上最聪明的人\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I mean, hell, you're the smartest man on the planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:35.70,0:49:38.31,Default,,0,0,0,,不需要天才也能看得出这世界有问题\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}It doesn't take a genius to see the world has problems.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:38.68,0:49:42.34,Default,,0,0,0,,对 但需要一屋子的蠢蛋以为自己够弱小 才能让你掌控\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Yeah, but it takes a room of morons to think they're small enough for you to handle.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:42.85,0:49:44.01,Default,,0,0,0,,你们这帮人\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You people.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:44.01,0:49:47.64,Default,,0,0,0,,你们听说摩罗神回到城里了 就全都激动起来\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You hear Moloch's back in town, get your panties all in a bunch.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:47.64,0:49:50.66,Default,,0,0,0,,- 你认为抓住他很重要?  - 正义很重要！\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}- You think catching him matters? - Justice matters.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:52.18,0:49:53.36,Default,,0,0,0,,正义\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Justice.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:54.66,0:49:56.85,Default,,0,0,0,,正义就要伸张到我们头上来了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Justice is coming to all of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:56.85,0:49:58.33,Default,,0,0,0,,不管我们他妈的做什么\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}No matter what the fuck we do.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:59.07,0:50:03.15,Default,,0,0,0,,你知道 人类自有史以来就不断地自相残杀\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You know, mankind's been trying to kill each other off since the beginning of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:03.15,0:50:08.22,Default,,0,0,0,,而现在 我们终于有了了结这项工作的力量\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Now we finally have the power to finish the job.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:08.22,0:50:11.87,Default,,0,0,0,,一旦那些核弹开始飞行 什么事都不再重要了 我们都成尘土\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Ain't nothing gonna matter once those nukes start flying. We'll all be dust.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:15.02,0:50:17.04,Default,,0,0,0,,然后这位法老王…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Then Ozymandias here...
Dialogue: 0,0:50:18.05,0:50:20.32,Default,,0,0,0,,将成为废墟里最聪明的人\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...will be the smartest man on the cinder.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:29.23,0:50:31.29,Default,,0,0,0,,全能的上帝…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}MAN: For as much as it hath pleased...
Dialogue: 0,0:50:32.02,0:50:36.43,Default,,0,0,0,,一视同仁地乐于接纳我们已故兄弟的灵魂…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...almighty God to take onto himself the soul of our dear departed brother...
Dialogue: 0,0:50:37.84,0:50:42.06,Default,,0,0,0,,让我们就此把他的身体埋藏吧\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...let us therefore commit his body to the ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:42.06,0:50:45.54,Default,,0,0,0,,土归土 尘归尘\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Earth to earth, ashes to ashes...
Dialogue: 0,0:50:50.15,0:50:51.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\a6}(警察说：让他们去做吧)
Dialogue: 0,0:50:55.47,0:51:00.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an7}(要警徽 不要面具)
Dialogue: 0,0:51:10.83,0:51:15.57,Default,,0,0,0,,我们要警察! 保护人民的警察!\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Police! Police to protect the people!
Dialogue: 0,0:51:20.23,0:51:24.30,Default,,0,0,0,,注意 市民们 我们正努力维持秩序\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}DAN: Attention, citizens. We are trying to maintain order.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:24.30,0:51:28.74,Default,,0,0,0,,你们必须离开街头 直到警察罢工结束\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You must clear the streets until the police strike is over.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:28.74,0:51:32.09,Default,,0,0,0,,如果你们能… 好了 没有必要使用暴力\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}If you could... Please, there's no need for violence.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:33.06,0:51:37.17,Default,,0,0,0,,我们是来恢复街头秩序的 直到警察罢工结束\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}We are trying to retain order on the streets until the police strike is over.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:37.17,0:51:39.54,Default,,0,0,0,,爬回你们的洞穴 免得受伤\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Crawl back in your holes before you get hurt.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:39.54,0:51:42.02,Default,,0,0,0,,- 我有橡胶子弹 - 我们有自己的权利\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}- I got rubber bullets. MAN 1: I want my rights!
Dialogue: 0,0:51:42.02,0:51:44.67,Default,,0,0,0,,- 你们不是法律！ - 我们要正常警察！\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}- You are not the law! MAN 2: We want regular cops!
Dialogue: 0,0:51:44.67,0:51:46.25,Default,,0,0,0,,不需要义警！\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}No more vigilantes!
Dialogue: 0,0:51:46.25,0:51:49.74,Default,,0,0,0,,我儿子就是警察 你个死基佬\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}My son's a police officer, you fucking faggots!
Dialogue: 0,0:51:51.45,0:51:54.27,Default,,0,0,0,,该死的 好吧 你们想这么做吗?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Goddamn it. All right. That's how you wanna do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:05.99,0:52:07.82,Default,,0,0,0,,没有必要使用暴力\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}There's no need for violence.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:07.82,0:52:10.65,Default,,0,0,0,,去你的！去你的！\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Fuck you. Fuck you!
Dialogue: 0,0:52:17.21,0:52:18.93,Default,,0,0,0,,噢 事情闹大了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Oh, this is getting heavy.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:43.37,0:52:46.55,Default,,0,0,0,,该死 我爱死在美国领土工作了 丹\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Goddamn, I love working on American soil, Dan.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:46.78,0:52:49.27,Default,,0,0,0,,自从伍德沃德和伯恩斯坦后就没这么好玩过了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Ain't had this much fun since Woodward and Bernstein.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:47.74,0:52:53.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\a6}(水门事件的两个记者)
Dialogue: 0,0:52:49.34,0:52:51.23,Default,,0,0,0,,这样我们能维持多久?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}How long can we keep this up?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:51.23,0:52:54.63,Default,,0,0,0,,国会正在推行几个新法案 要取缔蒙面英雄\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Congress is pushing through some new bill that's gonna outlaw masks.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:54.95,0:52:56.53,Default,,0,0,0,,我们的日子不多了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Our days are numbered.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:56.53,0:52:58.21,Default,,0,0,0,,但在那之前 就像你常说的\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Until then, it's like you always say:
Dialogue: 0,0:52:58.80,0:53:00.83,Default,,0,0,0,, "我们是社会的唯一保护"\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}We're society's only protection.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:00.83,0:53:05.24,Default,,0,0,0,,- 保护什么?  - 你说笑呢吧? 保护他们不被自己伤害\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}- From what? - Are you kidding me? From themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:05.72,0:53:07.92,Default,,0,0,0,,- 婊子养的  - 不 笑匠 等等！\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}- Son of a bitch. DAN: No, Comedian, wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:53:09.46,0:53:11.36,Default,,0,0,0,,把你的臭手拿开\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Get your stinking hands off me.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:13.53,0:53:15.80,Default,,0,0,0,,我们这是怎么了?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}What the hell happened to us?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:20.30,0:53:22.63,Default,,0,0,0,,美国梦是怎么了?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}What happened to the American dream?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:23.47,0:53:26.01,Default,,0,0,0,,美国梦怎么了?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}What happened to the American dream?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:26.48,0:53:28.20,Default,,0,0,0,,成为现实了啊\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}It came true!
Dialogue: 0,0:53:28.78,0:53:30.70,Default,,0,0,0,,你看到的就是\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You're looking at it.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:07.02,0:55:07.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}(帐户已过期)
Dialogue: 0,0:55:08.48,0:55:11.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}(金字塔跨国公司)
Dialogue: 0,0:55:15.53,0:55:17.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}(纽约公报：苏联不会容忍美国在阿富汗的冒险行为)
Dialogue: 0,0:55:25.02,0:55:27.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}(在你身后 罗夏标志)
Dialogue: 0,0:55:33.37,0:55:34.74,Default,,0,0,0,,埃德加·威廉·雅各比\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Edgar William Jacobi.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:34.74,0:55:38.74,Default,,0,0,0,,又称埃德加·威廉·沃恩 也就是"摩罗神"\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Also known as Edgar William Vaughn. Also known as Moloch.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:42.62,0:55:45.04,Default,,0,0,0,,我不知道你说什么\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:45.98,0:55:47.41,Default,,0,0,0,,我只是一个退休的商人\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I'm a retired businessman...
Dialogue: 0,0:55:49.72,0:55:52.55,Default,,0,0,0,,再说谎 摩罗神 我就折断另一根指头\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Lie again, Moloch, I break another finger.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:52.55,0:55:54.90,Default,,0,0,0,,我坐过牢\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I did my time.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:54.90,0:55:57.22,Default,,0,0,0,,我再也不是摩罗神了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I'm not Moloch anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:58.33,0:55:59.72,Default,,0,0,0,,你想从我这里知道什么?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}What do you want from me?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:59.72,0:56:02.76,Default,,0,0,0,,听说你参加了布雷克的葬礼 为什么?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Heard you attended Blake's funeral. Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:02.76,0:56:06.39,Default,,0,0,0,,我只是觉得我应该…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I just felt I should...
Dialogue: 0,0:56:07.57,0:56:10.47,Default,,0,0,0,,向笑匠表示敬意\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...pay my respects to the Comedian.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:12.77,0:56:14.40,Default,,0,0,0,,你怎么知道他是笑匠?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}How'd you know he was the Comedian?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:14.40,0:56:17.83,Default,,0,0,0,,他闯进了这里 一周前\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}He broke in here. A week ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:17.83,0:56:20.18,Default,,0,0,0,,他脱下了自己的面具\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}He had his mask off.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:20.65,0:56:24.30,Default,,0,0,0,,- 他喝醉了 - 敌人 有几十年了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}- He was drunk. - Enemies. For decades.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:24.30,0:56:27.50,Default,,0,0,0,,- 他为什么要拜访你?  - 我不知道\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}- Why should he visit you? - I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:27.50,0:56:30.46,Default,,0,0,0,,我在卧室里醒来 他就在我面前了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I woke up in my bedroom and there he was.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:30.46,0:56:32.59,Default,,0,0,0,,他很难过\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}He was upset.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:33.00,0:56:34.71,Default,,0,0,0,,他在哭\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}He was crying.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:35.20,0:56:37.51,Default,,0,0,0,,哭? 笑匠?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Crying? The Comedian?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:37.51,0:56:40.68,Default,,0,0,0,,他喃喃自语 没有意义的话\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}EDGAR: He was babbling, not making any sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:40.68,0:56:43.99,Default,,0,0,0,,我尿了裤子\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I was pissing in my pants.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:43.99,0:56:46.45,Default,,0,0,0,,我以为他要杀了我\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I thought he was gonna kill me.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:46.45,0:56:48.74,Default,,0,0,0,,他说了什么?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}RORSCHACH: What did he say?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:50.05,0:56:51.71,Default,,0,0,0,,这是个玩笑\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}It's a joke.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:52.45,0:56:55.01,Default,,0,0,0,,全都是个他妈的玩笑\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}It's all a fucking joke.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:57.05,0:56:59.45,Default,,0,0,0,,知道吗? 我以为我了解\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You know, I thought I knew how it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:59.45,0:57:02.65,Default,,0,0,0,,我以为我了解这世界\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I thought I knew how the world was.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:03.79,0:57:06.45,Default,,0,0,0,,我做过些坏事\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I've done some bad things.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:07.13,0:57:10.88,Default,,0,0,0,,我对女人做过坏事 我枪杀过孩子\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I did bad things to women. I shot kids.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:10.88,0:57:13.16,Default,,0,0,0,,你知道的 在越南\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}In 'Nam, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:13.74,0:57:15.17,Default,,0,0,0,,但那他妈是战争啊\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}But that was fucking war.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:16.14,0:57:17.47,Default,,0,0,0,,但是这次…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}This...
Dialogue: 0,0:57:18.14,0:57:20.80,Default,,0,0,0,,我从没有做过这样的事\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I never done anything like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:23.48,0:57:26.56,Default,,0,0,0,,天 我正在…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}God, here I am...
Dialogue: 0,0:57:26.56,0:57:28.67,Default,,0,0,0,,倾诉衷肠…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...spilling my guts...
Dialogue: 0,0:57:29.15,0:57:30.64,Default,,0,0,0,,对象是我最大的敌人之一\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...to one of my archenemies.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:32.82,0:57:35.15,Default,,0,0,0,,但事实是…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}But the truth is...
Dialogue: 0,0:57:35.76,0:57:40.35,Default,,0,0,0,,你是最接近于朋友的人了 那老话怎么说的来着?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...you're the closest thing to a friend I got. What the fuck does that say?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:44.27,0:57:46.46,Default,,0,0,0,,该死的\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Shit.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:47.83,0:57:49.82,Default,,0,0,0,,你的名字…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}And your name...
Dialogue: 0,0:57:49.82,0:57:52.55,Default,,0,0,0,,你的名字也在那名单上…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...your name was on the list...
Dialogue: 0,0:57:52.55,0:57:57.03,Default,,0,0,0,,还有珍妮 不管她他妈姓什么\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...along with Janey, you know, whatever the fuck her name is.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:57.03,0:57:59.48,Default,,0,0,0,,曼哈顿的前女友\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Manhattan's old girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:03.69,0:58:05.85,Default,,0,0,0,,母亲 原谅我\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Mother, forgive me.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:07.02,0:58:08.68,Default,,0,0,0,,然后他就走了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}EDGAR: And then he left.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:09.69,0:58:14.31,Default,,0,0,0,,我发誓我不知道他在说什么鬼话\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I swear I don't know what the hell he was talking about.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:21.04,0:58:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,有意思的故事\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Funny story.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:23.47,0:58:25.80,Default,,0,0,0,,听起来不可信\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Sounds unbelievable.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:26.41,0:58:28.66,Default,,0,0,0,,可能是真的\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Probably true.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:28.66,0:58:31.53,Default,,0,0,0,,就这样?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}So that's it?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:31.53,0:58:35.68,Default,,0,0,0,,- 我清白了?  - 你?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}- I'm clean? - You?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:36.89,0:58:38.22,Default,,0,0,0,,清白?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Clean?
