Dialogue: 0,1:07:45.40,1:07:48.70,Default,,0,0,0,,我不认识任何人 除了该死的超级英雄之外\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I don't know anybody except for goddamn superheroes.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:49.27,1:07:51.09,Default,,0,0,0,,没关系\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}That's okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:51.09,1:07:53.35,Default,,0,0,0,,你们大概只是吵嘴之类的\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You probably just had an argument or something.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:53.35,1:07:54.91,Default,,0,0,0,,不是的 丹\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}No, Dan.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:55.44,1:07:58.15,Default,,0,0,0,,你不知道和他一起生活是什么样子\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You don't know what it's been like living with him.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:58.15,1:08:01.60,Default,,0,0,0,,他看事物的方式 就好像他不…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}The way he looks at things now, it's like he doesn't...
Dialogue: 0,1:08:01.60,1:08:04.08,Default,,0,0,0,,不记得它们是什么样子了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...remember what they are.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:04.42,1:08:06.73,Default,,0,0,0,,就像这个世界 这个真实的世界…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}It's like this world, this real world...
Dialogue: 0,1:08:06.73,1:08:10.53,Default,,0,0,0,,对他来说 就像是走过烟雾\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}... to him, it's like walking through mist.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:10.53,1:08:14.29,Default,,0,0,0,,而人们只是一些影子\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}And people are just shadows.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:15.86,1:08:18.35,Default,,0,0,0,,雾中的影子\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Shadows in a fog.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:19.47,1:08:22.83,Default,,0,0,0,,天啊 事情怎么会变成一团乱麻\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}God, how did everything get so tangled up?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:24.44,1:08:26.43,Default,,0,0,0,,很抱歉 丹\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I'm sorry, Dan.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:27.17,1:08:30.17,Default,,0,0,0,,这是第二次了 我又搅乱了你的夜晚\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}This is twice now I've ruined your evening.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:30.61,1:08:33.60,Default,,0,0,0,,别这么说 你来了我很高兴\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Come on. I'm glad you came over.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:33.60,1:08:37.31,Default,,0,0,0,,我正要去看霍利斯 我们每周的啤酒聚会\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I was just gonna see Hollis for our weekly beer session.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:37.80,1:08:39.20,Default,,0,0,0,,我们绝对欢迎你加入\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You're more than welcome to join.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:40.65,1:08:43.94,Default,,0,0,0,,实际上 我坚持要你来\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}In fact, I insist.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:16.46,1:09:19.41,Default,,0,0,0,,好极了 曼哈顿博士已经到了但没人想要通知我\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Terrific. Dr. Manhattan arrives and no one thinks to tell me.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:19.41,1:09:21.48,Default,,0,0,0,,- 他就这样… - 没时间化妆了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}WOMAN: He just... - We don't have time for makeup.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:21.48,1:09:23.79,Default,,0,0,0,,这蓝光对摄影机来说太耀眼了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}That blue is too light for television.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:26.57,1:09:28.56,Default,,0,0,0,,这样够暗了吗?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Is that dark enough?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:30.37,1:09:33.26,Default,,0,0,0,,对 够暗了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}PRODUCER: Yeah, that's dark enough.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:33.26,1:09:35.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}(辐射庇护所)
Dialogue: 0,1:09:33.44,1:09:37.26,Default,,0,0,0,,世界的重量压在他身上 他会退缩吗? 不\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}BERNIE: The weight of the world's on him, but does he quit? No.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:37.26,1:09:39.62,Default,,0,0,0,,卖报纸的总是能解决 他们就像…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}News vendors always cope. They're the...
Dialogue: 0,1:09:39.62,1:09:43.27,Default,,0,0,0,,噢 天啊 他又来了 那个流浪者\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Oh, God, here comes that homeless guy again.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:43.72,1:09:46.61,Default,,0,0,0,,我说过了 这个月的一期还没有到\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I told you, this month's issue still hasn't arrived yet.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:46.61,1:09:48.99,Default,,0,0,0,,你干嘛那么关心那些右派的破报纸?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Why do you care about that right-wing rag so much?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:48.99,1:09:50.85,Default,,0,0,0,,那帮混蛋根本不关心…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Those bastards don't give a damn.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:51.53,1:09:53.90,Default,,0,0,0,,慢着 他们送来了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Hold up. Here they come.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:55.22,1:09:57.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}(新边缘人报：荣耀如同雄鹰：有时它也需要蒙上脸)
Dialogue: 0,1:09:57.60,1:10:00.39,Default,,0,0,0,,- 西摩尔 - 伯尼 近来可好?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}- Seymour. - Bernie, how's tricks?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:00.39,1:10:01.53,Default,,0,0,0,,不错 不错\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}BERNIE: Fine, fine.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:02.73,1:10:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,看到我身后那个男人吗? 这星期一直在烦我\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}See this guy behind me? Been bugging me all week.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:07.91,1:10:12.15,Default,,0,0,0,,或许我们该坐出租车 这里治安不好\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Maybe we should get a cab. These are bad neighborhoods.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:12.15,1:10:15.51,Default,,0,0,0,,管它呢 我正好心情坏\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Yeah, well, I'm in a bad mood.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:28.50,1:10:30.91,Default,,0,0,0,,- 小妞 - 看看谁来了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}MAN 1: Girl. MAN 2: What we got here?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:30.91,1:10:33.95,Default,,0,0,0,,这个是五角大楼开出的禁谈话题清单\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Here's a list of Pentagon-approved no-go areas.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:33.95,1:10:36.92,Default,,0,0,0,,他们一定会问起阿富汗的 一笔带过就好…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Afghanistan will obviously come up, but just play it cool...
Dialogue: 0,1:10:36.92,1:10:39.45,Default,,0,0,0,,还有别被逼进死胡同\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...and try not to get into any tight corners.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:39.45,1:10:43.32,Default,,0,0,0,,一位著名的核子物理学家 他在经过一场可怕的意外后…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}- A renowned nuclear physicist, who, through a terrible accident...
Dialogue: 0,1:10:43.32,1:10:49.26,Default,,0,0,0,,天赋了异乎寻常的力量 能够按自己的意愿改变物质\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...was gifted with extraordinary powers, capable of bending matter to his will.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:49.26,1:10:53.70,Default,,0,0,0,,今天 全世界都知道他的名字：曼哈顿博士\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Today, the world knows him as Dr. Manhattan.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:53.70,1:10:55.05,Default,,0,0,0,,欢迎你\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Welcome.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:00.06,1:11:01.25,Default,,0,0,0,,谢谢\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}JON: Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:01.25,1:11:03.40,Default,,0,0,0,,这就对了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}MAN 3: That's right.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:09.94,1:11:12.89,Default,,0,0,0,,布莱克女士 你来问第一个问题\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Ms. Black, you have the first question.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:12.89,1:11:14.30,Default,,0,0,0,,曼哈顿博士 如你所知…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Dr. Manhattan, as you know...
Dialogue: 0,1:11:14.30,1:11:17.18,Default,,0,0,0,,"末日时钟"是用来象征性地…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...the Doomsday Clock is a symbolic clock face...
Dialogue: 0,1:11:17.18,1:11:20.94,Default,,0,0,0,,类推人类如何接近灭绝时刻的\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...analogizing humankind's proximity to extinction...
Dialogue: 0,1:11:21.28,1:11:24.43,Default,,0,0,0,,午夜代表着核战爆发的威胁\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...midnight representing the threat of nuclear war.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:24.43,1:11:27.61,Default,,0,0,0,,而现在 它指向差4分钟到午夜的时刻\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}As of now, it stands at four minutes to midnight.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:28.26,1:11:30.94,Default,,0,0,0,,你同意我们距离毁灭有那么近吗?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Would you agree that we're that close to annihilation?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:30.94,1:11:33.30,Default,,0,0,0,,我父亲以前是一个钟表匠\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}My father was a watchmaker.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:34.13,1:11:38.47,Default,,0,0,0,,在爱因斯坦发现时间是相对的之后 他就抛弃了钟表\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}He abandoned it when Einstein discovered that time is relative.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:39.64,1:11:41.79,Default,,0,0,0,,我只能同意 一个象征性的钟表…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I would only agree that a symbolic clock...
Dialogue: 0,1:11:41.79,1:11:43.96,Default,,0,0,0,,对于智者而言 其营养…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...is as nourishing to the intellect...
Dialogue: 0,1:11:43.96,1:11:47.37,Default,,0,0,0,,就像一张氧气的照片之于溺水的人\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...as a photograph of oxygen to a drowning man.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:49.58,1:11:51.65,Default,,0,0,0,,所以你是说没有危险?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}So you're saying there is no danger.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:51.65,1:11:55.59,Default,,0,0,0,,即便在一个没有核武器的世界 依然有危险存在\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}JON: Even in a world without nuclear weapons, there would still be danger.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:00.39,1:12:03.43,Default,,0,0,0,,你会不会说 如同很多人说的那样…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}MAN: And would you say, as so many claim...
Dialogue: 0,1:12:03.43,1:12:05.39,Default,,0,0,0,,你实际上就是"神"…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...that you are, in fact, a god...
Dialogue: 0,1:12:05.39,1:12:08.42,Default,,0,0,0,,鉴于你能够同时看到过去和未来?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...given that you see the past and future simultaneously?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:08.42,1:12:10.86,Default,,0,0,0,,我只能看到我自己的过去…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I can only see my own past...
Dialogue: 0,1:12:11.17,1:12:12.44,Default,,0,0,0,,…我自己的未来\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}... my own future.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:12.97,1:12:15.19,Default,,0,0,0,,我并不是全知的\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I am not omniscient.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:15.68,1:12:17.20,Default,,0,0,0,,道格·罗斯 你的问题\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}KOPPEL: Doug Roth, your question?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:17.20,1:12:20.09,Default,,0,0,0,,说起你的过去 曼哈顿博士…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Speaking of your past, Dr. Manhattan...
Dialogue: 0,1:12:20.09,1:12:23.03,Default,,0,0,0,,你还记得一个叫沃利·维沃的男人吗?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...do you remember a man named Wally Weaver?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:23.03,1:12:28.29,Default,,0,0,0,,是的 我们在吉拉·弗莱茨研究基地共事过\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Yes. We were both physicists together at the Gila Flats Research Base.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:28.69,1:12:30.38,Default,,0,0,0,,他死于癌症\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}He died of cancer.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:31.12,1:12:33.54,Default,,0,0,0,,- 他是一个好人 - 那么埃德加·雅各比呢?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}- He was a good man. ROTH: How about Edgar Jacobi...
Dialogue: 0,1:12:33.54,1:12:36.46,Default,,0,0,0,,也就是被称作"摩罗神"的超级恶棍\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}... also known as the supervillain Moloch?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:37.38,1:12:41.64,Default,,0,0,0,,你和他在60年代的战斗、冲突中相遇过几次\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You encountered him several times in the '60s: Battles, conflicts.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:41.64,1:12:44.31,Default,,0,0,0,,你知道他也得了癌症吗?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Did you know that he has cancer as well?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:45.14,1:12:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,我并未被告知\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I wasn't told.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:46.48,1:12:48.83,Default,,0,0,0,,那么安东尼·兰道夫将军呢?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}ROTH: And what about General Anthony Randolph?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:48.83,1:12:52.03,Default,,0,0,0,,他是你在为政府工作时的联系人\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}He was your handler when you first started working for the government.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:52.78,1:12:53.96,Default,,0,0,0,,也是癌症\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Cancer.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:53.96,1:12:56.78,Default,,0,0,0,,你在暗示我是诱因?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You're suggesting I was the cause.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:57.05,1:13:00.20,Default,,0,0,0,,就我来看 结论看起来毋庸置疑\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}ROTH: From where I'm standing, it's starting to look pretty conclusive.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:00.20,1:13:02.40,Default,,0,0,0,,即便情况如此 也是不相干的\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}JON: Even if that's the case, it's irrelevant.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:02.40,1:13:05.33,Default,,0,0,0,,一个活着的人体和一个死去的人体…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}A live human body and a deceased human body...
Dialogue: 0,1:13:05.33,1:13:07.48,Default,,0,0,0,,具有相同数目的粒子\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}... have the same number of particles.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:10.17,1:13:12.25,Default,,0,0,0,,从结构上说 没有区别\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Structurally, there's no difference.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:13.27,1:13:15.71,Default,,0,0,0,,好了 请安静一下\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}All right. Let's settle down, please.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:21.39,1:13:22.76,Default,,0,0,0,,那么珍妮·斯莱特呢?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}What about Janey Slater?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:23.41,1:13:25.74,Default,,0,0,0,,你觉得她有不同吗?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You think it makes a difference to her?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:26.81,1:13:28.14,Default,,0,0,0,,珍妮?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Janey?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:28.48,1:13:30.20,Default,,0,0,0,,你的前女友\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}ROTH: Your ex-girlfriend?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:30.20,1:13:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,她也曾是个物理学家 你们交往了11年\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}She was a physicist too. You saw each other for 11 years.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:34.00,1:13:35.70,Default,,0,0,0,,道格 一次问一个问题\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Doug, one question at a time.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:35.70,1:13:39.24,Default,,0,0,0,,她也得了癌症 医生说她只有半年命\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}She has cancer as well. Doctors have given her six months.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:39.24,1:13:41.24,Default,,0,0,0,,我说的对吗 斯莱特女士?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Isn't that right, Miss Slater?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:56.61,1:13:58.55,Default,,0,0,0,,你曾是我的世界 乔恩\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You were the world to me, Jon.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:59.01,1:14:01.38,Default,,0,0,0,,你曾是我全部的生命\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You were my whole life.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:02.18,1:14:04.93,Default,,0,0,0,,还记得你说过多少次你爱我吗?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Do you remember how many times you said you loved me?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:04.93,1:14:06.65,Default,,0,0,0,,珍妮 没人告诉我\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Janey, I wasn't told.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:07.12,1:14:12.22,Default,,0,0,0,,那次意外后我对你不离不弃 我给了你一切\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I stuck by you after the accident. I gave you everything.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:17.53,1:14:19.32,Default,,0,0,0,,这就是你给我的回报吗?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}This is how you repay me?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:19.63,1:14:22.94,Default,,0,0,0,,- 珍妮 没人告诉过我 我不知道这事 - 诅咒你 乔恩\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}- Janey, I wasn't told. I didn't know. - Damn you, Jon.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:23.63,1:14:24.66,Default,,0,0,0,,愿上帝诅咒你\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Goddamn you.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:24.66,1:14:26.83,Default,,0,0,0,,珍妮 等等\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Janey, wait.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:28.08,1:14:30.66,Default,,0,0,0,,够了 本次采访结束 来人\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}- That's it. This interview is over. MAN: Get up there.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:30.66,1:14:33.08,Default,,0,0,0,,把相机都拿走 所有人后退\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Get those cameras off. Everybody back off.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:33.45,1:14:37.10,Default,,0,0,0,,所有人后退 我需要支援 别再烦他\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Everybody back off. I need some backup here. Leave him alone.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:37.10,1:14:43.37,Default,,0,0,0,,请你们大家 都走开…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Please, if everyone would just go away...
Dialogue: 0,1:14:43.37,1:14:46.44,Default,,0,0,0,,别再烦我…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...and leave me alone...
Dialogue: 0,1:14:46.44,1:14:48.01,Default,,0,0,0,,你愿意发表评论吗?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Do you care to comment?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:48.01,1:14:51.05,Default,,0,0,0,,我说过 别烦我！\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I said, leave me alone!
Dialogue: 0,1:15:16.69,1:15:18.59,Default,,0,0,0,,老天爷\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Jesus.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:19.69,1:15:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,,我们…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Us...
Dialogue: 0,1:15:22.20,1:15:24.03,Default,,0,0,0,,被打劫了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...getting mugged.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:26.37,1:15:27.96,Default,,0,0,0,,走吧\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:33.71,1:15:35.50,Default,,0,0,0,,我在发抖\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I'm shaking.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:39.71,1:15:41.48,Default,,0,0,0,,你知道吗?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You know what?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:41.85,1:15:45.50,Default,,0,0,0,,我心情好了 我会记住今晚的\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I'm wiped. I'm just gonna call it a night.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:45.50,1:15:48.90,Default,,0,0,0,,噢 你真的不和我一起去霍利斯家…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Oh, are you sure you don't wanna come by Hollis' with me...
Dialogue: 0,1:15:48.90,1:16:09.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\a5}新边疆人报 正直的新闻 立即订阅\N 内心里 你知道这是对的
Dialogue: 0,1:15:48.92,1:15:51.15,Default,,0,0,0,,然后摆脱一下肾上腺素吗?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...and shake off the adrenaline?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:51.96,1:15:55.09,Default,,0,0,0,,我想我一晚上做一件超级英雄的事情就够了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}LAURIE: I think I've had enough hero stuff for one night.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:56.23,1:15:58.87,Default,,0,0,0,,有你倾听帮了很大忙\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}It helped having you listen.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:58.87,1:16:00.63,Default,,0,0,0,,随时欢迎\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}DAN: Any time.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:01.33,1:16:03.23,Default,,0,0,0,,保重 丹\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}LAURIE: Take care, Dan.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:04.04,1:16:06.34,Default,,0,0,0,,这世道不太平\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}It's a rough world out there.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:07.81,1:16:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,回见\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}DAN: Be seeing you.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:10.65,1:16:10.65,Default,,0,0,0,,[片段3插入点][]
Dialogue: 0,1:16:15.35,1:16:16.85,Default,,0,0,0,,我想到了家人…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}MARINER: I thought of my family...
Dialogue: 0,1:16:17.62,1:16:20.03,Default,,0,0,0,,…我的妻子 我的女儿们\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}... my wife, my daughters.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:20.03,1:16:22.23,Default,,0,0,0,,她们毫无防备 毫无怀疑\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Vulnerable, unsuspecting.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:22.76,1:16:26.34,Default,,0,0,0,,等待着我的归来 而只会碰上天谴…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Awaiting my return, only to be met by damnation...
Dialogue: 0,1:16:26.34,1:16:28.79,Default,,0,0,0,,…扑向她们\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}... bearing down upon them.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:35.27,1:16:36.52,Default,,0,0,0,,嘿！\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Hey!
Dialogue: 0,1:16:36.52,1:16:38.17,Default,,0,0,0,,我在这儿！\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Over here!
Dialogue: 0,1:16:38.60,1:16:40.13,Default,,0,0,0,,这儿！\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Here!
Dialogue: 0,1:16:45.95,1:16:47.38,Default,,0,0,0,,瑞德里\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Ridley.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:03.76,1:17:05.19,Default,,0,0,0,,船帆\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}A sail.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:05.47,1:17:07.96,Default,,0,0,0,,瑞德里给我带来了一片船帆\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Ridley had brought me a sail.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:08.27,1:17:11.40,Default,,0,0,0,,或许这可以带我回到戴维斯城\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Perhaps this could be my route back to Davidstown.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:12.77,1:17:17.16,Default,,0,0,0,,我爱的一切 我为之而活的一切 取决于我赶快到家…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Everything I loved, everything I lived for, depended on my reaching home...
Dialogue: 0,1:17:17.16,1:17:20.48,Default,,0,0,0,,…赶在那可怕的黑货船之前\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}... in advance of that terrible Freighter.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:30.06,1:17:32.76,Default,,0,0,0,,朝阳升起 我的麻烦依然不少\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}The morning sun found me no less troubled.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:34.26,1:17:35.58,Default,,0,0,0,,在更远的海岸上…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Further down the shore...
Dialogue: 0,1:17:35.58,1:17:39.09,Default,,0,0,0,,…我的一些船员因臭气而膨胀\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}... some of my crew had become inflated with gas.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:39.53,1:17:41.14,Default,,0,0,0,,啊！\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Ugh!
Dialogue: 0,1:17:44.57,1:17:50.32,Default,,0,0,0,,我为自己的想法不寒而栗 尝试着赶走这令人厌恶的念头\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I shuddered at my own idea, attempting to banish this repulsive notion.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:57.55,1:18:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,即便已死 他们还努力履行职责…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Even in death, they sought to fulfill their duty...
Dialogue: 0,1:18:02.00,1:18:04.62,Default,,0,0,0,,…让我们的这艘船更有浮力\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}... making our vessel more buoyant.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:05.02,1:18:08.30,Default,,0,0,0,,而我会履行我对他们的责任 带他们回家\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}And I would do my duty to them in returning them home.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:09.83,1:18:15.25,Default,,0,0,0,,无礼地搅扰我那些长眠的船员 并把他们放进我准备的尸床\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Rudely jarring my men from eternal rest, and laying them in the bed I prepared...
Dialogue: 0,1:18:15.25,1:18:19.89,Default,,0,0,0,,我希望我的妻女大限来到之际…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}... I hoped my wife and daughters might be tucked in by gentler hands...
Dialogue: 0,1:18:19.89,1:18:21.60,Default,,0,0,0,,…可以被温柔的手安放\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}... when their turn came.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:38.96,1:18:41.32,Default,,0,0,0,,我们会一起回家的 我的朋友\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}We shall get home together, my friend.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:44.30,1:18:45.73,Default,,0,0,0,,我等待着涨潮\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I waited for the tide.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:46.38,1:18:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,然后 坐上船 向东航行\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Then, embarking, headed east.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:51.10,1:18:53.89,Default,,0,0,0,,东方 穿过黑夜海洋\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}East, across the night seas.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:53.89,1:18:58.37,Default,,0,0,0,,东方 靠在被虐杀的人的尸体上\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}East, borne on the bodies of murdered men.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:59.31,1:19:01.80,Default,,0,0,0,,希望 可能是一件可怕的事\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Hope can be a horrible thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:06.58,1:20:11.03,Default,,0,0,0,,随着黎明的到来 海鸥找寻早餐\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}With the dawn came the gulls looking for breakfast.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:11.03,1:20:12.34,Default,,0,0,0,,瑞德里\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Ridley.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:15.39,1:20:16.59,Default,,0,0,0,,滚开\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Get out.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:22.60,1:20:25.89,Default,,0,0,0,,我才想起我自己还没有吃东西\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I was reminded that I, myself, had not eaten.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:27.83,1:20:31.96,Default,,0,0,0,,我知道它倒胃口 但这是我们仅有的\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I know it is unappetizing, but it is all we have.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:34.24,1:20:36.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}(黑货船传奇)
Dialogue: 0,1:20:37.54,1:20:39.31,Default,,0,0,0,,他走了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}MAN: He's gone.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:39.81,1:20:41.43,Default,,0,0,0,,- 他走了 - 谁走了?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}- He's gone! BERNIE: Who's gone?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:41.43,1:20:43.79,Default,,0,0,0,,- 曼哈顿博士 - 什么? 你说什么?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}- Dr. Manhattan. BERNIE: What? What'd you say?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:43.79,1:20:46.75,Default,,0,0,0,,曼哈顿博士走了 他离开我们了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Dr. Manhattan's gone. He's left us.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:47.12,1:20:49.64,Default,,0,0,0,,什么? 去哪儿了?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}What? Gone where?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:51.64,1:20:51.64,Default,,0,0,0,,[片段3][音频切换点][]
Dialogue: 0,1:20:53.04,1:20:53.04,Default,,0,0,0,,[片段3][画面切换点][]
Dialogue: 0,1:20:55.76,1:20:57.04,Default,,0,0,0,,你晚了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You're late.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:57.04,1:21:00.31,Default,,0,0,0,,啊 我知道 你不会相信刚才发生的事的\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Ah, I know. I know. You won't believe what happened.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:00.31,1:21:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,曼哈顿博士刚在电视直播中消失了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Dr. Manhattan just lost it on live TV.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:03.28,1:21:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,等等 什么?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Wait, what?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:10.58,1:21:12.69,Default,,0,0,0,,我刚才和劳瑞一起 她不知道这事\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I was just with Laurie. She doesn't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:13.31,1:21:17.07,Default,,0,0,0,,她很快就会知道的 全世界也会的\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}HOLLIS: She's gonna know soon enough. The whole world will know.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:17.07,1:21:19.81,Default,,0,0,0,,我说过 别烦我！\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I said, leave me alone!
Dialogue: 0,1:21:29.66,1:21:31.86,Default,,0,0,0,,我看着星空\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}JON: I am looking at the stars.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:32.37,1:21:34.36,Default,,0,0,0,,它们是那么遥远…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}They're so far away...
Dialogue: 0,1:21:34.80,1:21:37.46,Default,,0,0,0,,它们的光芒要那么久才能到我们这里…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}... and their light takes so long to reach us...
Dialogue: 0,1:21:40.21,1:21:44.40,Default,,0,0,0,,我们看到的星星都只是它们的旧照片\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}... all we ever see of stars are their old photographs.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:48.01,1:21:51.85,Default,,0,0,0,,在1959年7月 我恋爱了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}It is July, 1959, and I am in love.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:52.79,1:21:54.35,Default,,0,0,0,,好极了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}MAN: That's great.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:54.66,1:21:56.41,Default,,0,0,0,,- 你明天来取相片 - 好的\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}- You can pick it up tomorrow. - Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:56.41,1:21:58.46,Default,,0,0,0,,- 75美分 - 好 谢谢你\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}- Seventy-five cents. - Okay, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:58.46,1:21:59.41,Default,,0,0,0,,谢谢\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:59.41,1:22:02.12,Default,,0,0,0,,天啊 乔恩 希望他刚才给我们一点提示\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Gosh, Jon, I wish he gave us a little notice.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:02.43,1:22:03.78,Default,,0,0,0,,我肯定做了怪样子\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I'm sure I made a face.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:03.78,1:22:08.79,Default,,0,0,0,,噢 不会 我保证你样子很好看\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Oh, no, no. I'm sure that you'll look beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:12.71,1:22:15.04,Default,,0,0,0,,她的名字是珍妮·斯莱特\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Her name is Janey Slater.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:15.88,1:22:18.54,Default,,0,0,0,,她是一个物理学家 和我一样\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}She is a physicist, like me.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:19.81,1:22:21.72,Default,,0,0,0,,我30岁\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I am 30 years old.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:26.29,1:22:30.22,Default,,0,0,0,,我们是我一位大学好友沃利·维勒介绍的\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}We were introduced by a good friend of mine from college, Wally Weaver.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:34.39,1:22:37.11,Default,,0,0,0,,那是在1981年2月12日\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}It is February 12th, 1981.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:37.11,1:22:41.03,Default,,0,0,0,,沃利死于癌症 他们现在说是我导致的\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Wally dies of cancer, of which they now say I am the cause.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:57.88,1:23:01.28,Default,,0,0,0,,那一晚 珍妮和我第一次做爱\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}That night, Janey and I make love for the first time.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:09.13,1:23:12.12,Default,,0,0,0,,一个月之后 那意外在等着我\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}A month from now, the accident awaits me.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:19.61,1:23:23.07,Default,,0,0,0,,噢 我一会儿赶上你们 我好像把手表留在了里面\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Oh, I'll catch up with you guys. I think I left my watch inside.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:23.78,1:23:26.16,Default,,0,0,0,,嘿 我们等等他吧\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Hey. Let's just wait a second.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:29.42,1:23:33.96,Default,,0,0,0,,我穿过房间来到本征域中心 找到我的手表\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I cross the room to the Intrinsic Field Center. I find my watch.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:40.53,1:23:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,当我走到门前时…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}When I get to the door...
Dialogue: 0,1:23:43.46,1:23:44.81,Default,,0,0,0,,沃利脸色都白了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}... Wally is turning white.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:44.81,1:23:49.05,Default,,0,0,0,,程序被锁死了 我们不能控制计时器\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}The program's locked in. We can't override the time lock.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:50.35,1:23:52.35,Default,,0,0,0,,我被吓坏了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I am terrified.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:52.35,1:23:53.50,Default,,0,0,0,,乔恩?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}JANEY: Jon?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:58.74,1:24:00.48,Default,,0,0,0,,对不起 乔恩…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I'm sorry, Jon...
Dialogue: 0,1:24:02.40,1:24:04.01,Default,,0,0,0,,我不能眼睁睁看着…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...but I can't...
Dialogue: 0,1:24:06.29,1:24:07.81,Default,,0,0,0,,珍妮 别离开我！\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Janey, don't leave me!
Dialogue: 0,1:24:08.35,1:24:10.35,Default,,0,0,0,,别离开我！\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Don't leave me!
Dialogue: 0,1:24:42.39,1:24:47.16,Default,,0,0,0,,那是1959年5月12日 我被介绍给珍妮的时候\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}It is May 12th, 1959, when I'm introduced to Janey.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:47.59,1:24:49.98,Default,,0,0,0,,她给我买了杯啤酒…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}She buys me a beer...
Dialogue: 0,1:24:49.98,1:24:52.95,Default,,0,0,0,,那是第一次有女人为我做这样的事\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}... the first time a woman has done this for me.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:54.20,1:24:58.03,Default,,0,0,0,,当她递给我那冰冷、溢满的酒杯时…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}As she passes me the cold, perspiring glass...
Dialogue: 0,1:24:58.67,1:25:00.04,Default,,0,0,0,,我们的手指相碰了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}... our fingers touch.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:12.79,1:25:15.10,Default,,0,0,0,,对 乔恩 不错\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Yes, Jon, good.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:15.10,1:25:20.62,Default,,0,0,0,,现在的问题只是 按照正确的顺序重新组装这些零件\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Now it's just a question of reassembling the components in the correct sequence.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:24.46,1:25:25.69,Default,,0,0,0,,我最后一次…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I feel fear...
Dialogue: 0,1:25:26.80,1:25:28.93,Default,,0,0,0,,感觉到了恐惧\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}... for the last time.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:45.75,1:25:48.33,Default,,0,0,0,,举行了一次象征性的葬礼\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}A token funeral is held.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:48.33,1:25:50.67,Default,,0,0,0,,没有东西可以埋葬\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}There is nothing to bury.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:50.67,1:25:53.47,Default,,0,0,0,,珍妮把那张快照装裱了起来\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Janey frames the snapshot.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:53.47,1:25:56.77,Default,,0,0,0,,那是别人所拥有的我唯一一张照片\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}It's the only photograph of me anyone has.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:57.93,1:26:02.94,Default,,0,0,0,,有人在墙外看到了一副人体循环系统\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}A circulatory system is seen by the perimeter fence.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:03.20,1:26:04.82,Default,,0,0,0,,几天后…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}A few days later...
Dialogue: 0,1:26:04.82,1:26:08.22,Default,,0,0,0,,一具覆盖了部分肌肉的人体骨骼站在走廊上\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}... a partially muscled skeleton stands in a hallway...
Dialogue: 0,1:26:08.22,1:26:12.07,Default,,0,0,0,,在它消失之前 还尖叫了一阵\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}... and screams for a moment before vanishing.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:37.44,1:26:39.62,Default,,0,0,0,,噢 上帝\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Oh, God.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:39.62,1:26:41.16,Default,,0,0,0,,乔恩?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Jon?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:42.21,1:26:44.04,Default,,0,0,0,,是你吗?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Is that you?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:44.65,1:26:47.89,Default,,0,0,0,,(NSB台晚间新闻)世界各国对今天上午的声明感到震惊…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Nations around the world reeling from this morning's announcement...
Dialogue: 0,1:26:47.89,1:26:50.70,Default,,0,0,0,,可能是当代历史上最重大的事件\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...possibly the most significant event in recent history.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:50.70,1:26:54.66,Default,,0,0,0,,我重复一次 超人存在 而且他的确是美国人\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}We repeat, the superman exists, and he is American.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:01.16,1:27:03.75,Default,,0,0,0,,他们叫我曼哈顿博士…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}They call me Dr. Manhattan.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:06.10,1:27:08.18,Default,,0,0,0,,他们解释说选这名字…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}They explain the name has been chosen...
Dialogue: 0,1:27:08.18,1:27:12.43,Default,,0,0,0,,是要让美国的敌人们联想到噩兆(原子弹的曼哈顿计划)\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}... for the ominous associations it will raise in America's enemies.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:17.04,1:27:20.38,Default,,0,0,0,,搞宣传的伙计们说我需要一个徽记\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}The marketing boys say I need a logo.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:29.19,1:27:31.55,Default,,0,0,0,,如果我要有个象征…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}If I'm to have a symbol...
Dialogue: 0,1:27:33.53,1:27:36.15,Default,,0,0,0,,就只能是我所敬仰的那个 (原子)\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}... it shall be one I respect.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:46.21,1:27:49.23,Default,,0,0,0,,他们把我塑造成一件俗丽的东西…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}They are shaping me into something gaudy...
Dialogue: 0,1:27:50.31,1:27:52.44,Default,,0,0,0,,一件致命的东西\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}... something lethal.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:57.25,1:27:59.93,Default,,0,0,0,,在1971年1月…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}In January, 1971...
Dialogue: 0,1:27:59.93,1:28:04.07,Default,,0,0,0,,尼克松总统要我干涉越战…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}... President Nixon asks me to intervene in Vietnam...
Dialogue: 0,1:28:04.07,1:28:06.98,Default,,0,0,0,,一件他的前任不会要求我干的事\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}... something that his predecessors would not ask.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:08.16,1:28:11.14,Default,,0,0,0,,一周之后 冲突结束了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}A week later, the conflict ends.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:11.14,1:28:15.60,Default,,0,0,0,,其中一些越共士兵还向我个人投降\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Some of the Vietcong forces wanna surrender to me personally.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:19.04,1:28:22.79,Default,,0,0,0,,霍利斯·梅森 一位退休的变装英雄 写了本书\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Hollis Mason, a retired costume hero, writes a book.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:22.79,1:28:27.79,Default,,0,0,0,,书里 他把我的到来称为超级英雄的黎明\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}In it, he calls my arrival the dawn of the superhero.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:28.48,1:28:31.13,Default,,0,0,0,,我不确定我是否明白这句话的意思\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I am not sure if I know what that means.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:47.70,1:28:50.94,Default,,0,0,0,,你看 当时 我被错误引用了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}WALLY: You see, at the time, I was misquoted.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:50.94,1:28:54.29,Default,,0,0,0,,我从未说过："超人存在 而且他是美国人"\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I never said, "The superman exists and he is American."
Dialogue: 0,1:28:54.29,1:29:00.27,Default,,0,0,0,,我当时说的是："神存在 而且他是美国人"\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}What I said was, "God exists, and he is American."
Dialogue: 0,1:29:00.95,1:29:03.40,Default,,0,0,0,,好了 如果你开始对这个概念…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Now, if you begin to feel an intense...
Dialogue: 0,1:29:03.40,1:29:07.32,Default,,0,0,0,,有一种极为糟糕的宗教恐怖的感觉\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...and crushing feeling of religious terror at the concept...
Dialogue: 0,1:29:07.75,1:29:09.78,Default,,0,0,0,,不要担心\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...don't be alarmed.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:10.42,1:29:14.45,Default,,0,0,0,,那说明你们的头脑依然清醒\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}That indicates only that you are still sane.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:16.93,1:29:20.06,Default,,0,0,0,,那是1963年的圣诞节\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}It is Christmas, 1963.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:20.40,1:29:24.10,Default,,0,0,0,,珍妮告诉我说她害怕而且担心\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Janey tells me she is afraid, and worried.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:24.74,1:29:27.53,Default,,0,0,0,,她说我现在就像一个神\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}She says I am like a god now.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:28.24,1:29:30.56,Default,,0,0,0,,我告诉她 我认为没有神\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I tell her I don't think there is a God.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:30.56,1:29:33.36,Default,,0,0,0,,如果真的有 我也一点都不像他\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}And if there is, I'm nothing like him.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:37.98,1:29:40.42,Default,,0,0,0,,我告诉她我依然想要她…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I tell her I still want her...
Dialogue: 0,1:29:41.19,1:29:43.32,Default,,0,0,0,,而且会永远想要她\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}... and that I always will.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:46.26,1:29:50.92,Default,,0,0,0,,我向她说了谎 在1970年9月4日\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}As I lie to her, it is September 4th, 1970.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:51.76,1:29:54.75,Default,,0,0,0,,我在一个人们全穿着变装的房间里\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I am in a room full of people wearing disguises.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:56.10,1:30:00.51,Default,,0,0,0,,一个很年轻的女孩对着我笑\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}A very young girl looks at me and smiles.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:02.24,1:30:04.23,Default,,0,0,0,,她很美\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}She's beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:07.78,1:30:13.83,Default,,0,0,0,,每次长吻后 她都在我唇上留下一个小小的温柔的吻…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}After each long kiss, she plants a smaller, gentler one upon my lips...
Dialogue: 0,1:30:13.83,1:30:15.57,Default,,0,0,0,,就像是一个签名\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}... like a signature.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:16.79,1:30:19.95,Default,,0,0,0,,珍妮指责我追逐未成年女\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Janey accuses me of chasing jailbait.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:20.46,1:30:25.88,Default,,0,0,0,,她爆发出愤怒的泪水 问我是不是因为她变老了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}She bursts into angry tears, asking if it's because she's getting older.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:25.88,1:30:27.87,Default,,0,0,0,,真的\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}It's true.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:29.80,1:30:32.83,Default,,0,0,0,,她每天都在明显地老去\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}She's aging more noticeably every day...
Dialogue: 0,1:30:39.41,1:30:42.24,Default,,0,0,0,,而我却一直不变\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}... while I am standing still.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:43.18,1:30:45.84,Default,,0,0,0,,我更喜欢这里的宁静不变\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I prefer the stillness here.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:46.76,1:30:49.07,Default,,0,0,0,,我厌倦了地球\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I am tired of Earth.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:49.07,1:30:50.75,Default,,0,0,0,,这些人\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}These people.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:51.32,1:30:55.15,Default,,0,0,0,,我厌倦了在他们的生命纠葛中被困住\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I'm tired of being caught in the tangle of their lives.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:17.85,1:31:21.18,Default,,0,0,0,,他们声称自己的劳作是要打造天堂…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}They claim their labors are to build a heaven...
Dialogue: 0,1:31:21.75,1:31:25.21,Default,,0,0,0,,但他们的天堂充满着恐惧\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}... yet their heaven is populated with horrors.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:25.69,1:31:28.35,Default,,0,0,0,,或许世界不是制造出来的\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Perhaps the world is not made.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:29.36,1:31:31.35,Default,,0,0,0,,或许没有什么东西能够被制造\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Perhaps nothing is made.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:32.23,1:31:35.76,Default,,0,0,0,,就像没有工匠的钟表\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}A clock without a craftsman.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:36.70,1:31:38.69,Default,,0,0,0,,太晚了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}It's too late.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:39.14,1:31:41.04,Default,,0,0,0,,从来都是…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Always has been...
Dialogue: 0,1:31:41.67,1:31:45.11,Default,,0,0,0,,永远都是…太晚了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}... always will be too late.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:47.53,1:31:50.38,Default,,0,0,0,,而你不知道他会去哪里?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}FORBES: And you have no idea where he would've gone.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:50.38,1:31:51.85,Default,,0,0,0,,我怎么会知道?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}LAURIE: How would I know?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:51.85,1:31:54.75,Default,,0,0,0,,大概是在世界的另一端研究分子\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Probably on the other side of the world studying molecules.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:54.75,1:31:57.45,Default,,0,0,0,,我们的卫星已经对地球作了一次扫描\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}FORBES: Our satellites have done a sweep of the planet.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:57.45,1:31:59.92,Default,,0,0,0,,哪里都没有他能量信号的迹象\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}There's no trace of his energy signature anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:59.92,1:32:01.39,Default,,0,0,0,,真的?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Really?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:01.39,1:32:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,朱庇特小姐 今天你和曼哈顿博士吵架了吗?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Miss Jupiter, did you and Dr. Manhattan have a fight today?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:04.96,1:32:06.63,Default,,0,0,0,,这他妈不关你的事\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}None of your fucking business.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:06.63,1:32:09.98,Default,,0,0,0,,当你拿政府的薪水但却没干活的时候 就关我的事了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}It is when you're on government payroll and you're not doing your job.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:10.82,1:32:14.77,Default,,0,0,0,,你说的话就相当于叫我"妓女" 佛布斯探员\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}That's as close to the word "whore" as you're gonna get with me, Agent Forbes.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:22.77,1:32:24.26,Default,,0,0,0,,抽烟吗?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Smoke?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:24.80,1:32:27.18,Default,,0,0,0,,我道歉 朱庇特小姐\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}My apologies, Miss Jupiter.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:27.18,1:32:30.57,Default,,0,0,0,,你了解曼哈顿博士对于我们的国家安全有多重要\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You know how important Dr. Manhattan is to our national security.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:31.47,1:32:33.56,Default,,0,0,0,,你能想象到我们的担忧\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You can imagine our concern.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:33.56,1:32:35.25,Default,,0,0,0,,我只能想象…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I can only imagine.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:41.35,1:32:45.34,Default,,0,0,0,,一旦那些核弹开始飞行 什么事都不再重要了 我们都成尘土\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}EDDIE: Ain't nothing gonna matter once those nukes start flying. We'll all be dust.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:45.79,1:32:48.35,Default,,0,0,0,,而后这位法老王…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Then Ozymandias here...
Dialogue: 0,1:32:48.79,1:32:51.56,Default,,0,0,0,,将会成为废墟里最聪明的人\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...will be the smartest man on the cinder.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:09.75,1:33:12.84,Default,,0,0,0,,劳瑞? 劳瑞·简?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}EDDIE: Laurel? Laurel Jane?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:14.38,1:33:16.33,Default,,0,0,0,,你是沙莉·朱庇特的女儿\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You're Sally Jupiter's kid.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:17.09,1:33:19.50,Default,,0,0,0,,你是笑匠 对吧?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You're the Comedian, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:19.50,1:33:21.17,Default,,0,0,0,,你刚才很酷\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You were pretty cool in there.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:21.79,1:33:25.67,Default,,0,0,0,,知道吗? 你妈妈她以前是空前的选美冠军\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You know, your mom, she was one of the all-time champion beauties.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:26.70,1:33:31.18,Default,,0,0,0,,你有她的眼睛 就连那可爱的小胎记你也有\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You got her eyes, you know. You even have that same funny little mole.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:31.50,1:33:33.67,Default,,0,0,0,,把你的手拿开\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Take your hands off her.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:33.67,1:33:35.82,Default,,0,0,0,,嘿 美人 好久不见\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Hey, doll. Long time no see.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:35.82,1:33:37.67,Default,,0,0,0,,对我来说还不够久 埃迪\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Not long enough in my book, Eddie.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:37.67,1:33:39.43,Default,,0,0,0,,上车\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Get in the car.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:41.01,1:33:43.16,Default,,0,0,0,,你的沉沦完全没有底线吗?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Are there no depths you won't sink to?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:43.16,1:33:47.01,Default,,0,0,0,,老天 莎莉 一个人就不能和他的…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Jesus Christ, Sally. Can't a guy talk to his...
Dialogue: 0,1:33:47.72,1:33:49.57,Default,,0,0,0,,老友的女儿说话?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...you know, old friend's daughter?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:49.87,1:33:51.86,Default,,0,0,0,,我说 你以为我是什么人?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I mean, what the hell do you think I am?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:51.86,1:33:53.55,Default,,0,0,0,,我们找到他了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}MAN: We found him!
Dialogue: 0,1:33:56.59,1:33:58.69,Default,,0,0,0,,- 找到他了 - 他在哪儿?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}- We found him. FORBES: Where is he?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:02.10,1:34:03.58,Default,,0,0,0,,火星\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Mars.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:04.10,1:34:07.43,Default,,0,0,0,,(这位是亨利·基辛格 国务卿)
Dialogue: 0,1:34:09.47,1:34:11.62,Default,,0,0,0,,总统先生…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Mr. President...
Dialogue: 0,1:34:11.62,1:34:16.43,Default,,0,0,0,,苏联军队已经把他们的坦克 开到阿富汗边界附近\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...the Soviets have moved their tanks just short of the Afghan border.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:17.85,1:34:19.34,Default,,0,0,0,,他们在测试我们…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}They are testing us...
Dialogue: 0,1:34:19.34,1:34:23.80,Default,,0,0,0,,要看我们是否捏造了曼哈顿博士的失踪…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...to see if we manufactured Dr. Manhattan's disappearance...
Dialogue: 0,1:34:23.80,1:34:27.07,Default,,0,0,0,,由此引诱他们出击\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...to coax a move out of them.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:27.07,1:34:31.21,Default,,0,0,0,,如果他们意识到这不是骗局 他们大概会开始发动空中袭击\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}GENERAL 1: If they realize it's not a hoax, they'll probably start with air strikes.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:31.21,1:34:35.45,Default,,0,0,0,,如果他们做了 就会在几天内控制阿富汗\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}If they do, they'll have Afghanistan under control in a matter of days.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:35.70,1:34:40.55,Default,,0,0,0,,核科学家监督组已经把"末日时钟"拨到…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}A watchdog group of nuclear scientists has moved the Doomsday Clock...
Dialogue: 0,1:34:40.55,1:34:42.95,Default,,0,0,0,,差2分钟到午夜\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...to two minutes until midnight.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:42.95,1:34:46.29,Default,,0,0,0,,把这烂东西撤下屏幕\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}NIXON: Get this shit off the screen.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:46.29,1:34:49.49,Default,,0,0,0,,这些混蛋算老几 来说末日接近时间?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Who are these assholes to say when doomsday approaches?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:49.49,1:34:52.13,Default,,0,0,0,,末日接近时间由我来说了算\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I say when doomsday is approaching.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:57.65,1:34:59.25,Default,,0,0,0,,那么\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Now, then.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:00.29,1:35:02.94,Default,,0,0,0,,华沙条约的其他成员国呢?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}What about the rest of the Warsaw Pact countries?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:02.94,1:35:07.31,Default,,0,0,0,,捷克斯洛伐克、波兰和东德 已经动员他们的部队\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Czechoslovakia, Poland and East Germany have mobilized their forces.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:07.31,1:35:10.65,Default,,0,0,0,,但是还没有动作 他们在玩"等等看"\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}But no movement yet. They're playing a wait-and-see.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:10.65,1:35:12.45,Default,,0,0,0,,让俄国人领头\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Letting the Russians take the lead.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:16.64,1:35:19.99,Default,,0,0,0,,大胆行动 亨利 这才是我们现在需要的\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Bold moves, Henry. That's what's needed right now.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:19.99,1:35:22.93,Default,,0,0,0,,不能让这些混蛋觉得我们软弱\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}We can't let these fuckers think we're weak.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:22.93,1:35:27.38,Default,,0,0,0,,是啊 他们一定怕"疯子理查德·尼克松"\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Yes. They must fear the madman Richard Nixon.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:32.29,1:35:35.93,Default,,0,0,0,,要多久我们才能准备好先发攻击?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}How soon can we be ready for a preemptive strike?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:36.93,1:35:38.10,Default,,0,0,0,,两天之后\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Two days.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:38.36,1:35:42.38,Default,,0,0,0,,我们有54%的几率在他们的导弹升空之前…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}We have a 54 percent chance of wiping out the entire U.S.S.R...
Dialogue: 0,1:35:42.38,1:35:44.64,Default,,0,0,0,,扫平整个苏联\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...before they get their missiles airborne.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:46.07,1:35:47.82,Default,,0,0,0,,我们的损失会是什么?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}What would our losses be?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:47.82,1:35:49.85,Default,,0,0,0,,保守地估算…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Assuming conservative projections...
Dialogue: 0,1:35:49.85,1:35:53.39,Default,,0,0,0,,我们能预先摧毁多少苏维埃核弹头\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...of how many Soviet warheads are destroyed beforehand...
Dialogue: 0,1:35:53.39,1:35:55.45,Default,,0,0,0,,我们会失去东海岸的全部\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...we'll lose all of the East Coast.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:55.71,1:35:57.41,Default,,0,0,0,,这将是…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}The last gasp...
Dialogue: 0,1:35:58.11,1:36:00.58,Default,,0,0,0,,哈佛校园的最后喘息了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...of the Harvard establishment.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:01.02,1:36:04.46,Default,,0,0,0,,让我们看看他们怎么走上绝路的\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Let's see them think their way out of fission.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:04.46,1:36:08.20,Default,,0,0,0,,根据预期风向模型 辐射云会飘往南方\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}With anticipated wind patterns, the fallout drift would head south.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:08.20,1:36:10.57,Default,,0,0,0,,墨西哥会遭受最坏结果\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Mexico would catch the worst of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:10.57,1:36:13.10,Default,,0,0,0,,大部分美国农业区可能不会受影响\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Most of the farm belt might remain unaffected.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:13.10,1:36:14.26,Default,,0,0,0,,不算太糟…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Not so bad...
Dialogue: 0,1:36:15.37,1:36:17.68,Default,,0,0,0,,全面考虑下来\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...all things considered.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:20.07,1:36:22.05,Default,,0,0,0,,总统先生…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}GENERAL 2: Mr. President...
Dialogue: 0,1:36:22.05,1:36:23.85,Default,,0,0,0,,你打算怎么做?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...what would you like to do?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:32.05,1:36:34.50,Default,,0,0,0,,把我们的戒备状态升到2级\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Take us to DEFCON two.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:34.50,1:36:36.51,Default,,0,0,0,,开始给导弹加燃料\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Begin fueling the bombers.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:37.12,1:36:40.12,Default,,0,0,0,,曼哈顿博士有两天时间\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Dr. Manhattan has two days.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:40.46,1:36:42.41,Default,,0,0,0,,那之后…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}After that...
Dialogue: 0,1:36:42.41,1:36:46.21,Default,,0,0,0,,人类就掌握在比我更高层的人手里了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...humanity is in the hands of a higher authority than mine.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:46.75,1:36:49.63,Default,,0,0,0,,让我们希望他站在我们这边吧\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Let's just hope he's on our side.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:50.87,1:36:53.12,Default,,0,0,0,,- 肯定有办法接近他的 - 打搅了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}FORBES: There must be a way to reach him. LAURIE: Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:53.12,1:36:54.95,Default,,0,0,0,,无线电广播、太空飞船\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}FORBES: Radio transmission, space shuttles...
Dialogue: 0,1:36:54.95,1:36:56.35,Default,,0,0,0,,- 打扰了 - 什么?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}LAURIE: Excuse me. FORBES: What?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:56.35,1:36:58.67,Default,,0,0,0,,我要去趟洗手间\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}LAURIE: I need to use the restroom.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:20.26,1:37:22.01,Default,,0,0,0,,你还不明白吗?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Don't you understand?
Dialogue: 0,1:37:22.01,1:37:24.81,Default,,0,0,0,,能把乔恩带回来的人只有乔恩\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}The only thing that can bring Jon back is Jon.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:24.81,1:37:26.95,Default,,0,0,0,,如果他想找到我 他会的\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}If he wants to find me, he will.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:26.95,1:37:29.58,Default,,0,0,0,,我这一生当囚徒当够了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I've been a prisoner in my life long enough.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:29.96,1:37:31.80,Default,,0,0,0,,没有曼哈顿博士在这里…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}MAN: Without Dr. Manhattan around...
Dialogue: 0,1:37:31.80,1:37:34.72,Default,,0,0,0,,威吓苏联遵守和平 维特先生…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...to bully the Russians into peace, Mr. Veidt...
Dialogue: 0,1:37:34.72,1:37:39.30,Default,,0,0,0,,人们将会需要依赖那些过时但实用的能源\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...people are going to need good, old-fashioned energy to rely on.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:39.30,1:37:41.13,Default,,0,0,0,,你能明白的\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You can understand.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:41.13,1:37:46.45,Default,,0,0,0,,世界不能突然放弃使用原油和核子能\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}The world can't just quit on oil and nuclear power cold turkey.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:46.45,1:37:48.82,Default,,0,0,0,,你会在一夜之间崩溃我们的整个经济\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You'll dismantle our entire economy overnight.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:48.82,1:37:49.85,Default,,0,0,0,,你说得对 李\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You're right, Lee.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:49.85,1:37:51.74,Default,,0,0,0,,而且为什么要免费能源?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}And why free energy?
Dialogue: 0,1:37:51.74,1:37:54.82,Default,,0,0,0,,其实 "免费"不过是"社会主义"的代名词\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Well, "free" is just another word for "socialist."
Dialogue: 0,1:37:54.82,1:37:56.95,Default,,0,0,0,,我们也许不得不开展一项公开调查…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}We might have to make a public inquiry...
Dialogue: 0,1:37:56.95,1:38:00.40,Default,,0,0,0,,你过去可能加入过什么共产团体\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...into any past communist affiliations you might have had.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:00.64,1:38:03.66,Default,,0,0,0,,拉科卡先生 各位…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}ADRIAN: Mr. Lacocca, gentlemen...
Dialogue: 0,1:38:04.67,1:38:07.13,Default,,0,0,0,,我尊重你们的地位…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...I respect your position...
Dialogue: 0,1:38:07.13,1:38:10.98,Default,,0,0,0,,还有你们作为业界首领的成就 我的确尊重\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...and what you've accomplished as captains of industry. I do.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:11.38,1:38:13.87,Default,,0,0,0,,你们想了解我的过去 嗯?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You wanna know my past? Hm?
Dialogue: 0,1:38:14.68,1:38:17.57,Default,,0,0,0,,好 愉快之至\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Okay. Happily.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:17.57,1:38:21.20,Default,,0,0,0,,这是公开的记录 我17岁时父母双亡…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}It's a matter of public record that by 17, both my parents were dead...
Dialogue: 0,1:38:21.20,1:38:23.06,Default,,0,0,0,,留下我一人\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...leaving me alone.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:24.06,1:38:27.58,Default,,0,0,0,,我猜你们可以说 我总是孤身一人\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I guess you could say I've always been alone.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:27.58,1:38:32.65,Default,,0,0,0,,他们说我是这世上最聪明的人 但真相是我时常感觉愚蠢…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}They say I'm the smartest man in the world, but the truth is I've often felt stupid...
Dialogue: 0,1:38:32.65,1:38:36.41,Default,,0,0,0,,因为没有能力与任何人牵连…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...at being unable to relate to anyone.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:36.41,1:38:39.89,Default,,0,0,0,,哦 我指的是活着的人\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Well, anyone living, that is.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:39.89,1:38:42.05,Default,,0,0,0,,唯一一位我感觉有亲情的人…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}The only person with whom I felt kinship...
Dialogue: 0,1:38:42.05,1:38:45.33,Default,,0,0,0,,在基督降世300年之前就死了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...died 300 years before the birth of Christ.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:45.33,1:38:50.87,Default,,0,0,0,,马其顿的亚历山大 或者你们熟知的：亚历山大大帝\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Alexander of Macedonia, or Alexander the Great, as you know him.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:50.87,1:38:54.81,Default,,0,0,0,,他对于联合世界的远见…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}His vision of a united world was...
Dialogue: 0,1:38:55.73,1:38:59.08,Default,,0,0,0,,其实 是史无前例的\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Well, it was unprecedented.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:59.08,1:39:00.94,Default,,0,0,0,,我想要…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I wanted...
Dialogue: 0,1:39:00.94,1:39:03.46,Default,,0,0,0,,我需要…去匹配他的功绩…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...needed to match his accomplishments...
Dialogue: 0,1:39:03.46,1:39:07.34,Default,,0,0,0,,所以我立志在今日的世界践行古训\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...so I resolved to apply antiquity's teachings to our world today.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:07.34,1:39:10.47,Default,,0,0,0,,于是开始了我的征服之路\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}And so began my path to conquest.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:10.47,1:39:13.86,Default,,0,0,0,,不是征服人类…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Conquest not of men...
Dialogue: 0,1:39:13.86,1:39:16.71,Default,,0,0,0,,而是征服那些困扰人类的邪恶\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...but of the evils that beset them.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:17.15,1:39:22.09,Default,,0,0,0,,矿物燃料、原油、核能…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Fossil fuels, oil, nuclear power...
Dialogue: 0,1:39:22.09,1:39:23.10,Default,,0,0,0,,它们就像是毒品\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...are like a drug
Dialogue: 0,1:39:23.10,1:39:25.80,Default,,0,0,0,,而你们各位 跟那些国外投资者 就是毒贩\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}and you, gentlmen, along with foreign interests are the pushers.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:25.80,1:39:26.82,Default,,0,0,0,,好了 听着\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Now, listen.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:27.22,1:39:28.66,Default,,0,0,0,,不\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}ADRIAN: No.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:31.19,1:39:32.99,Default,,0,0,0,,你们听着\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You listen.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:34.23,1:39:36.83,Default,,0,0,0,,这世界将会幸存…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}The world will survive...
Dialogue: 0,1:39:36.83,1:39:40.37,Default,,0,0,0,,而且它应得的 应该超过你们所能提供的\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...and it deserves more than you've been able to provide.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:40.75,1:39:43.38,Default,,0,0,0,,所以让我们直说吧 好吧?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}So let's cut to it, shall we?
Dialogue: 0,1:39:43.38,1:39:46.04,Default,,0,0,0,,私下里我的价值远超你们所有的公司合计\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Privately I'm worth more than all of your corporations combined.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:46.04,1:39:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,我可以收购并出售你们三次 这点你们应该在作决定时考虑进去\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I could buy and sell you three times over, which is something you should factor into your decision...
Dialogue: 0,1:39:50.00,1:39:51.42,Default,,0,0,0,,你们是否应该选择…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...should you choose to make our...
Dialogue: 0,1:39:52.71,1:39:56.12,Default,,0,0,0,,把我们的分歧 公之于众\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...disagreement public.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:57.59,1:40:00.02,Default,,0,0,0,,我想你们知道该怎么做了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I think you know the way out.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:01.76,1:40:03.49,Default,,0,0,0,,失陪了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Gentlemen.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:06.00,1:40:09.66,Default,,0,0,0,,玩具公司的人想和你讨论 法老王系列的新反派\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}The toy people wanna talk to you about new villains for the Ozymandias line.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:09.66,1:40:11.42,Default,,0,0,0,,好像老敌人都死光了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Seems all the old villains are dead
Dialogue: 0,1:40:11.76,1:40:13.34,Default,,0,0,0,,维特先生?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Mr. Veidt?
Dialogue: 0,1:40:13.34,1:40:14.65,Default,,0,0,0,,我想我有些主意\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I think I have some ideas.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:15.25,1:40:16.56,Default,,0,0,0,,维特先生?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Mr. Veidt?
Dialogue: 0,1:40:17.11,1:40:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,我认为我们开头这一步没走好\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I think we got off on the wrong foot.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:29.41,1:40:30.51,Default,,0,0,0,,(新世界递送)
Dialogue: 0,1:40:59.00,1:41:00.54,Default,,0,0,0,,他嘴里有剧毒胶囊\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}He's got a poison capsule.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:01.22,1:41:03.78,Default,,0,0,0,,不准吞下去 你这混蛋！谁派你来的?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Don't bite down, you son of a bitch. Who sent you?
Dialogue: 0,1:41:03.78,1:41:05.84,Default,,0,0,0,,我要一个名字\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I want a name.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:05.84,1:41:06.95,Default,,0,0,0,,把名字告诉我\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Give me a name!
Dialogue: 0,1:41:19.07,1:41:20.52,Default,,0,0,0,,自杀胶囊\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}LAURIE: Suicide pill.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:21.47,1:41:24.55,Default,,0,0,0,,氰化钾 入口即死\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Potassium cyanide. Guy was dead before he hit the ground.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:24.55,1:41:26.41,Default,,0,0,0,,谢谢 亲\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}WAITRESS: Thanks, hon.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:26.91,1:41:28.93,Default,,0,0,0,,那么罗夏说对了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Then Rorschach was right.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:29.31,1:41:31.48,Default,,0,0,0,,这不是个别案件\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}This wasn't some lone nut.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:31.48,1:41:32.58,Default,,0,0,0,,是一个组织\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}It's an organization:
Dialogue: 0,1:41:33.45,1:41:35.74,Default,,0,0,0,,资金充足 装备精良\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Well-funded, well-equipped.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:36.55,1:41:38.66,Default,,0,0,0,,可是现在谁会要杀我们?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}But who'd wanna kill us now?
Dialogue: 0,1:41:39.90,1:41:43.09,Default,,0,0,0,,我不知道 但是外面已经不安全了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I don't know, but it's not safe out here.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:48.46,1:41:50.59,Default,,0,0,0,,那个…没有乔恩的消息?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}So no word from Jon?
Dialogue: 0,1:41:51.40,1:41:53.03,Default,,0,0,0,,没有\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}No.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:53.40,1:41:55.30,Default,,0,0,0,,你看…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Well, listen...
Dialogue: 0,1:41:55.81,1:41:57.64,Default,,0,0,0,,为什么你不过来和我一起住呢?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...why don't you come stay with me?
Dialogue: 0,1:41:58.84,1:42:02.31,Default,,0,0,0,,不了 你真好心 但我不想打扰\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Oh, no. That's sweet, but I wouldn't wanna impose.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:02.31,1:42:05.82,Default,,0,0,0,,哦 不 就当帮我个忙好了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Oh, no. No. Think of it as doing me a favor.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:07.52,1:42:09.99,Default,,0,0,0,,这样我就不用担心你一人在外面了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I wouldn't have to worry about you being out there.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:13.26,1:42:14.62,Default,,0,0,0,,好吧\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:17.56,1:42:23.15,Default,,0,0,0,,罗夏日记 1985年10月21日\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Rorschach's journal, October 21 st, 1985.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:23.15,1:42:27.26,Default,,0,0,0,,在第43街和第7街 看见德雷伯格和朱庇特 吃完快餐出来\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}On 43rd and 7th, saw Dreiberg and Jupiter leaving diner.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:28.00,1:42:30.60,Default,,0,0,0,,我不戴面具他们就不认识我\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}They didn't know me without my mask.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:31.44,1:42:33.26,Default,,0,0,0,,外遇吗?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}An affair?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:33.26,1:42:36.31,Default,,0,0,0,,她有没有伤曼哈顿博士的心促使他亡走?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Did she break Manhattan's heart to engineer his exile...
Dialogue: 0,1:42:36.31,1:42:39.43,Default,,0,0,0,,从而给德雷伯格腾地方?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}... to make room for Dreiberg?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:39.43,1:42:42.94,Default,,0,0,0,,曼哈顿到底有没有一颗心可以受伤呢?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Does Manhattan even have a heart to break?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:44.19,1:42:47.14,Default,,0,0,0,,小巷阴冷而又荒凉\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}The alley was cold, deserted.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:47.14,1:42:51.91,Default,,0,0,0,,我的东西就在原地 等着我\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}My things were where I left them, waiting for me.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:51.91,1:42:56.45,Default,,0,0,0,,我的大衣 我的鞋子 我一尘不染的手套\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}My coat, my shoes, my spotless gloves.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:57.83,1:42:59.98,Default,,0,0,0,,我的脸\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}My face.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:59.98,1:43:04.09,Default,,0,0,0,,穿上他们 我就卸下了伪装\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Putting them on, I abandoned my disguise...
Dialogue: 0,1:43:04.09,1:43:06.23,Default,,0,0,0,,变回我自己\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}... became myself.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:06.74,1:43:09.99,Default,,0,0,0,,摆脱了恐惧和软弱\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Free from fear or weakness...
Dialogue: 0,1:43:09.99,1:43:11.10,Default,,0,0,0,,还有欲念\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}... or lust.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:12.68,1:43:14.70,Default,,0,0,0,,小巷深处\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Down alley...
Dialogue: 0,1:43:14.70,1:43:16.73,Default,,0,0,0,,听见女人尖叫\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}... heard woman scream.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:16.73,1:43:20.90,Default,,0,0,0,,城市夜间合唱团的第一个扬起的音符\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}First bubbling note of city's evening chorus.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:20.90,1:43:22.87,Default,,0,0,0,,意图强奸?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Attempted rape.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:22.87,1:43:24.21,Default,,0,0,0,,抢劫?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Mugging.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:24.21,1:43:25.69,Default,,0,0,0,,两样都是?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Both.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:27.20,1:43:29.05,Default,,0,0,0,,那人转过来\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}The man turned...
Dialogue: 0,1:43:29.05,1:43:32.25,Default,,0,0,0,,他的眼光里有一种奖赏\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}... and there was something rewarding in his eyes.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:33.25,1:43:35.78,Default,,0,0,0,,有时候夜晚对我很慷慨\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Sometimes the night is generous to me.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:41.83,1:43:46.16,Default,,0,0,0,,去刺杀维特的是一个本地的底层人 名叫罗伊·切斯\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Veidt's assassin was a local lowlife named Roy Chess.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:46.73,1:43:49.49,Default,,0,0,0,,在他的公寓里 我找到了线索\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}At his apartment, I found clues.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:50.63,1:43:53.92,Default,,0,0,0,,似乎他在金字塔跨国公司工作\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Seems he worked at Pyramid Transnational.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:53.92,1:43:56.50,Default,,0,0,0,,我以前见过这个标志\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I've seen the logo before...
Dialogue: 0,1:43:56.91,1:43:58.97,Default,,0,0,0,,在摩罗神家里\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}... at Moloch's.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:29.34,1:44:32.34,Default,,0,0,0,,今天有人想枪杀世上最聪明的人 摩罗神\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Someone tried to shoot the world's smartest man today, Moloch.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:33.11,1:44:35.97,Default,,0,0,0,,是个为金字塔跨国公司干活的人\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Guy worked for Pyramid Transnational.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:35.97,1:44:38.26,Default,,0,0,0,,应该不仅仅是送货服务 照我看来\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}More than a just delivery service, I take it.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:38.26,1:44:42.53,Default,,0,0,0,,我上次来的时候 看见同一家公司签发的退休金支票\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Last time I was here, I saw a pension check written from the same company.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:42.53,1:44:46.06,Default,,0,0,0,,我猜想这是个幌子公司 是某个想要我们蒙面英雄命的人开设的\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I'm guessing it's a front set up by whoever wants us masks dead.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:46.06,1:44:47.70,Default,,0,0,0,,现在别再撒谎了 摩罗神\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Now, no more lies, Moloch.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:47.70,1:44:49.75,Default,,0,0,0,,谁在运营金字塔公司?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Who runs Pyramid?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:54.63,1:44:56.32,Default,,0,0,0,,罗夏\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}FINE [O VER BULLHORN]: Rorschach.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:56.32,1:44:58.86,Default,,0,0,0,,我们是警察 我们知道你在里面\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}This is the police. We know you're in there.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:58.86,1:45:00.91,Default,,0,0,0,,不 不！\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}No. No!
Dialogue: 0,1:45:00.91,1:45:04.20,Default,,0,0,0,,如果有人和你在一起 请让他们安全地出来\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}If there's anybody in there with you, send them out unharmed.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:04.20,1:45:07.29,Default,,0,0,0,,不 不 不 不\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}No. No, no, no!
Dialogue: 0,1:45:07.29,1:45:11.96,Default,,0,0,0,,被陷害了 落入陷阱 愚蠢 愚蠢！\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Framed. Walked right into it. Stupid, stupid, stupid!
Dialogue: 0,1:45:11.96,1:45:13.66,Default,,0,0,0,,永远 永远不投降\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Never, never surrender.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:13.66,1:45:17.14,Default,,0,0,0,,好吧 我希望你已经准备好了 英雄\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}All right. I hope you're ready, hero.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:17.14,1:45:18.05,Default,,0,0,0,,随时奉陪\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}When you are.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:40.68,1:45:41.78,Default,,0,0,0,,一\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}One...
Dialogue: 0,1:45:46.72,1:45:47.83,Default,,0,0,0,,二\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...two...
Dialogue: 0,1:45:51.67,1:45:52.92,Default,,0,0,0,,三\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...three.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:44.84,1:46:46.60,Default,,0,0,0,,加把劲\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Come on.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:57.42,1:46:58.90,Default,,0,0,0,,这个混蛋\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}MAN: Son of a bitch.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:59.82,1:47:02.28,Default,,0,0,0,,- 天 这家伙臭死了 - 把他的面具拿掉\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}- Christ, he stinks. - Get that mask off him.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:02.28,1:47:05.38,Default,,0,0,0,,- 拿下了 - 不 不！\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}- I got it. - No. No!
Dialogue: 0,1:47:05.38,1:47:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,我的脸 把我脸还我\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}My face! Give me back my face!
Dialogue: 0,1:47:08.93,1:47:11.65,Default,,0,0,0,,蒙面义警罗夏已被逮捕\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}The masked vigilante Rorschach was apprehended...
Dialogue: 0,1:47:11.65,1:47:15.72,Default,,0,0,0,,确认身份是沃特·科瓦克斯 一位35岁的白人男性\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}... and identified as Walter Kovacs, a 35-year-old white male.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:15.72,1:47:18.61,Default,,0,0,0,,关于科瓦克斯所知不多 不过他已被控告…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Little's known about Kovacs, but he was charged with the murder...
Dialogue: 0,1:47:18.61,1:47:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,谋杀埃德加·雅各比 后者被发现在布朗克斯的家中头部中枪\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}... of Edgar Jacobi, found shot in the head in his home in the Bronx.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:22.96,1:47:26.16,Default,,0,0,0,,在艰难的抓捕过程中…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Police officers were injured and Jacobi's home was set ablaze...
Dialogue: 0,1:47:26.16,1:47:28.74,Default,,0,0,0,,多名警员受伤 雅各比的家被烧\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}... during the violent course of the capture.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:32.56,1:47:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,罗夏\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}MAN 1: Rorschach!
Dialogue: 0,1:47:34.00,1:47:37.81,Default,,0,0,0,,我会像干你妈一样干死你\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I'm gonna fuck you like I fucked your mother!
Dialogue: 0,1:47:44.40,1:47:46.64,Default,,0,0,0,,出来 罗夏\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}MAN 2: Come on out, Rorschach!
Dialogue: 0,1:47:49.79,1:47:52.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\a6}(罗夏 尸体在逮捕现场被发现)
Dialogue: 0,1:47:50.24,1:47:52.87,Default,,0,0,0,,我早知道这家伙是个怪人\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}BERNIE: I knew this guy was a kook.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:53.44,1:47:54.96,Default,,0,0,0,,但他是罗夏…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}But Rorschach...
Dialogue: 0,1:47:54.96,1:47:57.93,Default,,0,0,0,,通常我对这种事情有一种直觉\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Usually I got an intuition about these kind of things.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:57.93,1:47:59.53,Default,,0,0,0,,本以为这哥们块头会大些\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Thought the dude would be bigger.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:59.53,1:48:01.49,Default,,0,0,0,,如你所见 孩子 你永远想不到\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}It goes to show you, kid, you never know.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:01.49,1:48:02.50,Default,,0,0,0,,喂 给我来份公报\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Hey, let me get a Gazette.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:02.50,1:48:03.35,Default,,0,0,0,,好\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:03.92,1:48:05.21,Default,,0,0,0,,喂 看到这个了吗?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Hey, you see this?
Dialogue: 0,1:48:05.21,1:48:06.51,Default,,0,0,0,,他原来是我的一个老主顾\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}He was a customer of mine.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:06.51,1:48:09.12,Default,,0,0,0,,- 以前老是来这里 - 我靠\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}- Used to come here all the time. - No shit?
Dialogue: 0,1:48:11.36,1:48:14.09,Default,,0,0,0,,嘿 伯尼 有好消息吗?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Hey, Bernie. Any good news?
Dialogue: 0,1:48:23.87,1:48:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,不管我们是谁 不管我们在哪里\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}MARINER: Whoever we are, wherever we reside...
Dialogue: 0,1:48:27.41,1:48:30.24,Default,,0,0,0,,我们靠杀人犯的妄想而存活\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}... we exist on the whim of murderers.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:34.92,1:48:38.03,Default,,0,0,0,,我几乎认不出我的老朋友瑞德里\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I hardly recognized my old friend Ridley.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:38.03,1:48:41.34,Default,,0,0,0,,我无法迫使自己告诉他 他只是原来的他自身的…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I could not bring myself to tell him he was a horrible reflection...
Dialogue: 0,1:48:41.34,1:48:43.53,Default,,0,0,0,,…一副可怕的投射\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}... of his former self.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:43.53,1:48:48.24,Default,,0,0,0,,我必须带他回家 趁他变得更糟之前\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I really must get him home before... Before he gets any worse.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:48.24,1:48:50.39,Default,,0,0,0,,在他被压垮之前\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Before he succumbs.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:50.76,1:48:56.43,Default,,0,0,0,,我曾听说 每天少于一品脱 人可能喝咸水幸存\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I've heard that on less than a pint daily, a man might survive drinking saltwater.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:56.43,1:48:58.02,Default,,0,0,0,,船长?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}RIDLEY: Captain?
Dialogue: 0,1:48:58.02,1:48:59.56,Default,,0,0,0,,你在干什么 船长?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}What are you doing, captain?
Dialogue: 0,1:49:02.05,1:49:04.94,Default,,0,0,0,,我去戴维斯城 就这样\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I'm headed for Davidstown. That's what.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:05.35,1:49:08.04,Default,,0,0,0,,我需要去警告 警告大家\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I need to warn everyone.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:10.52,1:49:14.12,Default,,0,0,0,,你以为你会在黑货船号之前赶到戴维斯城?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You think you'll reach Davidstown in advance of the Black Freighter?
Dialogue: 0,1:49:14.42,1:49:18.67,Default,,0,0,0,,与世隔绝已经让你疯狂了 船长 真的疯了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Isolation has made you mad, captain. Mad, indeed.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:19.60,1:49:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,但我们必须一试\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}But we must try.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:21.00,1:49:22.45,Default,,0,0,0,,你是个傻瓜\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You are a fool.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:22.45,1:49:25.05,Default,,0,0,0,,你独自在黑货船的袭击中幸存\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You alone survived the Freighter's attack.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:25.05,1:49:29.43,Default,,0,0,0,,命运对你微笑 而你却唾在它脸上\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Fortune has smiled upon you, and you spit in its face.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:29.43,1:49:34.97,Default,,0,0,0,,掉转你可悲的破筏子远走高飞吧 有多远走多远\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Turn your wretched craft around and go far away, as far away as you can.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:37.01,1:49:41.02,Default,,0,0,0,,不 不 我的家人 我要保护她们\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}No. No, my family. I must protect them.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:42.22,1:49:44.07,Default,,0,0,0,,黑货船已经到那里了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}The Black Freighter is already there.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:44.79,1:49:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,你的妻子 死了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Your wife, dead.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:46.48,1:49:49.37,Default,,0,0,0,,- 你的孩子们 死了  - 你闭嘴\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}- Your children, dead. - Shut your mouth.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:49.37,1:49:53.78,Default,,0,0,0,,你辜负了你的家人 如同你辜负了你的船员\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You have failed your family, like you have failed your crew.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:15.08,1:50:18.60,Default,,0,0,0,,你最后会像他们一样死去 你徒然送命而已\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You'll end up dead like them. You give your life in vain.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:18.60,1:50:20.98,Default,,0,0,0,,我的生命送给高尚\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I give my life in nobility.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:23.67,1:50:25.42,Default,,0,0,0,,就算我的努力失败了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Even if I fail in my attempt,
Dialogue: 0,1:50:25.42,1:50:28.75,Default,,0,0,0,,我会因在天堂再见到家人而得到慰籍\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I take solace in the fact that I will see my family again in heaven.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:28.75,1:50:30.25,Default,,0,0,0,,天堂?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Heaven?
Dialogue: 0,1:50:30.25,1:50:32.41,Default,,0,0,0,,噢 根本没有天堂 船长\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Oh, there is no heaven, captain.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:32.87,1:50:35.03,Default,,0,0,0,,相信我吧 长官\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Believe me, sir.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:35.03,1:50:37.37,Default,,0,0,0,,有的话我现在就该知道了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I would know by now.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:43.98,1:50:45.75,Default,,0,0,0,,沃特·科瓦克斯\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}MAN: Walter Kovacs.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:45.75,1:50:48.70,Default,,0,0,0,,这是你的真名? 沃特?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Is that your name? Walter?
Dialogue: 0,1:50:48.70,1:50:52.94,Default,,0,0,0,,让我解释一下你的处境 沃特\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Well, let me explain your situation here, Walter.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:52.94,1:50:54.67,Default,,0,0,0,,你跟我合作\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You cooperate with me...
Dialogue: 0,1:50:54.67,1:50:59.48,Default,,0,0,0,,我也许就能说服他们 给你应该的医疗救治\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...and I may be able to convince them that you should be treated medically.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:59.48,1:51:03.02,Default,,0,0,0,,在一家医院 我相信那对你有好处\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}In a hospital. I believe that would be good for you.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:03.40,1:51:09.23,Default,,0,0,0,,可是当局想把你和普通犯人关在一起\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}But the authorities wanna put you with the general population.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:10.01,1:51:13.15,Default,,0,0,0,,- 监狱就是监狱  - 啊 没错\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}- Prison's a prison. - Uh-huh. Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:13.85,1:51:17.11,Default,,0,0,0,,不过差别在于 在那里\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}But the difference is, down there...
Dialogue: 0,1:51:17.68,1:51:19.12,Default,,0,0,0,,你会被生吞活剥的\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...you'd be eaten alive.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:20.02,1:51:24.33,Default,,0,0,0,,你导致这里很多人坐牢 沃特\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You're responsible for a lot of them being in prison here, Walter.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:27.25,1:51:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,告诉我你看见了什么\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Tell me what you see.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:28.88,1:51:33.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs50\an8}(罗夏墨迹测试 通过抽象图像反映被测者的潜意识 也是"罗夏"这个名字的由来)
Dialogue: 0,1:51:33.96,1:51:35.72,Default,,0,0,0,,一只漂亮的蝴蝶\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}A pretty butterfly.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:39.54,1:51:41.35,Default,,0,0,0,,现在呢? 你看见了什么?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}What about now? What do you see here?
Dialogue: 0,1:51:46.38,1:51:47.52,Default,,0,0,0,,妈妈?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Mom?
Dialogue: 0,1:51:47.88,1:51:49.27,Default,,0,0,0,,他在伤害你吗?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Is he hurting you?
Dialogue: 0,1:51:49.27,1:51:50.73,Default,,0,0,0,,你他妈的还有个孩子\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You got a fucking kid in here.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:51.24,1:51:52.64,Default,,0,0,0,,这个我家里就有\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I get that at home.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:52.64,1:51:55.91,Default,,0,0,0,,杂种 那次我应该堕胎的\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Bastard. I should have had that abortion.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:05.56,1:52:07.58,Default,,0,0,0,,一些漂亮的花儿\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Some nice flowers.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:13.13,1:52:14.97,Default,,0,0,0,,我听说这小子老妈是个妓女\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}BO Y 1: I heard this guy's mom's a whore.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:17.09,1:52:20.01,Default,,0,0,0,,你有没有从她那里染上什么病?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Did you catch any diseases from her?
Dialogue: 0,1:52:20.01,1:52:22.38,Default,,0,0,0,,有吗? 妓女的儿子?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Huh? Whoreson.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:22.90,1:52:24.98,Default,,0,0,0,,听我说 弱智\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Listen to me, retard.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:26.18,1:52:29.41,Default,,0,0,0,,喂 你觉得她会不会为一美元给我吸屌?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}BO Y 2: Hey, you think she'd suck my dick for a dollar?
Dialogue: 0,1:52:48.04,1:52:49.25,Default,,0,0,0,,云彩\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Clouds.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:54.11,1:52:56.93,Default,,0,0,0,,跟我谈谈罗夏 你愿意吗 沃特?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Tell me about Rorschach. Will you do that, Walter?
Dialogue: 0,1:52:56.93,1:52:58.92,Default,,0,0,0,,你一直叫我沃特\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You keep calling me Walter.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:59.36,1:53:00.64,Default,,0,0,0,,我不喜欢你\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I don't like you.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:01.62,1:53:05.89,Default,,0,0,0,,你不喜欢我 好吧 具体是为什么呢?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You don't like me. All right, why is that, exactly?
Dialogue: 0,1:53:05.89,1:53:07.44,Default,,0,0,0,,你肥胖\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You're fat.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:07.96,1:53:11.19,Default,,0,0,0,,富有 自由情感\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Wealthy. Liberal sensibilities.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:11.19,1:53:13.41,Default,,0,0,0,,你所谓的怜悯\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}What you call compassion.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:13.41,1:53:15.89,Default,,0,0,0,,想保护和理解那些犯罪\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Wanting to protect and understand the guilty.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:15.89,1:53:19.95,Default,,0,0,0,,这个腐败的社会 称之为康复的东西\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}This rotting society, what it calls rehabilitation.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:19.95,1:53:21.58,Default,,0,0,0,,无异于妥协\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Nothing short of compromise.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:21.58,1:53:24.33,Default,,0,0,0,,想让你正常也是一种妥协吗?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Is it a compromise to want to make you well?
Dialogue: 0,1:53:24.33,1:53:28.57,Default,,0,0,0,,这儿有别的人行为比我极端 医生\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}There are other men in here with behavior more extreme than mine, doctor.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:29.25,1:53:32.29,Default,,0,0,0,,当然他们不出名 对吧?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Of course, they're not famous, are they?
Dialogue: 0,1:53:32.62,1:53:35.31,Default,,0,0,0,,你想了解罗夏?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You wanna know about Rorschach?
Dialogue: 0,1:53:36.79,1:53:38.63,Default,,0,0,0,,我来跟你说说罗夏\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I'll tell you about Rorschach.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:39.86,1:53:42.56,Default,,0,0,0,,一旦一个人看过社会的污黑部分\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Once a man has seen society's black underbelly...
Dialogue: 0,1:53:42.56,1:53:44.35,Default,,0,0,0,,他就再不能置之不理\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...he can never turn his back on it.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:45.21,1:53:48.02,Default,,0,0,0,,再也不能假装 像你那样\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Never pretend, like you do...
Dialogue: 0,1:53:48.02,1:53:49.80,Default,,0,0,0,,假装它不存在\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...that it doesn't exist
Dialogue: 0,1:53:49.80,1:53:51.83,Default,,0,0,0,,不管有谁命令他转头他顾\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}no matter who orders him to look the other way.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:52.52,1:53:56.32,Default,,0,0,0,,我们做这件事 不是因为…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}We don't do this thing...
Dialogue: 0,1:53:56.32,1:53:58.53,Default,,0,0,0,,获得了许可\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...because it's permitted.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:59.18,1:54:01.74,Default,,0,0,0,,我们做是因为不得不做\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}We do it because we have to.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:02.41,1:54:04.74,Default,,0,0,0,,我们做是因为我们被迫如此\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}We do it because we're compelled.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:06.58,1:54:09.12,Default,,0,0,0,,那时候我正在调查一件绑架案\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I was investigating a kidnap case.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:10.75,1:54:12.71,Default,,0,0,0,,布莱尔·罗奇\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Blaire Roche.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:12.71,1:54:14.45,Default,,0,0,0,,6岁大的女孩\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Six-year-old girl.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:15.06,1:54:16.34,Default,,0,0,0,,我那时年轻\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I was young then.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:17.09,1:54:19.43,Default,,0,0,0,,对罪犯太手软\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Too soft on criminals.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:20.36,1:54:21.99,Default,,0,0,0,,我让他们活命\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I let them live.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:23.42,1:54:25.30,Default,,0,0,0,,打断一个人的胳膊 得到线索\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Broke a man's arm to get a tip.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:25.92,1:54:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,指引我来到失踪女孩的位置\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Led me to the missing girl's location.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:36.61,1:54:39.05,Default,,0,0,0,,我知道那女孩在这儿\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I knew the girl was here...
Dialogue: 0,1:54:39.38,1:54:42.74,Default,,0,0,0,,不过我搜查那地方时什么也没看到\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}... but when I searched the place, I saw nothing.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:43.62,1:54:46.05,Default,,0,0,0,,然后我找到了她\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}And then I found her.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:35.40,1:55:37.27,Default,,0,0,0,,弗雷德\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}MAN: Fred.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:38.14,1:55:39.55,Default,,0,0,0,,巴尼\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Barney.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:40.14,1:55:42.67,Default,,0,0,0,,谁给老爸叫两声?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Who's gonna bark for Daddy?
Dialogue: 0,1:55:48.32,1:55:51.18,Default,,0,0,0,,杀人犯回来的时候 天已经黑了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}It was dark when the murderer got back.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:53.32,1:55:54.91,Default,,0,0,0,,一片漆黑\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}As dark as it gets.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:33.66,1:56:38.52,Default,,0,0,0,,老天 谁在外面? 是谁?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Oh, God. Who's out there? Who is it?
Dialogue: 0,1:56:40.24,1:56:41.36,Default,,0,0,0,,是谁?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Who is it?
Dialogue: 0,1:56:52.04,1:56:55.62,Default,,0,0,0,,什么? 他妈的怎么回事?  你他妈的是谁?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}What? What the fuck? Who the fuck are you?
Dialogue: 0,1:56:55.86,1:56:57.18,Default,,0,0,0,,你他妈想怎么样?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}What the fuck do you want?
Dialogue: 0,1:56:58.25,1:57:00.29,Default,,0,0,0,,你弄死了我的狗 老哥！\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You killed my dogs, man!
Dialogue: 0,1:57:05.13,1:57:07.62,Default,,0,0,0,,你以为我和那个女孩有关?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You think I had something to do with that girl?
Dialogue: 0,1:57:08.22,1:57:09.84,Default,,0,0,0,,那是我发现的\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I found that.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:10.30,1:57:12.70,Default,,0,0,0,,你有什么证据? 那什么都不是\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}What evidence have you got? That's nothing.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:20.28,1:57:23.19,Default,,0,0,0,,好吧 我认罪\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Okay. I confess.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:24.28,1:57:27.07,Default,,0,0,0,,我绑架了她 我杀了她\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I kidnapped her. I killed her.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:27.75,1:57:29.24,Default,,0,0,0,,逮捕我吧\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Arrest me.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:30.04,1:57:32.24,Default,,0,0,0,,怎么了? 逮捕我！\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}What? Arrest me!
Dialogue: 0,1:57:32.59,1:57:35.37,Default,,0,0,0,,是我干的 我说了是我干的\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I did it! I said I did it!
Dialogue: 0,1:57:35.80,1:57:36.95,Default,,0,0,0,,老天哪！\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Christ.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:36.95,1:57:41.83,Default,,0,0,0,,听着 我有问题 老兄 他妈的送我进去吧 我需要帮助\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Look, I've got a problem, man. Fucking take me in. I need help.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:42.23,1:57:46.17,Default,,0,0,0,,不 不要 不要这么干 送我进去吧\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}No, don't. Don't do that. Take me in.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:46.38,1:57:48.87,Default,,0,0,0,,不要啊 不\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Don't! No!
Dialogue: 0,1:57:53.84,1:57:57.34,Default,,0,0,0,,人 被捕\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Men get arrested.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:58.75,1:58:00.90,Default,,0,0,0,,狗受死\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Dogs get put down.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:08.89,1:58:11.20,Default,,0,0,0,,我的手被震到麻痹\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Tremors of impact shook my arm.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:12.46,1:58:14.79,Default,,0,0,0,,温暖的血液溅到我脸上\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Warm blood splashed my face.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:16.03,1:58:20.13,Default,,0,0,0,,不管沃特·科瓦克斯还剩下什么 那晚都随那小姑娘而去了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Whatever was left of Walter Kovacs died that night with that little girl.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:21.21,1:58:23.46,Default,,0,0,0,,从那时起 就只有罗夏\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}From then on, there was only Rorschach.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:25.11,1:58:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,你看 医生 上帝并没有杀死那小女孩\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}See, doctor, God didn't kill that little girl.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:28.14,1:58:32.31,Default,,0,0,0,,命运并没有把她切块 宿命也没有拿她喂那些狗\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Fate didn't butcher her and destiny didn't feed her to those dogs.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:33.48,1:58:36.92,Default,,0,0,0,,要是上帝看到那晚我们俩的所作所为 他好像也不介意\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}If God saw what any of us did that night, he didn't seem to mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:38.82,1:58:40.65,Default,,0,0,0,,从那时起 我就明白\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}From then on, I knew:
Dialogue: 0,1:58:41.99,1:58:44.32,Default,,0,0,0,,上帝并没有把世界造成这样\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}God doesn't make the world this way.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:46.33,1:58:47.78,Default,,0,0,0,,是我们做的\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}We do.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:54.20,1:58:56.57,Default,,0,0,0,,我帮不了他\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I can't help him.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:08.57,1:59:10.04,Default,,0,0,0,,嘿 罗夏\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Hey, Rorschach.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:11.37,1:59:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,嘿 你很有名 是吧?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Hey, you're pretty famous, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:59:13.93,1:59:16.21,Default,,0,0,0,,罗夏 我听说你妈是个妓女\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}MAN 1: Rorschach, I heard your mother was a whore.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:16.21,1:59:17.47,Default,,0,0,0,,你知道吗?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Hey, you know what?
Dialogue: 0,1:59:17.80,1:59:19.93,Default,,0,0,0,,我也挺出名的\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I'm pretty famous too.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:19.93,1:59:22.44,Default,,0,0,0,,- 我说的对不对?  - 说得对\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}- Ain't that right?  MAN 2: That's right.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:24.15,1:59:25.56,Default,,0,0,0,,你看 也许我能给你签个名\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You know, maybe I can give you an autograph.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:26.58,1:59:27.57,Default,,0,0,0,,你说怎么样 大人物?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}What you say, big boy?
Dialogue: 0,1:59:42.80,1:59:45.19,Default,,0,0,0,,你们好像没人搞明白\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}None of you seem to understand.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:45.19,1:59:46.65,Default,,0,0,0,,不是我被跟你们关在一起\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I'm not locked in here with you.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:46.65,1:59:48.36,Default,,0,0,0,,够了 住手\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}OFFICER: All right, that's it!
Dialogue: 0,1:59:49.21,1:59:51.64,Default,,0,0,0,,是你们被跟我关在一起\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You're locked in here with me.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:10.33,2:01:11.63,Default,,0,0,0,,劳瑞！\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}DAN: Laurie!
Dialogue: 0,2:01:12.66,2:01:13.99,Default,,0,0,0,,糟了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Shit.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:14.99,2:01:16.89,Default,,0,0,0,,- 撑住 - 妈的\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}DAN: Hold on. - Fuck.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:20.16,2:01:21.68,Default,,0,0,0,,我来 我来 我来\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I got it, I got it, I got it.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:26.41,2:01:29.91,Default,,0,0,0,,真抱歉 我到处探究 一定是按错了按钮\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I'm so sorry. I was snooping and must have hit the wrong button.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:29.91,2:01:31.80,Default,,0,0,0,,- 你受伤了吗?  - 没有\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}- Are you hurt? - No, no.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:31.80,2:01:34.78,Default,,0,0,0,,- 那就好 - 我没事 只是感觉很糟糕\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}- Okay. - I'm fine. I just feel so bad.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:34.78,2:01:37.03,Default,,0,0,0,,没事 别担心\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}No, don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:37.03,2:01:40.41,Default,,0,0,0,,以前就发生过 笑匠77年时就曾干过\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}It's happened before. Comedian did it back in '77.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:41.35,2:01:43.18,Default,,0,0,0,,阿基逃过了那一劫\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Archie survived that.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:43.62,2:01:48.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\a6}(他的猫头鹰形状飞行器)
Dialogue: 0,2:01:43.62,2:01:44.95,Default,,0,0,0,,阿基?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}LAURIE: Archie?
Dialogue: 0,2:01:45.69,2:01:49.32,Default,,0,0,0,,呃 就是阿基米德的简称\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Oh. Well, uh, short for Archimedes...
Dialogue: 0,2:01:49.32,2:01:51.04,Default,,0,0,0,,梅林{\fs33.333} 亚瑟王的法师 {\r}的宠物猫头鹰\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...Merlin's pet owl.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:51.96,2:01:53.62,Default,,0,0,0,,愚蠢的外号\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Stupid nickname.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:54.70,2:01:57.67,Default,,0,0,0,,你怎么买得起这些东西的?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}LAURIE: How did you ever afford all this stuff, anyway?
Dialogue: 0,2:01:57.67,2:02:00.13,Default,,0,0,0,,哦 我爸之前在企业银行 后来…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Well, my dad was in corporate banking and...
Dialogue: 0,2:02:00.90,2:02:03.03,Default,,0,0,0,,他死后给我留下很多钱\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}left me a lot of money when he died...
Dialogue: 0,2:02:03.87,2:02:07.21,Default,,0,0,0,,这事一直让我惊讶 我是说 他以前…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...which always surprised me. I mean, he was...
Dialogue: 0,2:02:07.88,2:02:10.68,Default,,0,0,0,,我以为他很失望我去打击犯罪\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I think he was disappointed I went into crime fighting...
Dialogue: 0,2:02:10.68,2:02:12.38,Default,,0,0,0,,而不是步他后尘\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...instead of following him.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:13.15,2:02:20.15,Default,,0,0,0,,我猜我就是对鸟类 航天飞机和神话更感兴趣\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Guess I was just more interested in birds and airplanes, mythology and...
Dialogue: 0,2:02:20.59,2:02:24.58,Default,,0,0,0,,再加上有够多人在做这个 所以我追随在后就不感觉荒谬了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Plus, there were enough other guys doing this so that I didn't feel ridiculous behind.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:25.50,2:02:26.91,Default,,0,0,0,,比如霍利斯\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Like Hollis.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:26.91,2:02:28.39,Default,,0,0,0,,对\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:29.17,2:02:31.93,Default,,0,0,0,,对 他是我的英雄\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Yeah, he was my hero.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:32.97,2:02:36.37,Default,,0,0,0,,哇 我记得第一次遇见他的时候 我…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Man, I remember the first time that I met him...
Dialogue: 0,2:02:37.27,2:02:40.32,Default,,0,0,0,,我就感觉有联系 你知道吗?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...I just felt so connected, you know?
Dialogue: 0,2:02:40.32,2:02:42.68,Default,,0,0,0,,在一些重要的方面\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}To something that mattered.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:45.70,2:02:48.35,Default,,0,0,0,,有个秘密身份肯定很不错吧?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Must be nice having a secret identity.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:48.94,2:02:51.19,Default,,0,0,0,,有个没人知道的秘密据点\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}A secret place that nobody knows about.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:51.19,2:02:56.36,Default,,0,0,0,,你可以…进进出出 没人会对你进行安检\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You can just come down here and hang out without anyone checking up on you.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:57.75,2:02:59.99,Default,,0,0,0,,没有人监视你\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Nobody watching you.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:03.44,2:03:04.57,Default,,0,0,0,,想戴上试试吗?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Wanna try those on?
Dialogue: 0,2:03:15.18,2:03:16.84,Default,,0,0,0,,来吧\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}There we go.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:20.02,2:03:22.01,Default,,0,0,0,,哇 这太酷了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Wow, these rock.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:24.85,2:03:27.35,Default,,0,0,0,,它放大了光谱范围\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}They amplify the spectral range.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:27.60,2:03:29.45,Default,,0,0,0,,热成像\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Thermal imaging.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:31.13,2:03:33.12,Default,,0,0,0,,黑暗中效果更好\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}They work even better in the dark.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:38.03,2:03:39.80,Default,,0,0,0,,你能看见我 对吧?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You can see me, right?
Dialogue: 0,2:03:41.97,2:03:44.63,Default,,0,0,0,,我什么都能看见\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I can see everything.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:47.38,2:03:50.87,Default,,0,0,0,,我记得 不管外面有多黑\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I remember, no matter how black it got...
Dialogue: 0,2:03:51.30,2:03:55.34,Default,,0,0,0,,只要我戴上这副眼镜 一切就像白天一样清楚\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...whenever I looked through those goggles, everything was as clear as day.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:57.80,2:04:00.17,Default,,0,0,0,,这一定是乔恩看见世界的样子\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}This must be the way Jon sees the world.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:02.49,2:04:05.43,Default,,0,0,0,,我们也许该上去了 饭菜快凉了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}We should probably head up. Food's getting cold.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:05.75,2:04:07.80,Default,,0,0,0,,看完了把它放回去\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Put those away when you're done.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:16.64,2:04:19.83,Default,,0,0,0,,苏联驻联合国大使今天没有任何评论…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}MAN [ON TV]: Soviet ambassador to the U.N. had no comment today...
Dialogue: 0,2:04:19.83,2:04:24.12,Default,,0,0,0,,他被问及曼哈顿博士的消失 是否加速了苏联在阿富汗的侵略\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}... when asked if Dr. Manhattan's disappearance has fueled Soviet aggression in Afghanistan.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:24.12,2:04:25.79,Default,,0,0,0,,丹\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Dan.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:25.79,2:04:26.62,Default,,0,0,0,,与此同时 这两…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Main while, these two...
Dialogue: 0,2:04:26.62,2:04:28.41,Default,,0,0,0,,乔恩看得见很多东西\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Jon sees a lot of things...
Dialogue: 0,2:04:30.65,2:04:32.95,Default,,0,0,0,,但他看不见我\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...but he doesn't see me.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:40.10,2:04:41.62,Default,,0,0,0,,这个 嗯...\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Well, uh...
Dialogue: 0,2:04:59.85,2:05:01.41,Default,,0,0,0,,哦\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Oh.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:35.25,2:05:36.77,Default,,0,0,0,,抱歉\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:38.59,2:05:39.92,Default,,0,0,0,,过来\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Come here.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:46.00,2:05:47.39,Default,,0,0,0,,怎么了?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,2:05:47.39,2:05:49.91,Default,,0,0,0,,- 你能稍微挪一下… - 好的\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}- If you could just move a little... - Okay.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:49.91,2:05:52.13,Default,,0,0,0,,嗯 好了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Yeah. There you go.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:58.64,2:06:01.27,Default,,0,0,0,,丹 怎么了?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Dan, what's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,2:06:02.95,2:06:04.25,Default,,0,0,0,,抱歉 我\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Sorry, I...
Dialogue: 0,2:06:06.22,2:06:08.45,Default,,0,0,0,,哦 我只是需要几分钟\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Yeah, I just need a couple minutes.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:10.62,2:06:12.72,Default,,0,0,0,,哦 见鬼了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Oh, hell.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:14.32,2:06:16.16,Default,,0,0,0,,没事的\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}It's okay.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:17.56,2:06:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,可能我们发展太快了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Maybe we were just moving too fast.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:25.57,2:06:28.20,Default,,0,0,0,,我们有大把的时间\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}We've got all the time in the world.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:29.71,2:06:31.70,Default,,0,0,0,,我们慢慢来\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}We'll take it slow.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:45.69,2:06:48.02,Default,,0,0,0,,好久不见 罗夏\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}It's been a long time, Rorschach.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:48.69,2:06:50.18,Default,,0,0,0,,大块头\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}RORSCHACH: Big Figure.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:50.53,2:06:52.36,Default,,0,0,0,,世界真小\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Small world.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:53.70,2:06:55.19,Default,,0,0,0,,我喜欢这样\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I like that.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:55.97,2:06:58.37,Default,,0,0,0,,不过你得知道 这地方很小的\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}But you know, it is a small world in here.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:58.80,2:07:01.73,Default,,0,0,0,,我已经在这里有多久了 洛伊德?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}And I've been in it for, how long now, Lloyd?
Dialogue: 0,2:07:01.73,2:07:04.21,Default,,0,0,0,,快15年了 大块头先生\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}LLO YD: Almost 15 years, Mr. Figure.
Dialogue: 0,2:07:04.21,2:07:05.54,Default,,0,0,0,,说得对\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}That's right.
Dialogue: 0,2:07:06.54,2:07:10.03,Default,,0,0,0,,自从你和那个夜枭把我抓进来已经15年了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Fifteen years since you and that Owl fella put me away.
Dialogue: 0,2:07:13.05,2:07:14.21,Default,,0,0,0,,那么\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}So...
Dialogue: 0,2:07:14.72,2:07:19.64,Default,,0,0,0,,罗夏 你烫伤的那个人快死了 随时可能挂掉\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...Rorschach, that guy you burned is dying. Could go any minute.
Dialogue: 0,2:07:19.64,2:07:25.21,Default,,0,0,0,,知道吗 我算过 这里有超过50人是你抓进来的\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You know, by my count, there are more than 50 people in here that you put away.
Dialogue: 0,2:07:25.21,2:07:29.53,Default,,0,0,0,,我和他们每个人都谈过了 他们都恨不得要分你的一片肉\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I been talking to every one of them and they're all dying to get a piece of you.
Dialogue: 0,2:07:29.53,2:07:32.83,Default,,0,0,0,,这地方将会爆炸！\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}This place is gonna explode!
Dialogue: 0,2:07:34.40,2:07:37.07,Default,,0,0,0,,然后 你寸断而死\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Then, you die by inches.
Dialogue: 0,2:07:38.01,2:07:39.89,Default,,0,0,0,,办不到\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Tall order.
Dialogue: 0,2:07:39.89,2:07:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,我要给这家伙开个新口子\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I'm gonna tear this guy a new hole.
Dialogue: 0,2:07:43.08,2:07:46.07,Default,,0,0,0,,放轻松 劳伦斯 快了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Relax, Lawrence. Soon.
Dialogue: 0,2:07:46.92,2:07:48.25,Default,,0,0,0,,走吧\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Come on.
Dialogue: 0,2:09:22.15,2:09:24.36,Default,,0,0,0,,了解一下吧 我的朋友\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}MARINER: Know this, my friends.
Dialogue: 0,2:09:24.36,2:09:25.47,Default,,0,0,0,,冥王是湿漉漉的\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Hades is wet.
Dialogue: 0,2:09:26.82,2:09:28.37,Default,,0,0,0,,冥王是孤独的\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Hades is lonely.
Dialogue: 0,2:09:44.23,2:09:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,在那一瞬间 我们认识了对方\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}And in that instant, we knew each other.
Dialogue: 0,2:10:24.41,2:10:26.67,Default,,0,0,0,,很抱歉 我的朋友\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I'm sorry, my friend.
Dialogue: 0,2:10:46.90,2:10:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,我的木筏已经变得越发离奇古怪\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}My raft had grown increasingly grotesque...
Dialogue: 0,2:10:50.40,2:10:53.43,Default,,0,0,0,,反映着我自身的变化\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}... reflecting my own transformation.
Dialogue: 0,2:11:07.02,2:11:11.23,Default,,0,0,0,,漂流中 我最黑暗的想象自由地涌现\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Adrift, my darkest imaginings welled up unchecked...
Dialogue: 0,2:11:11.23,2:11:14.54,Default,,0,0,0,,如同黑墨水般从大脑流向心脏\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}... spilling from brain to heart like black ink...
Dialogue: 0,2:11:14.54,2:11:16.99,Default,,0,0,0,,不可移除\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}... impossible to remove.
Dialogue: 0,2:11:25.84,2:11:28.83,Default,,0,0,0,,那艘船肯定早已到达戴维斯城\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}The vessel had surely reached Davidstown already.
Dialogue: 0,2:11:29.67,2:11:34.22,Default,,0,0,0,,我想象着宁静的街道被黑货船上的恶魔蹂躏\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I pictured quiet streets overrun by the fiends from the Black Freighter.
Dialogue: 0,2:11:34.22,2:11:37.63,Default,,0,0,0,,我的妻子 我的孩子 极有可能死了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}My wife, my children, most certainly dead.
Dialogue: 0,2:11:37.63,2:11:39.88,Default,,0,0,0,,我的船员 死了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}My crew, dead.
Dialogue: 0,2:11:39.88,2:11:43.48,Default,,0,0,0,,我乘坐的这头野兽 死了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}The beast I ride on, dead.
Dialogue: 0,2:11:52.48,2:11:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,更多血 更多血 更多血\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}VOICES [CHANTING]: More blood, more blood, more blood.
Dialogue: 0,2:12:09.68,2:12:11.16,Default,,0,0,0,,爸爸?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}GIRL: Father?
Dialogue: 0,2:12:11.16,2:12:13.87,Default,,0,0,0,,这不可能 哦 上帝 这不可能\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}It can't be. Oh, Lord, it can't be.
Dialogue: 0,2:12:13.87,2:12:17.25,Default,,0,0,0,,爸爸 救救我们 求求你\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Father, help us. Please.
Dialogue: 0,2:12:17.25,2:12:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,等等\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}MARINER: Wait.
Dialogue: 0,2:12:19.96,2:12:20.98,Default,,0,0,0,,我来了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I'm coming.
Dialogue: 0,2:12:21.76,2:12:23.09,Default,,0,0,0,,赶快 亲爱的\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Hurry, my dear.
Dialogue: 0,2:12:23.86,2:12:26.91,Default,,0,0,0,,等等 除了她们谁都行\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Wait. Anyone but them.
Dialogue: 0,2:12:26.91,2:12:28.80,Default,,0,0,0,,谁都行\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Anyone.
Dialogue: 0,2:12:28.80,2:12:30.39,Default,,0,0,0,,谁都行\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Anyone.
Dialogue: 0,2:12:34.67,2:12:37.10,Default,,0,0,0,,我吞下了太多的海水\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I'd swallowed too much seawater.
Dialogue: 0,2:12:37.10,2:12:40.11,Default,,0,0,0,,我吞下了太多的恐怖\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I'd swallowed too much horror.
Dialogue: 0,2:12:43.38,2:12:44.64,Default,,0,0,0,,上天对我下了诅咒\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}God has damned me.
Dialogue: 0,2:12:45.78,2:12:48.56,Default,,0,0,0,,上天对我们全体下了诅咒\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}God has damned us all.
Dialogue: 0,2:12:48.56,2:12:54.52,Default,,0,0,0,,的确 生活就是地狱 而死亡大概是我们唯一的解脱\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Truly, life is hell, and death's rough hand our only deliverance.
Dialogue: 0,2:12:55.26,2:12:57.54,Default,,0,0,0,,我不能再忍受了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I can endure no more.
Dialogue: 0,2:12:57.54,2:13:01.46,Default,,0,0,0,,我急切地想要追随我的家人\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I want to join my family desperately.
Dialogue: 0,2:13:09.27,2:13:11.10,Default,,0,0,0,,嘿\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}MAN: Yo, man.
Dialogue: 0,2:13:11.64,2:13:13.02,Default,,0,0,0,,在看什么呢?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}What you reading?
Dialogue: 0,2:13:14.68,2:13:16.35,Default,,0,0,0,,没什么 老兄\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Nothing, man.
Dialogue: 0,2:13:17.55,2:13:20.26,Default,,0,0,0,,- 没什么 哈?  - 嘿 嘿 你们别碰那孩子\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}- Nothing, huh? - Hey, hey! You leave that kid alone!
Dialogue: 0,2:13:20.26,2:13:22.15,Default,,0,0,0,,闭嘴 老头\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Shut up, old man!
Dialogue: 0,2:13:30.79,2:13:33.70,Default,,0,0,0,,你在看漫画书? 你怎么回事 脑残了?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You're reading a comic book? What are you, retarded?
Dialogue: 0,2:13:40.80,2:13:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,嘿 你去哪儿 残障?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Aw, hey, where you going, short bus?
Dialogue: 0,2:13:54.12,2:13:55.45,Default,,0,0,0,,丹?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Dan?
Dialogue: 0,2:14:02.29,2:14:03.95,Default,,0,0,0,,一切都好吧?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Is everything all right?
Dialogue: 0,2:14:06.30,2:14:09.23,Default,,0,0,0,,我厌倦了担惊受怕\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I'm tired of being afraid.
Dialogue: 0,2:14:10.30,2:14:12.67,Default,,0,0,0,,害怕战争\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Afraid of war...
Dialogue: 0,2:14:13.47,2:14:17.03,Default,,0,0,0,,害怕那个面具杀手\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...afraid of the mask killer...
Dialogue: 0,2:14:18.64,2:14:21.99,Default,,0,0,0,,害怕这该死的衣服\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...and afraid of this goddamn suit...
Dialogue: 0,2:14:21.99,2:14:24.13,Default,,0,0,0,,以及我是多么需要它\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...and how much I need it.
Dialogue: 0,2:14:24.81,2:14:26.63,Default,,0,0,0,,我也是\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Me too.
Dialogue: 0,2:14:27.98,2:14:29.42,Default,,0,0,0,,那就让他们见鬼去吧\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}So to hell with it.
Dialogue: 0,2:14:30.15,2:14:31.64,Default,,0,0,0,,我们开阿基出去吧\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Let's take Archie out.
Dialogue: 0,2:14:37.43,2:14:38.68,Default,,0,0,0,,你是认真的吗?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You're serious.
Dialogue: 0,2:14:38.68,2:14:41.41,Default,,0,0,0,,我以前也是面具复仇者 记得吧?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I used to be a masked avenger too, remember?
Dialogue: 0,2:14:41.41,2:14:44.82,Default,,0,0,0,,我以前经常半夜3点出去 做一些傻事\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I'm used to going out at 3 in the morning and doing something stupid.
Dialogue: 0,2:15:46.40,2:15:48.64,Default,,0,0,0,,紧急火情 所有单位 听候指示\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}MAN [O VER RADIO]: Rapid burner. Be advised, all units.
Dialogue: 0,2:15:48.64,2:15:51.38,Default,,0,0,0,,第五大街和格兰特大街租屋失火\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Tenement fire at 5th and Grand. Rapid burner.
Dialogue: 0,2:15:51.38,2:15:52.73,Default,,0,0,0,,我们走\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,2:15:57.51,2:16:00.02,Default,,0,0,0,,- 我看到了 - 好的 抓紧了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}LAURIE: I can see it. DAN: All right, hold on.
Dialogue: 0,2:16:10.72,2:16:12.28,Default,,0,0,0,,丹 里面有孩子\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}LAURIE: Dan, there are kids in there.
Dialogue: 0,2:16:12.28,2:16:14.85,Default,,0,0,0,,每个人都请待在原处 保持镇静\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Everyone, please stay where you are and remain calm.
Dialogue: 0,2:16:14.85,2:16:16.25,Default,,0,0,0,,我们会把你们救出去的\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}We're gonna get you out of there.
