Dialogue: 0,2:17:36.04,2:17:38.02,Default,,0,0,0,,那是耶稣吗?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Is that Jesus?
Dialogue: 0,2:17:38.44,2:17:40.27,Default,,0,0,0,,不 宝贝\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}No, baby.
Dialogue: 0,2:17:41.18,2:17:43.30,Default,,0,0,0,,- 小心脚下  - 好的\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}DAN: Watch your step. LAURIE: All right.
Dialogue: 0,2:17:45.65,2:17:46.67,Default,,0,0,0,,我们上来了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}We're all set.
Dialogue: 0,2:17:47.72,2:17:49.38,Default,,0,0,0,,都到齐了吗?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Is that everyone?
Dialogue: 0,2:18:13.44,2:18:15.90,Default,,0,0,0,,再见！\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}MAN: Bye. GIRL: Bye!
Dialogue: 0,2:18:19.35,2:18:21.07,Default,,0,0,0,,不敢相信我们这么做了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}LAURIE: I can't believe we did that.
Dialogue: 0,2:18:22.87,2:18:25.50,Default,,0,0,0,,- 他们会把我们和罗夏关在一起  - 管他呢\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}- They'll lock us up with Rorschach. - Who cares?
Dialogue: 0,2:18:25.50,2:18:27.62,Default,,0,0,0,,第三次世界大战可能明天就开打\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}World War III could start tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,2:18:29.59,2:18:30.92,Default,,0,0,0,,对吧?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Right?
Dialogue: 0,2:18:32.59,2:18:33.93,Default,,0,0,0,,对\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Right.
Dialogue: 0,2:20:59.04,2:21:00.94,Default,,0,0,0,,给我回来！\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}MAN: Come back here!
Dialogue: 0,2:21:03.55,2:21:05.60,Default,,0,0,0,,他死了 罗夏\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}He's dead, Rorschach.
Dialogue: 0,2:21:05.60,2:21:09.77,Default,,0,0,0,,人人都在暴乱的时候 我们觉得应该给你一份乔迁礼物\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}While everyone's distracted, we thought we'd bring you a housewarming gift.
Dialogue: 0,2:21:09.77,2:21:12.12,Default,,0,0,0,,机械店买的\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Something from the machine shop.
Dialogue: 0,2:21:13.59,2:21:15.37,Default,,0,0,0,,老大 你注意到没有?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Hey, boss, you notice?
Dialogue: 0,2:21:15.84,2:21:18.57,Default,,0,0,0,,再不说"世界真小""办不到"那些废话了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}None of that "small world, tall order" crap.
Dialogue: 0,2:21:18.57,2:21:21.96,Default,,0,0,0,,他知道一旦我们切开他的门锁 下一个就是他\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}He knows once we slice open his lock, he's next on the block.
Dialogue: 0,2:21:22.36,2:21:23.55,Default,,0,0,0,,机会太小\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Fat chance.
Dialogue: 0,2:21:24.10,2:21:25.38,Default,,0,0,0,,你死定了 罗夏\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You're dead, Rorschach!
Dialogue: 0,2:21:25.38,2:21:29.22,Default,,0,0,0,,我们有满满一监狱的杀手 你有什么?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}We got a prison full of killers out here. What do you got?
Dialogue: 0,2:21:32.01,2:21:34.44,Default,,0,0,0,,有你的手 我很荣幸\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Your hands, my pleasure.
Dialogue: 0,2:21:36.43,2:21:38.59,Default,,0,0,0,,我没法够到门锁 要把栏杆锯断吗?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}LLO YD: Can't reach the lock. Should I cut the bars?
Dialogue: 0,2:21:38.59,2:21:42.07,Default,,0,0,0,,暴乱不会持续多久 这一刻我等了15年了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}This riot won't last. I been waiting 15 years for this.
Dialogue: 0,2:21:43.05,2:21:46.57,Default,,0,0,0,,抱歉劳伦斯 你挡到我复仇了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I'm sorry, Lawrence, but you're in the way of my revenge.
Dialogue: 0,2:21:50.13,2:21:51.85,Default,,0,0,0,,不是针对你的 大块头\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Nothing personal, big guy.
Dialogue: 0,2:21:53.30,2:21:55.45,Default,,0,0,0,,老大！等等！\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Boss! Wait!
Dialogue: 0,2:22:09.44,2:22:11.39,Default,,0,0,0,,现在你明白比分多少了吧?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Now you find out what the score is.
Dialogue: 0,2:22:11.68,2:22:14.97,Default,,0,0,0,,1比O 进来抓我吧\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}One-nothing. Come and get me.
Dialogue: 0,2:22:20.86,2:22:22.67,Default,,0,0,0,,快点\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Come on.
Dialogue: 0,2:22:22.67,2:22:24.48,Default,,0,0,0,,所以我一直在想\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}DAN: So I've been thinking.
Dialogue: 0,2:22:25.26,2:22:29.42,Default,,0,0,0,,我觉得我们对我们的同伴有道义的责任\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I feel that we have an obligation to our fraternity.
Dialogue: 0,2:22:30.27,2:22:31.93,Default,,0,0,0,,我想我们应该去救罗夏\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I think we ought to spring Rorschach.
Dialogue: 0,2:22:32.47,2:22:33.48,Default,,0,0,0,,什么?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}LAURIE: What?
Dialogue: 0,2:22:33.48,2:22:35.27,Default,,0,0,0,,有人陷害了他\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}DAN: Someone set him up.
Dialogue: 0,2:22:36.10,2:22:39.87,Default,,0,0,0,,还有乔恩跟癌症的事情 完全没有道理\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}And this whole cancer thing with Jon, it just doesn't make sense.
Dialogue: 0,2:22:39.87,2:22:42.08,Default,,0,0,0,,你就没有得癌\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You didn't get it.
Dialogue: 0,2:22:42.08,2:22:44.71,Default,,0,0,0,,对 不过闯入最高安全级别的监狱\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Yeah, but breaking into a maximum-security prison...
Dialogue: 0,2:22:44.71,2:22:48.38,Default,,0,0,0,,- …跟灭火有点不一样了 - 对 你说对了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...is a little different than putting out a fire. - Yeah, you're right.
Dialogue: 0,2:22:49.28,2:22:51.12,Default,,0,0,0,,会更好玩\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}It'll be more fun.
Dialogue: 0,2:22:55.40,2:22:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,快点洛伊德 我想闻到这婊子养的被烤熟\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Hurry, Lloyd. I wanna smell this son of a bitch cooking.
Dialogue: 0,2:23:03.68,2:23:05.41,Default,,0,0,0,,好啊\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,2:23:10.03,2:23:11.24,Default,,0,0,0,,不\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}No.
Dialogue: 0,2:23:25.10,2:23:27.34,Default,,0,0,0,,以前从没用马桶处理过污物\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Never disposed of sewage with a toilet before.
Dialogue: 0,2:23:28.23,2:23:29.96,Default,,0,0,0,,明显早该用\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Obvious, really.
Dialogue: 0,2:23:30.77,2:23:34.14,Default,,0,0,0,,2比O 该你出招了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Two-nothing. Your move.
Dialogue: 0,2:23:37.41,2:23:39.10,Default,,0,0,0,,给我让开！\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}BIG FIGURE: Get out of the way!
Dialogue: 0,2:24:05.98,2:24:07.88,Default,,0,0,0,,你怎么知道他还活着?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}How do we know he's still alive?
Dialogue: 0,2:24:10.08,2:24:11.38,Default,,0,0,0,,他还活着\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}DAN: He's alive.
Dialogue: 0,2:24:22.93,2:24:24.64,Default,,0,0,0,,不要 不\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}No. No.
Dialogue: 0,2:24:25.26,2:24:26.69,Default,,0,0,0,,我的脸呢?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Where's my face?
Dialogue: 0,2:24:29.20,2:24:30.63,Default,,0,0,0,,别杀我\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Don't kill me.
Dialogue: 0,2:24:34.60,2:24:36.03,Default,,0,0,0,,到你了 医生\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Your turn, doctor.
Dialogue: 0,2:24:36.03,2:24:39.41,Default,,0,0,0,,告诉我 你看见什么?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Tell me, what do you see?
Dialogue: 0,2:26:05.53,2:26:07.26,Default,,0,0,0,,不许动\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Don't move!
Dialogue: 0,2:26:15.54,2:26:17.10,Default,,0,0,0,,罗夏\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Rorschach.
Dialogue: 0,2:26:17.81,2:26:20.64,Default,,0,0,0,,丹尼尔 朱庇特小姐\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Daniel. Miss Jupiter.
Dialogue: 0,2:26:20.64,2:26:24.22,Default,,0,0,0,,抱歉 得去一下男厕\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Excuse me. Have to visit men's room.
Dialogue: 0,2:26:24.71,2:26:26.72,Default,,0,0,0,,哦 老天在上\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Oh, for chrissake.
Dialogue: 0,2:27:03.89,2:27:06.17,Default,,0,0,0,,看见你穿上制服真高兴 丹尼尔\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}RORSCHACH: Good to see you in uniform, Daniel.
Dialogue: 0,2:27:06.17,2:27:09.78,Default,,0,0,0,,早该知道你只需要一双美腿的激励\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Should've known all you needed was nice pair of legs to motivate you.
Dialogue: 0,2:27:09.78,2:27:14.02,Default,,0,0,0,,- 你真是个混蛋 罗夏  - 原谅我的激愤\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}LAURIE: You're such an asshole, Rorschach. - Spare me indignation.
Dialogue: 0,2:27:15.26,2:27:18.45,Default,,0,0,0,,你挑了个好时间对乔恩不忠\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Picked hell of a time to be unfaithful to Jon.
Dialogue: 0,2:27:18.45,2:27:21.32,Default,,0,0,0,,是厌倦了爱国精神 还是有人逼你那么做?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Get tired of being patriotic, or someone put you up to it?
Dialogue: 0,2:27:21.32,2:27:24.25,Default,,0,0,0,,知道吗 你他妈的不知道自己在说什么！\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You don't know what the fuck you're talking about!
Dialogue: 0,2:27:24.25,2:27:28.29,Default,,0,0,0,,嘿 你俩能停下吗 你们可以回头再吵\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Hey! Would you two stop? You can argue later.
Dialogue: 0,2:27:28.29,2:27:32.04,Default,,0,0,0,,我得把噪音关掉 这样能快点离开这儿\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I had to turn the screechers off, so we'll be drawing fire soon.
Dialogue: 0,2:27:36.05,2:27:38.46,Default,,0,0,0,,站住！站住！不然开枪了！\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Stop! Stop or we will shoot!
Dialogue: 0,2:28:17.17,2:28:19.42,Default,,0,0,0,,你还好吗?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,2:28:20.86,2:28:23.06,Default,,0,0,0,,还好 只是…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Yeah. Just...
Dialogue: 0,2:28:23.50,2:28:24.80,Default,,0,0,0,,觉得沉重 你知道的\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...heavy, you know?
Dialogue: 0,2:28:25.57,2:28:27.72,Default,,0,0,0,,战争 越狱\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}War, jailbreak.
Dialogue: 0,2:28:28.20,2:28:30.47,Default,,0,0,0,,别担心 好吗?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Don't worry about it. Okay?
Dialogue: 0,2:28:31.20,2:28:32.47,Default,,0,0,0,,一切都会好的\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Everything's gonna be fine.
Dialogue: 0,2:28:38.08,2:28:41.15,Default,,0,0,0,,- 你好 劳瑞  - 乔恩\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}- Hello, Laurie. - Jon.
Dialogue: 0,2:28:41.15,2:28:44.91,Default,,0,0,0,,- 电视上说你在火星 - 我是在火星\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}- TV said you were on Mars. - I am on Mars.
Dialogue: 0,2:28:45.49,2:28:47.95,Default,,0,0,0,,你跟我要在那里谈谈\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You and I are about to have a conversation there.
Dialogue: 0,2:28:48.21,2:28:49.58,Default,,0,0,0,,你在说什么?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,2:28:49.58,2:28:52.41,Default,,0,0,0,,你要努力说服我去拯救这个世界\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You're going to try to convince me to save the world.
Dialogue: 0,2:28:58.27,2:29:01.42,Default,,0,0,0,,- 劳瑞 不要  - 丹 相信我\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}- Laurie, don't. - Dan, trust me.
Dialogue: 0,2:29:01.42,2:29:02.96,Default,,0,0,0,,我必须去\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I have to go.
Dialogue: 0,2:29:08.78,2:29:10.77,Default,,0,0,0,,很美 不是吗?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Beautiful, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,2:29:15.62,2:29:18.55,Default,,0,0,0,,原谅我 有时我脑子会忘记这类事情\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Forgive me. These things sometimes slip my mind.
Dialogue: 0,2:29:19.96,2:29:21.79,Default,,0,0,0,,不会再发生了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}It won't happen again.
Dialogue: 0,2:29:23.46,2:29:25.45,Default,,0,0,0,,令人欣慰\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}LAURIE: That's comforting.
Dialogue: 0,2:29:27.80,2:29:29.46,Default,,0,0,0,,哦 我的天啊\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Oh, my God.
Dialogue: 0,2:29:30.13,2:29:31.96,Default,,0,0,0,,我在火星上\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I'm on Mars.
Dialogue: 0,2:29:35.97,2:29:39.88,Default,,0,0,0,,- 嘿 屁股不错 - 嘿 混蛋\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}MAN: Hey. Nice ass. WOMAN: Hey, asshole.
Dialogue: 0,2:29:39.88,2:29:42.60,Default,,0,0,0,,嘿 我们看看那个喜欢连环漫画的在不在这里\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}MAN: Hey, let's see if that comic-book retard's up here.
Dialogue: 0,2:29:43.41,2:29:45.49,Default,,0,0,0,,嘿嘿嘿 喂\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Hey, hey, hey. Yo.
Dialogue: 0,2:29:45.49,2:29:50.37,Default,,0,0,0,,你们都听说了吗? 有个超级猫头鹰哥们劫狱带走了罗夏\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You all hear? Some super-owl dude just busted Rorschach out of prison.
Dialogue: 0,2:29:50.37,2:29:52.27,Default,,0,0,0,,- 罗夏?  - 对\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}- Rorschach? - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,2:29:52.27,2:29:54.30,Default,,0,0,0,,那个混蛋把我表哥打到坐轮椅\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}That fool put my cousin in a wheelchair.
Dialogue: 0,2:29:54.30,2:29:57.34,Default,,0,0,0,,你是说夜枭 他之前和罗夏是搭档 记得吗?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You mean Nite Owl. Him and Rorschach used to be partners, remember?
Dialogue: 0,2:29:57.34,2:30:00.47,Default,,0,0,0,,- 对 - 可能他也整了你表哥\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}- Yeah. - Maybe he messed your cousin up too.
Dialogue: 0,2:30:00.47,2:30:02.58,Default,,0,0,0,,- 他是不是写过一本书什么的?  - 对\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}- Didn't he write a book or something? - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,2:30:02.58,2:30:06.62,Default,,0,0,0,,告诉你 他住在一个加油站边 就在这附近\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You know, he lives over a garage right near here.
Dialogue: 0,2:30:06.62,2:30:09.30,Default,,0,0,0,,- 明白?  - 是吗?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}- Yeah? - Does he, now?
Dialogue: 0,2:30:12.04,2:30:13.28,Default,,0,0,0,,喂?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}SALLY [ON PHONE]: Hello?
Dialogue: 0,2:30:14.21,2:30:16.25,Default,,0,0,0,,莎莉?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}HOLLIS: Sally?
Dialogue: 0,2:30:16.25,2:30:19.33,Default,,0,0,0,,- 霍利斯?  - 是我\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}- Hollis? - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,2:30:19.33,2:30:23.35,Default,,0,0,0,,哇 霍利斯·梅森 老天\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Yes, Hollis Mason. Jesus.
Dialogue: 0,2:30:24.25,2:30:28.92,Default,,0,0,0,,你一直都有我的号码 却等到我们日薄西山才打?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}All this time you've had my number and you wait until our sunset years to use it?
Dialogue: 0,2:30:28.92,2:30:32.10,Default,,0,0,0,,哦 看来这是个特殊的时刻 小莎\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}HOLLIS: Well, it seemed like a special occasion, Sal.
Dialogue: 0,2:30:32.10,2:30:33.31,Default,,0,0,0,,怎么了?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}What?
Dialogue: 0,2:30:33.31,2:30:37.60,Default,,0,0,0,,电视正在报道昨晚有场公寓火灾\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}The TV is reporting there was a tenement fire last night.
Dialogue: 0,2:30:38.43,2:30:41.38,Default,,0,0,0,,受困人群是被一艘飞船救出的\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}There were trapped people rescued by airship...
Dialogue: 0,2:30:41.38,2:30:47.12,Default,,0,0,0,,他们说驾驶者穿得像猫头鹰一样\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}... and they say the pilot was dressed like an owl.
Dialogue: 0,2:30:47.12,2:30:49.49,Default,,0,0,0,,好像还有个性感女人和他一起\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}And it seems he had a sexy woman with him.
Dialogue: 0,2:30:49.49,2:30:52.11,Default,,0,0,0,,劳瑞? 我的女儿 劳瑞?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Laurie? My daughter, Laurie?
Dialogue: 0,2:30:53.57,2:30:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,我说服不了劳瑞再穿上制服\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I can't get over Laurie back in costume.
Dialogue: 0,2:30:57.00,2:31:00.64,Default,,0,0,0,,或许她最后会感谢我一开始 把她带上这条路\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Maybe she'll finally thank me for getting her started in the first place.
Dialogue: 0,2:31:00.64,2:31:03.95,Default,,0,0,0,,小莎 听你说话的声音\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You know, Sal, by the sound of your voice...
Dialogue: 0,2:31:04.29,2:31:06.31,Default,,0,0,0,,你比以前还年轻\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...you're sounding younger than ever.
Dialogue: 0,2:31:06.31,2:31:08.67,Default,,0,0,0,,哦 祝福你 霍利斯\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Oh. Why, bless you, Hollis.
Dialogue: 0,2:31:09.20,2:31:11.38,Default,,0,0,0,,不过我还是老了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}But that's probably just senility.
Dialogue: 0,2:31:14.10,2:31:17.19,Default,,0,0,0,,能和你聊天很开心 小莎\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Well, it's been great talking to you, Sal...
Dialogue: 0,2:31:17.19,2:31:19.60,Default,,0,0,0,,但是有人在敲门\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...but someone's knocking.
Dialogue: 0,2:31:20.11,2:31:25.10,Default,,0,0,0,,好的 想起旧日时光不要太泪目了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}SALLY: Well, don't get too misty-eyed thinking about old times.
Dialogue: 0,2:31:25.98,2:31:27.96,Default,,0,0,0,,你保重 霍利斯\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You take care now, Hollis.
Dialogue: 0,2:31:27.96,2:31:29.43,Default,,0,0,0,,你也是\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Ah, you too.
Dialogue: 0,2:31:29.43,2:31:30.74,Default,,0,0,0,,拜\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Bye.
Dialogue: 0,2:31:31.25,2:31:32.74,Default,,0,0,0,,拜\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Bye.
Dialogue: 0,2:31:36.19,2:31:38.49,Default,,0,0,0,,我们想找猫头鹰先生\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}MAN 1: We're looking for Mr. Owl.
Dialogue: 0,2:31:39.36,2:31:41.71,Default,,0,0,0,,在 别着急\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Yeah. Hold your horses.
Dialogue: 0,2:31:41.71,2:31:43.33,Default,,0,0,0,,猫头鹰先生 你在吗?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}MAN 1: Mr. Owl, you there?
Dialogue: 0,2:31:43.87,2:31:45.29,Default,,0,0,0,,不给糖就捣乱\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}MAN 2: Trick or treat.
Dialogue: 0,2:31:46.87,2:31:48.46,Default,,0,0,0,,你应该好好退你的休 猫头鹰\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}MAN 1: You should've stayed retired, Owl.
Dialogue: 0,2:32:53.70,2:32:55.32,Default,,0,0,0,,我讨厌这样\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}RORSCHACH: I hate this.
Dialogue: 0,2:32:55.32,2:32:59.46,Default,,0,0,0,,畏缩在洞里 躲避着当局\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Cowering in cave, hiding from authorities.
Dialogue: 0,2:32:59.91,2:33:01.51,Default,,0,0,0,,警察在外面追捕我们\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Cops are out there hunting us.
Dialogue: 0,2:33:01.82,2:33:05.89,Default,,0,0,0,,除非你想回监狱 没有计划地随便暴露自己很愚蠢\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Unless you wanna go back to prison we'd be stupid to expose ourselves without a plan.
Dialogue: 0,2:33:05.89,2:33:08.18,Default,,0,0,0,,那要怎么样?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}And what would that be?
Dialogue: 0,2:33:08.52,2:33:12.21,Default,,0,0,0,,一旦我们找出其中模式\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Once we've established a pattern...
Dialogue: 0,2:33:12.62,2:33:14.90,Default,,0,0,0,,我们就能入侵金字塔公司 看看能发现什么\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...we can break into Pyramid, see what we find.
Dialogue: 0,2:33:14.90,2:33:17.51,Default,,0,0,0,,做过了 死胡同\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}RORSCHACH: Did that. Dead end.
Dialogue: 0,2:33:17.51,2:33:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,,我认为那只是个掩护幕后人用的公司 但不能证明\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I think it's a front company for whoever's really behind it, but can't prove it.
Dialogue: 0,2:33:25.07,2:33:29.55,Default,,0,0,0,,我们需要敲打黑社会的线人 逼问那些人\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}We need to hit up underworld contacts, squeeze people.
Dialogue: 0,2:33:29.55,2:33:32.55,Default,,0,0,0,,是啊 我们干嘛不直接从电话簿里挑人问?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Sure, why don't we just pick names out of a phone book?
Dialogue: 0,2:33:32.55,2:33:34.76,Default,,0,0,0,,你忘了我们以前是怎么做事的 丹尼尔\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You forgot how we do things, Daniel.
Dialogue: 0,2:33:34.76,2:33:39.41,Default,,0,0,0,,你变得太软 太轻信 特别是面对女人\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You've gone too soft. Too trusting. Especially with women.
Dialogue: 0,2:33:39.41,2:33:41.66,Default,,0,0,0,,好了 住嘴 听着 我受够了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Okay, no. Listen, I've had it with that.
Dialogue: 0,2:33:41.66,2:33:43.89,Default,,0,0,0,,天哪 你以为你是谁 罗夏?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}God, who do you think you are, Rorschach?
Dialogue: 0,2:33:43.89,2:33:46.14,Default,,0,0,0,,你污蔑自己投靠的人\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You live off people while insulting them...
Dialogue: 0,2:33:46.14,2:33:49.95,Default,,0,0,0,,没人会埋怨你 因为他们都觉得你是个该死的疯子\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...and no one complains because they think you're a goddamn lunatic.
Dialogue: 0,2:34:01.94,2:34:03.77,Default,,0,0,0,,抱歉 我…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,2:34:06.44,2:34:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,我不该那么说 老兄\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I shouldn't have said that, man.
Dialogue: 0,2:34:10.61,2:34:11.94,Default,,0,0,0,,丹尼尔\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Daniel...
Dialogue: 0,2:34:13.45,2:34:15.92,Default,,0,0,0,,你是个好朋友\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...you are a good friend.
Dialogue: 0,2:34:18.79,2:34:21.95,Default,,0,0,0,,我知道和我相处有时会很难\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I know it can be difficult with me sometimes.
Dialogue: 0,2:34:28.46,2:34:29.95,Default,,0,0,0,,算了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Forget it.
Dialogue: 0,2:34:31.13,2:34:32.79,Default,,0,0,0,,没事的 伙计\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}It's okay, man.
Dialogue: 0,2:34:34.07,2:34:35.71,Default,,0,0,0,,就照你的办法做\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Let's do it your way.
Dialogue: 0,2:34:54.80,2:34:56.07,Default,,0,0,0,,哦 老天\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Oh, God.
Dialogue: 0,2:34:56.07,2:35:00.56,Default,,0,0,0,,金字塔跨国公司 有人听说过吗?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Pyramid Transnational. Anyone heard of it?
Dialogue: 0,2:35:07.91,2:35:09.86,Default,,0,0,0,,哦 你们这些混蛋\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Oh, you bastards.
Dialogue: 0,2:35:09.86,2:35:12.88,Default,,0,0,0,,我请这里每个人喝酒 你们就这样出卖我?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I buy everyone a round and you sell me out like this?
Dialogue: 0,2:35:14.01,2:35:17.31,Default,,0,0,0,,退后 不然我就把这杯子 黏在你潮湿的脸上\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Back off, or I'll stick this glass in your squidgy face.
Dialogue: 0,2:35:19.01,2:35:21.95,Default,,0,0,0,,大家保持冷静 我们尽量简短\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Everybody stay calm. We'll try to keep this brief.
Dialogue: 0,2:35:23.93,2:35:26.26,Default,,0,0,0,,罗伊·切斯 领金字塔的工资\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Roy Chess. On Pyramid payroll.
Dialogue: 0,2:35:26.26,2:35:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,试图谋杀阿德里安·维特 现在已经死了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Tried to kill Adrian Veidt. Dead now.
Dialogue: 0,2:35:29.54,2:35:30.94,Default,,0,0,0,,你以前知道他吗?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Did you know him?
Dialogue: 0,2:35:31.42,2:35:32.77,Default,,0,0,0,,不\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}No.
Dialogue: 0,2:35:33.90,2:35:34.81,Default,,0,0,0,,知道 知道\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Yeah, yeah!
Dialogue: 0,2:35:35.53,2:35:38.81,Default,,0,0,0,,- 我雇了他 我在牢里认识的他  - 你是重刑犯\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}- I hired him. I knew him from the inside. - You're a felon.
Dialogue: 0,2:35:38.81,2:35:41.75,Default,,0,0,0,,曾经是 但我出狱之后就改过自新了 我发誓\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I was. I've been straight ever since I got out, I swear.
Dialogue: 0,2:35:41.75,2:35:45.30,Default,,0,0,0,,我没那么了解切斯 但我被告知要去雇佣以前认识的人\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I barely knew Chess that well, but I was told to hire from the old life.
Dialogue: 0,2:35:45.85,2:35:49.63,Default,,0,0,0,,- 谁让你做的?  - 我的接头人 斯莱特小姐\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}- Told by whom? - My contact, Miss Slater.
Dialogue: 0,2:35:49.63,2:35:52.21,Default,,0,0,0,,珍妮·斯莱特? 也为金字塔工作?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Janey Slater works for Pyramid too?
Dialogue: 0,2:35:52.21,2:35:53.94,Default,,0,0,0,,对 她真是个好人\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Yeah, she was real nice.
Dialogue: 0,2:35:53.94,2:35:56.40,Default,,0,0,0,,她说雇佣有前科的人是公司政策的一部分\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}She said hiring ex-cons was part of the company program.
Dialogue: 0,2:35:56.40,2:35:58.04,Default,,0,0,0,,给人第二次机会\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Give people a second chance.
Dialogue: 0,2:35:58.04,2:36:00.09,Default,,0,0,0,,老天 拜托松手吧 我说的是实话\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}God, please let go! I'm telling the truth!
Dialogue: 0,2:36:04.19,2:36:07.47,Default,,0,0,0,,珍妮·斯莱特 曼哈顿的前女友\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Janey Slater, Manhattan's old girlfriend.
Dialogue: 0,2:36:07.47,2:36:10.55,Default,,0,0,0,,阿德里安的人也许能帮我们查到谁在金字塔背后\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Adrian's peaple might help us find out who's underwriting Pyramid.
Dialogue: 0,2:36:10.55,2:36:11.56,Default,,0,0,0,,跟着钱查\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Follow the money.
Dialogue: 0,2:36:11.56,2:36:15.11,Default,,0,0,0,,前民兵成员霍利斯·梅森被发现遭杀害…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}WOMAN [ON TV]:former member of the Minutemen Hollis Mason found murdered...
Dialogue: 0,2:36:15.11,2:36:17.62,Default,,0,0,0,,不到一个小时之前在其公寓\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}... in his apartment less than an hour ago.
Dialogue: 0,2:36:17.62,2:36:21.90,Default,,0,0,0,,目击者报告称看见本地结首帮几名成员…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Witnesses reported seeing members of a local gang known as the Knot-Tops...
Dialogue: 0,2:36:21.90,2:36:25.33,Default,,0,0,0,,大约在估计的案发时间离开了现场\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}... leaving the area right around the estimated time of death.
Dialogue: 0,2:36:25.33,2:36:28.28,Default,,0,0,0,,现场直播 蒂芙尼·伯恩斯…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Reporting live, Tiffany Burns...
Dialogue: 0,2:36:30.62,2:36:33.77,Default,,0,0,0,,- 是谁干的?  - 我就知道你要迫害我 老兄\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}- Who did it? - I knew you were gonna victimize me, man.
Dialogue: 0,2:36:33.77,2:36:36.07,Default,,0,0,0,,我的公民权利呢? 就因为我穿了一件…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}What about my civil rights? Just because I'm wearing...
Dialogue: 0,2:36:36.07,2:36:39.15,Default,,0,0,0,,- 告诉我谁干的?  - 很多人都这么穿\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}- Tell me who did it! - A lot of people dress like this.
Dialogue: 0,2:36:40.50,2:36:42.42,Default,,0,0,0,,谁杀了霍利斯·梅森?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Who murdered Hollis Mason?
Dialogue: 0,2:36:48.07,2:36:50.39,Default,,0,0,0,,告诉你的朋友们 他们死定了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You tell your friends they're dead.
Dialogue: 0,2:36:50.39,2:36:54.10,Default,,0,0,0,,我要踏平你们整个老巢！\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I'm gonna take out this entire rathole neighborhood.
Dialogue: 0,2:36:54.10,2:36:56.73,Default,,0,0,0,,我要拧断你的脖子！\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I'll break your neck!
Dialogue: 0,2:36:57.31,2:37:00.30,Default,,0,0,0,,丹尼尔 别在公众面前这样\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Daniel, not in front of the civilians.
Dialogue: 0,2:37:00.92,2:37:03.78,Default,,0,0,0,,该死的 该死的 霍利斯\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Oh, goddamn. Goddamn, Hollis.
Dialogue: 0,2:37:13.76,2:37:16.93,Default,,0,0,0,,这就是我们要谈话的地方\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}JON: This is where we hold our conversation.
Dialogue: 0,2:37:17.42,2:37:21.03,Default,,0,0,0,,在这里 你向我揭示你和德雷伯格一起睡了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}In it, you reveal to me that you and Dreiberg have been sleeping together.
Dialogue: 0,2:37:22.60,2:37:24.30,Default,,0,0,0,,你知道我和丹的事情?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You know about me and Dan?
Dialogue: 0,2:37:24.30,2:37:25.67,Default,,0,0,0,,现在还不知道\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Not yet.
Dialogue: 0,2:37:26.14,2:37:28.91,Default,,0,0,0,,但是过一会儿你就会告诉我\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}But in a few moments you're going to tell me.
Dialogue: 0,2:37:31.45,2:37:34.18,Default,,0,0,0,,如果你已经知道未来 那么…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}If you already know the future, then...
Dialogue: 0,2:37:34.18,2:37:36.27,Default,,0,0,0,,我离开你时你干嘛还惊讶?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}why were you surprised when I left you?
Dialogue: 0,2:37:36.65,2:37:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,还有那个记者突袭陷害你的时候?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Or when that reporter ambushed you?
Dialogue: 0,2:37:39.00,2:37:42.25,Default,,0,0,0,,为什么还要争论呢? 你一早就知道结果如何了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Why even argue about it if you already know how this is gonna end?
Dialogue: 0,2:37:43.83,2:37:45.40,Default,,0,0,0,,我没有选择\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I have no choice.
Dialogue: 0,2:37:47.45,2:37:50.03,Default,,0,0,0,,每一件事都是注定的\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Everything is preordained.
Dialogue: 0,2:37:50.50,2:37:52.53,Default,,0,0,0,,甚至我的反应也是\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Even my responses.
Dialogue: 0,2:37:53.80,2:37:57.10,Default,,0,0,0,,所以你也就是走个过场\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}And you're just going through the motions.
Dialogue: 0,2:37:57.46,2:38:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,宇宙里最强大的事物 仍然不过是个傀儡\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}The most powerful thing in the universe is still just a puppet.
Dialogue: 0,2:38:04.11,2:38:06.77,Default,,0,0,0,,我们都是傀儡 劳瑞\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}We are all puppets, Laurie.
Dialogue: 0,2:38:07.72,2:38:10.26,Default,,0,0,0,,我只是个能看到背后联系的傀儡\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I'm just a puppet who can see the strings.
Dialogue: 0,2:38:10.26,2:38:12.14,Default,,0,0,0,,如果你错了呢?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}And what if you're wrong?
Dialogue: 0,2:38:12.14,2:38:16.81,Default,,0,0,0,,为什么我对时间的知觉 会如此困扰你呢?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Why does my perception of time distress you so?
Dialogue: 0,2:38:16.81,2:38:18.97,Default,,0,0,0,,因为那是非人的\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Because it's inhuman.
Dialogue: 0,2:38:18.97,2:38:21.54,Default,,0,0,0,,因为那让我发疯\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Because it makes me insane.
Dialogue: 0,2:38:21.54,2:38:25.24,Default,,0,0,0,,你总是说你要安慰我 但是都没有起作用\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You always say you wanna comfort me. Well, it isn't working.
Dialogue: 0,2:38:32.87,2:38:35.37,Default,,0,0,0,,瞧 我不想争吵\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Look, I don't wanna fight.
Dialogue: 0,2:38:36.83,2:38:39.61,Default,,0,0,0,,我抱歉我跟丹睡了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I'm sorry I slept with Dan.
Dialogue: 0,2:38:40.18,2:38:42.21,Default,,0,0,0,,你和丹睡了?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You slept with Dan?
Dialogue: 0,2:38:43.92,2:38:46.84,Default,,0,0,0,,你刚才说过 你已经知道了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You just said that you already knew about that.
Dialogue: 0,2:38:47.62,2:38:51.62,Default,,0,0,0,,我经常说\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I said often...
Dialogue: 0,2:38:52.29,2:38:56.63,Default,,0,0,0,,你是我唯一剩下的跟人类的联系\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...that you were my only remaining link to humanity.
Dialogue: 0,2:38:59.07,2:39:02.90,Default,,0,0,0,,为什么我要去拯救一个很快就跟我无关的世界呢?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Why would I save a world I no longer have any stake in?
Dialogue: 0,2:39:04.97,2:39:07.03,Default,,0,0,0,,那就为了我而做\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Then do it for me.
Dialogue: 0,2:39:07.91,2:39:09.32,Default,,0,0,0,,如果你真的在乎\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}If you really care.
Dialogue: 0,2:39:09.32,2:39:12.95,Default,,0,0,0,,当你离开了我 我离开了地球\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}When you left me, I left Earth.
Dialogue: 0,2:39:12.95,2:39:15.98,Default,,0,0,0,,那还不够表示我的真心吗?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Does that not show you that I care?
Dialogue: 0,2:39:19.19,2:39:22.12,Default,,0,0,0,,我的红色世界 此时此地\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}My red world here, now...
Dialogue: 0,2:39:23.12,2:39:25.85,Default,,0,0,0,,对于我比你们的蓝色世界意义更大\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...means more to me than your blue one.
Dialogue: 0,2:39:26.80,2:39:28.32,Default,,0,0,0,,我给你看看\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Let me show you.
Dialogue: 0,2:39:46.65,2:39:49.61,Default,,0,0,0,,炸弹都已加注燃料并准备好 先生\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}KISSINGER: Bombers are fueled and ready, sir.
Dialogue: 0,2:39:58.93,2:40:00.90,Default,,0,0,0,,是时候了 各位\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}It's time, gentlemen.
Dialogue: 0,2:40:03.26,2:40:05.66,Default,,0,0,0,,把我们的戒备状态升到1级\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Take us to DEFCON one.
Dialogue: 0,2:40:12.94,2:40:16.05,Default,,0,0,0,,不在顶楼公寓 不在办公室\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}RORSCHACH: Not in penthouse. Not in office.
Dialogue: 0,2:40:16.05,2:40:19.28,Default,,0,0,0,,什么样的夜行癖好诱使一个拥有一切的男人\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}What nocturnal proclivities entice a man with everything...
Dialogue: 0,2:40:19.28,2:40:21.10,Default,,0,0,0,,在晚上这时候外出?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...out into the night at this hour?
Dialogue: 0,2:40:23.12,2:40:24.68,Default,,0,0,0,,丹尼尔?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Daniel?
Dialogue: 0,2:40:26.22,2:40:27.65,Default,,0,0,0,,你跟我一起吗\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You with me?
Dialogue: 0,2:40:28.79,2:40:29.52,Default,,0,0,0,,是的\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,2:40:30.02,2:40:31.32,Default,,0,0,0,,那你在干什么?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Then what are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,2:40:34.03,2:40:35.80,Default,,0,0,0,,我去找阿德里安的日程表\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}DAN: I'm gonna look for Adrian's itinerary.
Dialogue: 0,2:40:36.15,2:40:38.33,Default,,0,0,0,,也许他用文件保存\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}RORSCHACH: Maybe he keeps on file.
Dialogue: 0,2:40:43.24,2:40:45.85,Default,,0,0,0,,- 有些事不对头  - 同意\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}- Something's not right. - Agreed.
Dialogue: 0,2:40:45.85,2:40:50.44,Default,,0,0,0,,珍妮·斯莱特 摩罗神 罗伊·切斯 都为金字塔工作\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Janey Slater, Moloch, Roy Chess all work for Pyramid.
Dialogue: 0,2:40:51.00,2:40:55.60,Default,,0,0,0,,摩罗神说笑匠提到的名单 有他和斯莱特的名字在上面\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Moloch said the Comedian mentioned list with his and Slater's name on it.
Dialogue: 0,2:40:55.60,2:40:59.07,Default,,0,0,0,,不管谁掌管金字塔公司 都有可能让这些人患上癌症\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Whoever owns Pyramid could be giving these people cancer.
Dialogue: 0,2:40:59.07,2:41:01.56,Default,,0,0,0,,陷害曼哈顿\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Setting Manhattan up.
Dialogue: 0,2:41:11.10,2:41:13.20,Default,,0,0,0,,(法老王)
Dialogue: 0,2:41:13.20,2:41:14.82,Default,,0,0,0,,(拒绝访问)
Dialogue: 0,2:41:15.70,2:41:16.66,Default,,0,0,0,,有趣\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Funny.
Dialogue: 0,2:41:16.91,2:41:20.69,Default,,0,0,0,,古代法老期待世界末日的到来\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Ancient pharaohs looked forward to the end of the world.
Dialogue: 0,2:41:20.69,2:41:25.79,Default,,0,0,0,,相信死尸能复活 从金罐子里拿回自己的心脏\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Believed cadavers would rise, reclaim hearts from golden jars.
Dialogue: 0,2:41:26.38,2:41:29.27,Default,,0,0,0,,现在他们一定在期待中屏住了呼吸\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Must currently be holding breath in anticipation.
Dialogue: 0,2:41:29.27,2:41:30.46,Default,,0,0,0,,法老?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Pharaohs?
Dialogue: 0,2:41:37.29,2:41:39.34,Default,,0,0,0,,找到一份曼哈顿的心理资料\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Got a psych profile on Manhattan.
Dialogue: 0,2:41:39.96,2:41:42.47,Default,,0,0,0,,看看那些企业的大脑窥探者怎么说\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}See what the corporate head-peepers say.
Dialogue: 0,2:41:44.47,2:41:46.99,Default,,0,0,0,,"对象持续情感退化\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}"Subject continues to retreat emotionally.
Dialogue: 0,2:41:49.30,2:41:52.40,Default,,0,0,0,,"如果仅剩的情感连接被切断\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}If the only remaining ties were to be severed...
Dialogue: 0,2:41:50.00,2:41:52.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\a6}拉美西斯二世(法老)
Dialogue: 0,2:41:52.97,2:41:56.99,Default,,0,0,0,,"我们预测会完全超然人类本性"\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...we predict total detachment from the human condition."
Dialogue: 0,2:42:01.05,2:42:02.31,Default,,0,0,0,,我进入了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}DAN: I'm in.
Dialogue: 0,2:42:26.56,2:42:29.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}(母公司：维特国际)
Dialogue: 0,2:42:31.68,2:42:33.01,Default,,0,0,0,,不\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}No.
Dialogue: 0,2:42:35.18,2:42:36.95,Default,,0,0,0,,恭喜 维特先生\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}MAN: Congratulations, Mr. Veidt.
Dialogue: 0,2:42:37.30,2:42:40.65,Default,,0,0,0,,曼哈顿博士的能量反应堆已经连上了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Dr. Manhattan's energy reactor is online.
Dialogue: 0,2:42:40.99,2:42:45.19,Default,,0,0,0,,你的支持 还有你的热忱\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Your support and your enthusiasm...
Dialogue: 0,2:42:45.19,2:42:47.61,Default,,0,0,0,,促成了这次凯旋\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...is what has led to this triumph.
Dialogue: 0,2:42:47.61,2:42:51.91,Default,,0,0,0,,我们代表研究团队 向你致敬\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}On behalf of the research team, we salute you.
Dialogue: 0,2:42:51.91,2:42:54.27,Default,,0,0,0,,- 干杯 - 干杯\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}- Cheers. - Cheers.
Dialogue: 0,2:42:55.04,2:42:59.17,Default,,0,0,0,,生命中的什么不值得庆祝?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}ADRIAN: What in life does not deserve celebrating?
Dialogue: 0,2:42:59.97,2:43:03.90,Default,,0,0,0,,这就是新的卡纳克(神庙)\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}This is the new Karnak.
Dialogue: 0,2:43:04.38,2:43:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,这代表了一个两千年之久的梦想的顶点\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}This represents the culmination of a dream more than 2000 years old...
Dialogue: 0,2:43:08.24,2:43:14.42,Default,,0,0,0,,一个因为你们盲目支持而实现的梦想\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...a dream now assured because of your unquestioning assistance.
Dialogue: 0,2:43:16.56,2:43:18.22,Default,,0,0,0,,为此\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}And for this...
Dialogue: 0,2:43:19.06,2:43:21.39,Default,,0,0,0,,我有愧于你们\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...I am ashamed...
Dialogue: 0,2:43:22.56,2:43:26.90,Default,,0,0,0,,愧在你们必须分享这样不恰当的奖励\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...ashamed that you must now share such inadequate a reward.
Dialogue: 0,2:43:28.57,2:43:30.56,Default,,0,0,0,,敬法老们\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}To the pharaohs...
Dialogue: 0,2:43:31.51,2:43:34.54,Default,,0,0,0,,他们最伟大的秘密托付给他们的仆人\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...their greatest secrets entrusted to their servants...
Dialogue: 0,2:43:35.14,2:43:39.48,Default,,0,0,0,,活埋在了黄沙覆盖的厅堂里\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...buried alive with them in sand-floored chambers.
Dialogue: 0,2:43:40.35,2:43:42.75,Default,,0,0,0,,好梦 先生们\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Sleep well, gentlemen.
Dialogue: 0,2:43:43.42,2:43:46.75,Default,,0,0,0,,我们的新的和平世界将受惠于…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Our new, peaceful world will be indebted...
Dialogue: 0,2:43:47.09,2:43:49.65,Default,,0,0,0,,…你们的伟大的牺牲\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...to your great sacrifice.
Dialogue: 0,2:43:50.59,2:43:52.79,Default,,0,0,0,,布巴斯提斯 {\fs33.333}古埃及的猫神{\r}\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Bubastis.
Dialogue: 0,2:43:56.96,2:43:59.96,Default,,0,0,0,,罗夏日记 最后的记录\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Rorschach's journal. Final entry.
Dialogue: 0,2:44:00.50,2:44:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,一切都是维特在幕后\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Veidt's behind everything.
Dialogue: 0,2:44:03.00,2:44:04.61,Default,,0,0,0,,为什么?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Why?
Dialogue: 0,2:44:04.61,2:44:06.95,Default,,0,0,0,,他的终局是什么?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}What's his endgame?
Dialogue: 0,2:44:06.95,2:44:10.83,Default,,0,0,0,,我想不出还有更危险的对手\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I cannot imagine a more dangerous opponent.
Dialogue: 0,2:44:10.83,2:44:14.43,Default,,0,0,0,,曾经开玩笑说他快到能抓住子弹\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Used to joke he was fast enough to catch a bullet.
Dialogue: 0,2:44:14.43,2:44:17.50,Default,,0,0,0,,他在雪地里能够干掉我们俩\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}He could kill us both alone in the snow.
Dialogue: 0,2:44:17.50,2:44:21.37,Default,,0,0,0,,那就是我们要去的地方：南极\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}That's where we're going now: Antarctica.
Dialogue: 0,2:44:21.37,2:44:24.31,Default,,0,0,0,,不管这文字被读到时我是生是死\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Whether I'm alive or dead upon this reading...
Dialogue: 0,2:44:24.31,2:44:28.74,Default,,0,0,0,,我希望这个世界存活时间够长 让你们能得到这本日记\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}... I hope the world survives long enough for this journal to reach you.
Dialogue: 0,2:44:28.74,2:44:31.48,Default,,0,0,0,,我活的一生没有妥协\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I live my life free of compromise...
Dialogue: 0,2:44:31.48,2:44:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,步入死亡阴影也没有抱怨和后悔\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}... and step into the shadow without complaint or regret.
Dialogue: 0,2:44:36.07,2:44:39.06,Default,,0,0,0,,罗夏 11月1号\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Rorschach, November 1 st.
Dialogue: 0,2:44:40.73,2:44:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}(纽约公报：苏联入侵阿富汗)
Dialogue: 0,2:44:44.85,2:44:47.25,Default,,0,0,0,,噢 愿上帝帮帮我们\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Oh, God help us.
Dialogue: 0,2:44:50.32,2:44:52.90,Default,,0,0,0,,- 你今天是不是来早了 哈?  - 是啊\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}- It's a little early for you, huh? - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,2:44:52.90,2:44:55.25,Default,,0,0,0,,我想上学之前看完那本书\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I wanted to finish the story before school.
Dialogue: 0,2:45:00.63,2:45:04.13,Default,,0,0,0,,听着 你留着它吧 明白吗?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Listen, now you just keep it, okay?
Dialogue: 0,2:45:05.23,2:45:07.98,Default,,0,0,0,,- 哈?  - 归你了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}- Huh? - It's yours.
Dialogue: 0,2:45:07.98,2:45:11.18,Default,,0,0,0,,我是说 生命太短暂了 对吧?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I mean, life's too short, right?
Dialogue: 0,2:45:11.18,2:45:12.56,Default,,0,0,0,,是啊\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,2:45:12.84,2:45:14.32,Default,,0,0,0,,呃…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Uh...
Dialogue: 0,2:45:14.32,2:45:15.93,Default,,0,0,0,,谢了 老兄\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Thanks, man.
Dialogue: 0,2:45:41.37,2:45:43.80,Default,,0,0,0,,为何死神与我擦肩而过?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Why does death pass me by?
Dialogue: 0,2:45:46.81,2:45:48.47,Default,,0,0,0,,戴维斯城?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Davidstown?
Dialogue: 0,2:45:49.74,2:45:51.44,Default,,0,0,0,,戴维斯城\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Davidstown.
Dialogue: 0,2:45:51.75,2:45:54.30,Default,,0,0,0,,我只剩几英里了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I was only miles away.
Dialogue: 0,2:45:54.30,2:45:56.18,Default,,0,0,0,,到现在那镇子已经被占领了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}By now the town was overrun.
Dialogue: 0,2:45:56.62,2:45:59.80,Default,,0,0,0,,那些恶魔们想着我已不是威胁\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}The fiends imagined themselves safe from me.
Dialogue: 0,2:45:59.80,2:46:01.34,Default,,0,0,0,,但现在我回家了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}But now I was home.
Dialogue: 0,2:46:01.34,2:46:03.76,Default,,0,0,0,,我就要报仇了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}And revenge would be mine.
Dialogue: 0,2:46:11.43,2:46:14.28,Default,,0,0,0,,不 那不是黑货船上的强盗\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}No, not the brigands from the Black Freighter.
Dialogue: 0,2:46:14.28,2:46:17.54,Default,,0,0,0,,这人我认出来了 戴维斯城的一个放债人\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}The man I recognized, a moneylender from Davidstown.
Dialogue: 0,2:46:17.81,2:46:20.09,Default,,0,0,0,,既然戴维斯城一定被占领了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}With Davidstown certainly captured...
Dialogue: 0,2:46:20.09,2:46:24.83,Default,,0,0,0,,为什么这无赖和他的淫妇 被允许自由通行半夜幽会? …\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}... why would this scoundrel and his wench be allowed free passage for this midnight tryst?
Dialogue: 0,2:46:24.83,2:46:26.17,Default,,0,0,0,,他勾结通敌?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Had he collaborated?
Dialogue: 0,2:46:26.17,2:46:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,他背叛了我的人民?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Had he betrayed my people?
Dialogue: 0,2:46:28.12,2:46:30.85,Default,,0,0,0,,- 还有我的家人?  - 来抓我吧 宝贝\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}- My family? WOMAN: Come and get it, babe.
Dialogue: 0,2:46:31.32,2:46:32.64,Default,,0,0,0,,来\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Here.
Dialogue: 0,2:46:41.60,2:46:43.95,Default,,0,0,0,,我的心变凉了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}My heart grew cold.
Dialogue: 0,2:46:43.95,2:46:47.25,Default,,0,0,0,,在被这个通敌者和他的海盗主子 冷笑着杀死之前…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Was my wife comforted before her execution...
Dialogue: 0,2:46:47.25,2:46:51.33,Default,,0,0,0,,…我的妻子有没有得到过宽慰?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}... while this collaborator and his pirate masters sneered?
Dialogue: 0,2:46:51.70,2:46:54.24,Default,,0,0,0,,我的决定很仓促 但并不难\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}My decision was hurried, but not difficult.
Dialogue: 0,2:46:54.24,2:46:55.64,Default,,0,0,0,,你是谁? 干什么?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}MAN: Who are you? What?
Dialogue: 0,2:46:58.28,2:47:01.92,Default,,0,0,0,,他的脑袋开了花 好像被他内心的罪孽压爆\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}His head burst, as if pressurized by the guilt within.
Dialogue: 0,2:47:11.36,2:47:14.01,Default,,0,0,0,,海盗的婊子不值得同情\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}A buccaneer's whore deserves no pity.
Dialogue: 0,2:47:18.07,2:47:20.38,Default,,0,0,0,,两个人骑马来了这儿\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Two figures had ridden here.
Dialogue: 0,2:47:20.38,2:47:23.23,Default,,0,0,0,,回去的必须是两个人\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Two must ride back.
Dialogue: 0,2:47:27.38,2:47:29.86,Default,,0,0,0,,一个海盗哨兵\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}A pirate sentry.
Dialogue: 0,2:47:29.86,2:47:34.04,Default,,0,0,0,,我从容骑过以免被怀疑\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I trotted unhurriedly to avoid suspicion.
Dialogue: 0,2:47:34.98,2:47:38.27,Default,,0,0,0,,他们的暴行 没有因戴维斯城的好人而停止…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Their violation did not stop with the good people of Davidstown...
Dialogue: 0,2:47:38.27,2:47:42.60,Default,,0,0,0,,但却极深地切割和浸染了我热爱的家乡\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}... but had cut deeply, infecting my beloved homeland.
Dialogue: 0,2:47:42.60,2:47:46.07,Default,,0,0,0,,我的戴维斯城不是我最后看到的那样了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}My Davidstown was not as I last saw it.
Dialogue: 0,2:47:46.07,2:47:50.18,Default,,0,0,0,,它已经被黑货船的诅咒折磨过\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Already it was afflicted with the curse of the Black Freighter.
Dialogue: 0,2:47:50.18,2:47:53.87,Default,,0,0,0,,很快 我将会在恶人当中涉险\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Soon, I would venture amongst evil men
Dialogue: 0,2:47:53.87,2:47:56.65,Default,,0,0,0,,…这些屠夫如今住在我的家里\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}butchers who now reside in my home...
Dialogue: 0,2:47:56.65,2:47:58.47,Default,,0,0,0,,…我要让他们畏惧我\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}... and make them fear me.
Dialogue: 0,2:48:00.85,2:48:05.85,Default,,0,0,0,,当我回家时 我发现街道出奇地安静\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Upon my return home, I found the streets conspicuously silent.
Dialogue: 0,2:48:07.82,2:48:10.78,Default,,0,0,0,,我悄无声息地进入我原本的住所\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I entered my former residence noiselessly.
Dialogue: 0,2:48:11.39,2:48:17.28,Default,,0,0,0,,小心不把海盗屠夫们从他们 放纵的熟睡中惊醒\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Careful not to rouse the pirate butchers occupying it from their debauched slumber.
Dialogue: 0,2:48:23.03,2:48:25.35,Default,,0,0,0,,没有察觉死神已在他们身边\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Unaware that death was amongst them...
Dialogue: 0,2:48:25.35,2:48:30.62,Default,,0,0,0,,他们将毫不知情地尝到死神的拥抱\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}... they would know its dark embrace without ever understanding why.
Dialogue: 0,2:48:30.62,2:48:33.76,Default,,0,0,0,,不过有一个人醒了 慌乱\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}One, however, was awake. Frantic.
Dialogue: 0,2:48:33.76,2:48:35.34,Default,,0,0,0,,为免他发出警报…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Lest he should raise alarms...
Dialogue: 0,2:48:35.34,2:48:39.26,Default,,0,0,0,,…我在他进入这夜幕包围的房间时 把他打倒了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}... I set upon him as he entered the night-wrapped chamber.
Dialogue: 0,2:48:39.91,2:48:41.94,Default,,0,0,0,,没有海盗过来 但更糟的事情发生了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}No pirates come, but something worse.
Dialogue: 0,2:48:43.62,2:48:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,父亲\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Father?
Dialogue: 0,2:48:44.80,2:48:49.25,Default,,0,0,0,,我抬头看着这些熟悉的脸庞 因她们的恐惧而住手\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I look up into faces familiar, save for their terror.
Dialogue: 0,2:48:49.69,2:48:53.21,Default,,0,0,0,,从那无力而带血的唇中 她说出了我的名字\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Through puffed and bloodied lips, she mouthed my name.
Dialogue: 0,2:48:53.21,2:48:56.53,Default,,0,0,0,,我的爱人 为什么?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}My love, why?
Dialogue: 0,2:49:01.04,2:49:06.53,Default,,0,0,0,,到来的真相如此沉重 没有余地让人恢复理智\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}There came an understanding so large it left no room for sanity.
Dialogue: 0,2:49:07.34,2:49:09.04,Default,,0,0,0,,于是我跑了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}So I ran.
Dialogue: 0,2:49:09.46,2:49:11.50,Default,,0,0,0,,她怎么了?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}MAN 1: What's happened to her?
Dialogue: 0,2:49:12.31,2:49:13.75,Default,,0,0,0,,你\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}MAN 2: You.
Dialogue: 0,2:49:15.12,2:49:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,对我诅咒的认知占据了我 呼喊着庆祝它那可怕的胜利\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}The knowledge of my damnation paced me, shouting, celebrating its awful victory.
Dialogue: 0,2:49:21.00,2:49:22.90,Default,,0,0,0,,我的推论是无暇的\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}My deduction was flawless.
Dialogue: 0,2:49:22.90,2:49:25.17,Default,,0,0,0,,黑货船是朝戴维斯城航行的\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}The Black Freighter was heading to Davidstown.
Dialogue: 0,2:49:25.17,2:49:28.06,Default,,0,0,0,,- 它应该到了 - 他往这边跑了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}- It should have arrived. MAN 3: He went that way!
Dialogue: 0,2:49:28.86,2:49:32.44,Default,,0,0,0,,你就不能告诉我这事的结局如何吗? 省得我们再啰嗦\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}LAURIE: Can't you just tell me how this ends and save us the trouble?
Dialogue: 0,2:49:33.37,2:49:35.42,Default,,0,0,0,,它会以你的眼泪结束\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}JON: It ends with you in tears.
Dialogue: 0,2:49:35.42,2:49:36.43,Default,,0,0,0,,眼泪?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Tears?
Dialogue: 0,2:49:37.14,2:49:39.19,Default,,0,0,0,,那么你不回地球了?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}So you don't come back to Earth.
Dialogue: 0,2:49:39.19,2:49:42.58,Default,,0,0,0,,在某个时刻 是的\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}At some point, yes.
Dialogue: 0,2:49:43.71,2:49:46.79,Default,,0,0,0,,街道上满是死亡\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}The streets are filled with death.
Dialogue: 0,2:49:46.79,2:49:49.03,Default,,0,0,0,,乔恩 拜托\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Jon, please.
Dialogue: 0,2:49:49.03,2:49:53.77,Default,,0,0,0,,你必须阻止这一切 每个人都会死\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You have to stop this. Everyone will die.
Dialogue: 0,2:49:53.77,2:49:58.12,Default,,0,0,0,,而宇宙根本不会察觉\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}And the universe will not even notice.
Dialogue: 0,2:50:00.56,2:50:04.79,Default,,0,0,0,,在我看来 生命的存在\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}In my opinion, the existence of life...
Dialogue: 0,2:50:05.67,2:50:08.66,Default,,0,0,0,,是一种被极为高估的现象\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...is a highly overrated phenomenon.
Dialogue: 0,2:50:10.57,2:50:12.87,Default,,0,0,0,,看看你的周围吧\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Just look around you.
Dialogue: 0,2:50:15.61,2:50:19.94,Default,,0,0,0,,没有那么多微小生物 火星过得如此完美\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Mars gets along perfectly well without so much as a microorganism.
Dialogue: 0,2:50:20.58,2:50:25.30,Default,,0,0,0,,这儿 是一幅永远在变化的地形图\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Here, it's a constantly changing topographical map...
Dialogue: 0,2:50:25.30,2:50:31.26,Default,,0,0,0,,围绕着地极流动变换 涟漪广阔千年\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...flowing and shifting around the pole in ripples 10,000 years wide.
Dialogue: 0,2:50:32.09,2:50:33.74,Default,,0,0,0,,告诉我\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}So tell me...
Dialogue: 0,2:50:33.74,2:50:38.17,Default,,0,0,0,,所有这些 怎会靠一条输油管道而获得巨大改进?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...how would all of this be greatly improved by an oil pipeline?
Dialogue: 0,2:50:38.60,2:50:40.59,Default,,0,0,0,,靠购物中心吗?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}By a shopping mall?
Dialogue: 0,2:50:44.94,2:50:49.39,Default,,0,0,0,,所以要求奇迹发生 就是太过分了吗?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}So it's too much to ask for a miracle?
Dialogue: 0,2:50:49.39,2:50:51.71,Default,,0,0,0,,奇迹 按照他们的定义 是无意义的\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Miracles, by their definition, are meaningless.
Dialogue: 0,2:50:51.71,2:50:53.38,Default,,0,0,0,,哦 老天 乔恩！\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Oh, God, Jon!
Dialogue: 0,2:50:53.38,2:50:58.44,Default,,0,0,0,,- 只有能够发生的才会发生 - 别再胡说八道\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}- Only what can happen does happen. - Just stop your bullshit.
Dialogue: 0,2:50:59.52,2:51:02.20,Default,,0,0,0,,让这东西着陆 马上\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Land this thing. Now.
Dialogue: 0,2:51:02.20,2:51:04.78,Default,,0,0,0,,如你所愿\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}JON: As you wish.
Dialogue: 0,2:51:10.40,2:51:11.61,Default,,0,0,0,,你知道吗?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}LAURIE: You know what?
Dialogue: 0,2:51:11.61,2:51:14.25,Default,,0,0,0,,你可以把我送回地球 让我跟丹和我妈妈一起被烤焦\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You can send me back to Earth to fry with Dan and my mom...
Dialogue: 0,2:51:14.25,2:51:17.02,Default,,0,0,0,,还有其他无用的人类一起\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...and all the other worthless humans.
Dialogue: 0,2:51:17.02,2:51:18.37,Default,,0,0,0,,但要知道你错了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}But know that you were wrong.
Dialogue: 0,2:51:19.24,2:51:20.51,Default,,0,0,0,,你说过这事会以我的眼泪结束\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You said this ended with me in tears...
Dialogue: 0,2:51:20.51,2:51:22.54,Default,,0,0,0,,看吧 什么也没有\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...and look: Nothing.
Dialogue: 0,2:51:23.24,2:51:25.07,Default,,0,0,0,,也许每一件事你都错了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Maybe you were wrong about everything.
Dialogue: 0,2:51:25.07,2:51:30.25,Default,,0,0,0,,你抱怨我拒绝以生命的视角来看待生命\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You complain that I refuse to see life on life's terms...
Dialogue: 0,2:51:30.99,2:51:34.77,Default,,0,0,0,,然而你不断地拒绝从我的视角去看待事情\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...yet you continuously refuse to see things from my perspective.
Dialogue: 0,2:51:34.77,2:51:39.47,Default,,0,0,0,,- 你排除了你害怕的东西  - 我不害怕\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}- You shut out what you're afraid of. - I'm not afraid.
Dialogue: 0,2:51:39.47,2:51:41.48,Default,,0,0,0,,你要我按你的方式看待事物吗?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You want me to see things your way?
Dialogue: 0,2:51:41.48,2:51:44.57,Default,,0,0,0,,来吧 给我看看 照你那样来做\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Go ahead, show me. Do that thing you do.
Dialogue: 0,2:51:51.56,2:51:54.74,Default,,0,0,0,,魔法 梦想 那是我以前拥有的\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Magic. Dreams. That is what I had before.
Dialogue: 0,2:51:54.74,2:51:57.13,Default,,0,0,0,,我以前是个英雄 该死的\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I was a hero, goddamn it!
Dialogue: 0,2:51:57.13,2:51:59.92,Default,,0,0,0,,你变老了又不是我的错 你有什么好抱怨的?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}It's not my fault you got old. What do you have to complain about?
Dialogue: 0,2:51:59.92,2:52:02.26,Default,,0,0,0,,我给你和你的孩子 提供餐桌上的食物\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I put food on the table for you and your child.
Dialogue: 0,2:52:02.26,2:52:03.34,Default,,0,0,0,,你干嘛不打电话给你朋友艾迪?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Why don't you call your friend Eddie?
Dialogue: 0,2:52:03.34,2:52:05.28,Default,,0,0,0,,也许他能给你更好的生活\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Maybe he can give you a better life.
Dialogue: 0,2:52:06.02,2:52:08.77,Default,,0,0,0,,即使是最肮脏的部分\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}SALLY: Even the grimy parts of it...
Dialogue: 0,2:52:09.09,2:52:11.32,Default,,0,0,0,,却越来越明亮\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...keep on getting brighter.
Dialogue: 0,2:52:11.66,2:52:15.31,Default,,0,0,0,,知道吗? 你妈妈她以前是空前的选美冠军\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You know, your mom, she was one of the all-time champion beauties.
Dialogue: 0,2:52:15.31,2:52:20.09,Default,,0,0,0,,- 你有她的眼睛 你还有…  - 把你手拿开\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}- You got her eyes, you know. You got... - Take your hands off her.
Dialogue: 0,2:52:20.09,2:52:22.32,Default,,0,0,0,,嘿 美人 好久不见\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}EDDIE: Hey, doll. Long time no see.
Dialogue: 0,2:52:22.32,2:52:24.15,Default,,0,0,0,,对我来说还不够久 埃迪\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Not long enough in my book, Eddie.
Dialogue: 0,2:52:24.15,2:52:25.16,Default,,0,0,0,,上车\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Get in the car.
Dialogue: 0,2:52:25.80,2:52:27.47,Default,,0,0,0,,立刻\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Now.
Dialogue: 0,2:52:28.44,2:52:30.50,Default,,0,0,0,,你的沉沦完全没有底线吗?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Are there no depths you won't sink to?
Dialogue: 0,2:52:30.50,2:52:34.45,Default,,0,0,0,,老天 莎莉 一个人就不能跟他的…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Jesus Christ, Sally. Can't a guy talk to his...
Dialogue: 0,2:52:35.15,2:52:36.92,Default,,0,0,0,,…老朋友的女儿说说话吗?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...you know, old friend's daughter?
Dialogue: 0,2:52:39.15,2:52:40.48,Default,,0,0,0,,开车\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Drive.
Dialogue: 0,2:52:46.49,2:52:49.26,Default,,0,0,0,,那是个错误 就那一次\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}SALLY: It was a mistake. One time.
Dialogue: 0,2:52:49.75,2:52:52.64,Default,,0,0,0,,那个试图强奸你的人 几年后你倒让他得手了?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Guy tries to rape you, and years later, you let him finish the job?
Dialogue: 0,2:52:52.64,2:52:55.85,Default,,0,0,0,,怎么? 当时你喝醉了还是寂寞了?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}What? Were you drunk or just lonely?
Dialogue: 0,2:52:55.85,2:52:58.81,Default,,0,0,0,,难道我要背负着这件事活下去?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Am I ever gonna live this down?
Dialogue: 0,2:53:02.18,2:53:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,劳瑞\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Laurie.
Dialogue: 0,2:53:08.18,2:53:09.51,Default,,0,0,0,,不\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}No.
Dialogue: 0,2:53:11.52,2:53:14.17,Default,,0,0,0,,不 不是他\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}No, not him.
Dialogue: 0,2:53:14.17,2:53:16.28,Default,,0,0,0,,笑匠\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}The Comedian...
Dialogue: 0,2:53:16.69,2:53:18.78,Default,,0,0,0,,是你的父亲\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...was your father.
Dialogue: 0,2:53:20.26,2:53:21.96,Default,,0,0,0,,不\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}No.
Dialogue: 0,2:53:25.27,2:53:30.97,Default,,0,0,0,,不！不！不！\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}No! No! No!
Dialogue: 0,2:54:03.57,2:54:05.56,Default,,0,0,0,,我的人生就是…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}My life is just...
Dialogue: 0,2:54:06.24,2:54:08.52,Default,,0,0,0,,一个大笑话\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...one big joke.
Dialogue: 0,2:54:08.52,2:54:11.10,Default,,0,0,0,,我并不觉得你的人生是个笑话\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I don't think your life is a joke.
Dialogue: 0,2:54:12.75,2:54:14.74,Default,,0,0,0,,好吧\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Yeah, well...
Dialogue: 0,2:54:16.58,2:54:20.75,Default,,0,0,0,,抱歉 我不相信你的幽默感\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...I'm sorry if I don't trust your sense of humor.
Dialogue: 0,2:54:28.93,2:54:30.59,Default,,0,0,0,,我要是承认我错了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Will you smile...
Dialogue: 0,2:54:32.27,2:54:34.73,Default,,0,0,0,,你会笑一笑吗?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...if I admit I was wrong?
Dialogue: 0,2:54:37.60,2:54:39.60,Default,,0,0,0,,关于什么事?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}LAURIE: About what?
Dialogue: 0,2:54:41.50,2:54:43.17,Default,,0,0,0,,奇迹\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Miracles.
Dialogue: 0,2:54:44.78,2:54:47.94,Default,,0,0,0,,天文级数的小概率事件发生 比如…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Events with astronomical odds of occurring like...
Dialogue: 0,2:54:48.78,2:54:51.43,Default,,0,0,0,,…氧气变成金子\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...oxygen turning into gold.
Dialogue: 0,2:54:51.43,2:54:56.29,Default,,0,0,0,,我一直渴望见证这样的事件 然而我却忽视了…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I've longed to witness such an event, and yet I neglect that...
Dialogue: 0,2:54:56.96,2:54:59.32,Default,,0,0,0,,…人类的结合\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...in human coupling...
Dialogue: 0,2:55:00.13,2:55:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,数以百万的细胞争相创造一个生命\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...millions upon millions of cells compete to create life...
Dialogue: 0,2:55:04.47,2:55:07.26,Default,,0,0,0,,一代又一代 直到…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...for generation after generation until...
Dialogue: 0,2:55:08.24,2:55:11.20,Default,,0,0,0,,终于 你的母亲\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}... finally, your mother...
Dialogue: 0,2:55:11.57,2:55:12.82,Default,,0,0,0,,爱上了一个男人\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...loves a man...
Dialogue: 0,2:55:13.41,2:55:17.18,Default,,0,0,0,,艾德华·布雷克 笑匠 这个人她有百般理由憎恨\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...Edward Blake, the Comedian, a man she has every reason to hate...
Dialogue: 0,2:55:17.18,2:55:21.25,Default,,0,0,0,,超出这种矛盾 违反这莫测的几率\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...and out of that contradiction, against unfathomable odds...
Dialogue: 0,2:55:21.85,2:55:23.75,Default,,0,0,0,,是你…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...it's you...
Dialogue: 0,2:55:25.49,2:55:26.82,Default,,0,0,0,,唯一的\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Only...
Dialogue: 0,2:55:27.49,2:55:28.98,Default,,0,0,0,,你\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...you.
Dialogue: 0,2:55:29.82,2:55:31.13,Default,,0,0,0,,显现出来\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}That emerged.
Dialogue: 0,2:55:31.66,2:55:36.31,Default,,0,0,0,,要在所有的混沌中…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}To distill so specific a form...
Dialogue: 0,2:55:36.31,2:55:38.64,Default,,0,0,0,,提取出这样特定的一个形体\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...from all that chaos...
Dialogue: 0,2:55:40.50,2:55:43.47,Default,,0,0,0,,就像是把空气变成了金子\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...is like turning air into gold.
Dialogue: 0,2:55:47.84,2:55:49.90,Default,,0,0,0,,一个奇迹\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}A miracle.
Dialogue: 0,2:55:53.35,2:55:54.84,Default,,0,0,0,,因此\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}And so...
Dialogue: 0,2:55:55.35,2:55:57.18,Default,,0,0,0,,我错了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...I was wrong.
Dialogue: 0,2:55:59.19,2:56:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,擦干眼泪 我们回家吧\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Now dry your eyes, and let's go home.
Dialogue: 0,2:56:30.55,2:56:32.58,Default,,0,0,0,,我们的人工结构受压\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}We got a bearing on that artificial structure.
Dialogue: 0,2:56:33.05,2:56:34.66,Default,,0,0,0,,热力信号破表了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Heat signature's off the charts.
Dialogue: 0,2:56:35.56,2:56:38.70,Default,,0,0,0,,- 维特  - 我不喜欢阿基米德这样动作\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}- Veidt. - I don't like the way Archie's kicking.
Dialogue: 0,2:56:45.07,2:56:46.10,Default,,0,0,0,,(警告：引擎故障)
Dialogue: 0,2:56:47.07,2:56:49.96,Default,,0,0,0,,- 是引擎  - 它们在结冰 抓牢了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}- The engines. - They're icing up. Hold onto something.
Dialogue: 0,2:56:50.67,2:56:52.76,Default,,0,0,0,,丹尼尔 你飞得太低了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Daniel, you're coming in too low.
Dialogue: 0,2:56:55.47,2:56:58.89,Default,,0,0,0,,不是想干扰 但是也许应该即刻拉升\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Don't wish to interfere, but perhaps should pull up sharply...
Dialogue: 0,2:56:58.89,2:57:02.85,Default,,0,0,0,,我知道 我正在尝试 该死的\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I know! I'm trying. I'm trying to pull him up, goddamn it!
Dialogue: 0,2:57:30.11,2:57:33.80,Default,,0,0,0,,我打算重定向喷射的热量 加快除冰\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}DAN: I'm gonna redirect the heat from the flamethrower to speed up deicing...
Dialogue: 0,2:57:33.80,2:57:36.84,Default,,0,0,0,,不过这需要一阵子 我们没有时间等\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...but it's gonna take a while and we don't have time to wait.
Dialogue: 0,2:57:38.29,2:57:39.80,Default,,0,0,0,,你需要穿点更暖和的\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You need something warmer.
Dialogue: 0,2:57:40.29,2:57:42.45,Default,,0,0,0,,我穿这就行\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Fine like this.
Dialogue: 0,2:58:11.95,2:58:13.82,Default,,0,0,0,,怎么了 姑娘?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}What is it, girl?
Dialogue: 0,2:58:43.42,2:58:45.28,Default,,0,0,0,,阿德里安是和平主义者\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}DAN: Adrian's a pacifist.
Dialogue: 0,2:58:45.89,2:58:47.42,Default,,0,0,0,,他是个素食者 老天在上\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}He's a vegetarian, for chrissakes.
Dialogue: 0,2:58:48.95,2:58:50.68,Default,,0,0,0,,他一生没杀过一个人\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}He's never killed anyone in his life.
Dialogue: 0,2:58:50.68,2:58:52.25,Default,,0,0,0,,希特勒也是素食主义者\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Hitler was vegetarian.
Dialogue: 0,2:58:52.25,2:58:54.29,Default,,0,0,0,,你神经过敏了 把他交给我吧\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You're squeamish, leave him to me.
Dialogue: 0,2:58:54.29,2:58:56.55,Default,,0,0,0,,我们不会有第二次机会\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}We won't get second chance.
Dialogue: 0,3:00:08.04,3:00:09.41,Default,,0,0,0,,先生们\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Gentlemen.
Dialogue: 0,3:00:09.87,3:00:10.94,Default,,0,0,0,,欢迎\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Welcome.
Dialogue: 0,3:00:10.94,3:00:13.87,Default,,0,0,0,,阿德里安 我们全都知道了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Adrian, we know everything.
Dialogue: 0,3:00:13.87,3:00:16.09,Default,,0,0,0,,那我们还有什么好说的 丹?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Then what's there to discuss, Dan?
Dialogue: 0,3:00:16.09,3:00:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,多着呢 你杀了笑匠\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Plenty. You killed Comedian.
Dialogue: 0,3:00:18.96,3:00:20.67,Default,,0,0,0,,愿他安息\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}May he rest in peace.
Dialogue: 0,3:00:21.11,3:00:23.76,Default,,0,0,0,,布雷克第一个想明白\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Blake figured it out first.
Dialogue: 0,3:00:23.76,3:00:28.01,Default,,0,0,0,,尼克松派他监视我们 确保我们不会坏事\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Nixon had him keeping tabs on us, making sure we weren't rocking the boat.
Dialogue: 0,3:00:28.89,3:00:31.31,Default,,0,0,0,,布雷克发现了我在卡纳克这里做的事情\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Blake found out what I was doing here in Karnak...
Dialogue: 0,3:00:31.31,3:00:35.39,Default,,0,0,0,,他去拜访可怜的摩罗神的时候 已经快不行了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}... and by the time he visited poor Moloch, he was cracking badly.
Dialogue: 0,3:00:35.70,3:00:38.90,Default,,0,0,0,,连我都无法预计他会是个改邪归正的人\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Even I couldn't predict he'd be the one to have a change of heart.
Dialogue: 0,3:00:39.57,3:00:41.15,Default,,0,0,0,,所以\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}So...
Dialogue: 0,3:00:42.14,3:00:44.07,Default,,0,0,0,,我不得不杀了他\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...I had to kill him.
Dialogue: 0,3:00:44.64,3:00:48.45,Default,,0,0,0,,然后我中立了乔恩 这任务不容易\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Then I neutralized Jon. No easy task.
Dialogue: 0,3:00:48.45,3:00:51.17,Default,,0,0,0,,我花了大约20亿去研究超光速粒子\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I put roughly $2 billion into tachyon research...
Dialogue: 0,3:00:51.17,3:00:53.29,Default,,0,0,0,,以阻断乔恩的未来视像\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...to block Jon's vision of the future.
Dialogue: 0,3:00:53.29,3:00:55.75,Default,,0,0,0,,你利用他的心理特征操纵了他\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}RORSCHACH: You used his psych profile to manipulate him.
Dialogue: 0,3:00:56.18,3:00:57.57,Default,,0,0,0,,让他离开了这个星球\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Got him to leave the planet.
Dialogue: 0,3:00:57.57,3:01:01.37,Default,,0,0,0,,我认识乔恩很长时间了 知道他缺乏情感\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I've known Jon long enough to see he isn't devoid of emotion.
Dialogue: 0,3:01:01.37,3:01:05.49,Default,,0,0,0,,他微妙的招牌表情抽动 外行不易察觉 但对我…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}His subtle facial twitches wouldn't be noticed by the layman, but to me...
Dialogue: 0,3:01:05.49,3:01:07.34,Default,,0,0,0,,…就跟他在啜泣一样\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}... he might as well have been sobbing.
Dialogue: 0,3:01:07.66,3:01:10.94,Default,,0,0,0,,我所需要的就是继续牵引这条线\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}All I needed to do was tug on the thread.
Dialogue: 0,3:01:10.94,3:01:13.03,Default,,0,0,0,,乔恩感受到突然的情感冲击…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}The sudden flood of emotion Jon felt...
Dialogue: 0,3:01:13.03,3:01:16.78,Default,,0,0,0,,当他逐步相信他给所爱的人带去癌症…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}... when he came to believe he'd given cancer to the people he loved...
Dialogue: 0,3:01:16.78,3:01:19.09,Default,,0,0,0,,这成了他离开地球的所有借口\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}... was all the excuse he needed to leave Earth.
Dialogue: 0,3:01:19.09,3:01:23.09,Default,,0,0,0,,你的混蛋杀手 你雇他想干掉我们\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}DAN: Your bullshit assassin. You paid him to throw us off.
Dialogue: 0,3:01:23.09,3:01:27.82,Default,,0,0,0,,切斯先生为了更高的理由献出了自己的生命 丹\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}ADRIAN: Mr. Chess gave his life in the service of a higher cause, Dan.
Dialogue: 0,3:01:29.92,3:01:33.08,Default,,0,0,0,,我放了一个氰化物胶囊在他嘴里\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I put a cyanide capsule in his mouth...
Dialogue: 0,3:01:33.08,3:01:35.83,Default,,0,0,0,,只留下了一个未解决的尾巴\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}... leaving only one loose end:
Dialogue: 0,3:01:36.45,3:01:40.19,Default,,0,0,0,,就是你 还有你的面具杀手理论\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You, and your mask-killer theory...
Dialogue: 0,3:01:40.19,3:01:43.45,Default,,0,0,0,,一个你带着反社会人格执着追寻的理论\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}... one you followed with the tenacity of a true sociopath.
Dialogue: 0,3:01:43.45,3:01:45.15,Default,,0,0,0,,我给警察做了提示\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I tipped off the police.
Dialogue: 0,3:01:45.15,3:01:47.71,Default,,0,0,0,,一旦你进了监狱 我就能继续行动\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Once you were in prison, I was able to move forward.
Dialogue: 0,3:01:47.71,3:01:50.36,Default,,0,0,0,,抱歉让你失望了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}RORSCHACH: Sorry to disappoint you.
Dialogue: 0,3:02:03.55,3:02:06.18,Default,,0,0,0,,我们本该让世界更美好\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}DAN: We were supposed to make the world a better place.
Dialogue: 0,3:02:06.18,3:02:07.95,Default,,0,0,0,,丹 那正是我在做的事\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}ADRIAN: Dan, that's exactly what I am doing.
Dialogue: 0,3:02:07.95,3:02:09.49,Default,,0,0,0,,核战?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}DAN: Nuclear war?
Dialogue: 0,3:02:09.49,3:02:11.75,Default,,0,0,0,,灭绝人类?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Human extinction?
Dialogue: 0,3:02:21.40,3:02:26.45,Default,,0,0,0,,当然 我的道德保障让我休止于必要的牺牲\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}ADRIAN: Of course, my moral safeguards gave me pause at the necessary sacrifice.
Dialogue: 0,3:02:26.45,3:02:29.59,Default,,0,0,0,,全球的几个重要的地区\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}A few key regions around the globe...
Dialogue: 0,3:02:29.59,3:02:35.23,Default,,0,0,0,,纽约 洛杉矶 莫斯科 香港\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}New York, Los Angeles, Moscow, Hong Kong.
Dialogue: 0,3:02:35.23,3:02:36.98,Default,,0,0,0,,瞬间崩溃\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Disintegrated in an instant.
Dialogue: 0,3:02:37.65,3:02:41.13,Default,,0,0,0,,1500万人被杀死\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Fifteen million people killed...
Dialogue: 0,3:02:41.13,3:02:43.27,Default,,0,0,0,,是曼哈顿博士所为\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...by Dr. Manhattan himself.
Dialogue: 0,3:02:44.42,3:02:47.28,Default,,0,0,0,,这是第三次世界大战对地球的惩罚\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}The world's punishment for flirting with World War III.
Dialogue: 0,3:02:47.28,3:02:48.57,Default,,0,0,0,,乔恩不会做这种事的\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Jon wouldn't do that.
Dialogue: 0,3:02:49.10,3:02:51.87,Default,,0,0,0,,这个房间之外的人们不必知道这个事实\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}A fact no one outside this room ever has to know.
Dialogue: 0,3:02:52.43,3:02:56.23,Default,,0,0,0,,我一直致力的能源突破刚刚取得成果\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}The energy breakthrough I was working on just came to fruition.
Dialogue: 0,3:02:56.84,3:03:00.99,Default,,0,0,0,,这些年来 乔恩一直在帮我复制他的能量\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}All these years, Jon was helping me replicate his power...
Dialogue: 0,3:03:00.99,3:03:03.59,Default,,0,0,0,,却不知道我打算怎么利用这些能量\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...unaware of how I planned to use it.
Dialogue: 0,3:03:03.86,3:03:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,你们看…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You see...
Dialogue: 0,3:03:06.61,3:03:08.01,Default,,0,0,0,,笑匠是对的\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...the Comedian was right.
Dialogue: 0,3:03:09.72,3:03:14.76,Default,,0,0,0,,人性的凶残天性将必然导致全球毁灭\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Humanity's savage nature will inevitably lead to global annihilation.
Dialogue: 0,3:03:14.76,3:03:17.93,Default,,0,0,0,,所以为了拯救这个星球\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}So in order to save this planet...
Dialogue: 0,3:03:17.93,3:03:20.02,Default,,0,0,0,,我必须用计取胜…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...I had to trick it...
Dialogue: 0,3:03:20.39,3:03:24.48,Default,,0,0,0,,用人类历史上最伟大的恶作剧\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...with the greatest practical joke in human history.
Dialogue: 0,3:03:24.48,3:03:28.15,Default,,0,0,0,,- 杀死上百万人  - 为了救数亿人\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}- Killing millions. - To save billions.
Dialogue: 0,3:03:28.64,3:03:30.75,Default,,0,0,0,,必要的犯罪\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}A necessary crime.
Dialogue: 0,3:03:30.75,3:03:32.99,Default,,0,0,0,,你知道我们不可能让你去做的\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}RORSCHACH: You know we can't let you do that.
Dialogue: 0,3:03:34.37,3:03:36.66,Default,,0,0,0,,"去做" 罗夏?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}"Do that," Rorschach?
Dialogue: 0,3:03:36.66,3:03:38.37,Default,,0,0,0,,我不是漫画里的恶棍\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I'm not a comic-book villain.
Dialogue: 0,3:03:39.15,3:03:41.60,Default,,0,0,0,,你真的以为 但凡你们有一点可能影响我的计划\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Do you seriously think I'd explain my masterstroke to you...
Dialogue: 0,3:03:41.60,3:03:45.55,Default,,0,0,0,,我会给你们解释我的妙招吗?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...if there were even the slightest possibility you could affect the outcome?
Dialogue: 0,3:03:48.49,3:03:51.34,Default,,0,0,0,,35分钟前我就启动了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I triggered it 35 minutes ago.
Dialogue: 0,3:03:51.34,3:03:59.29,Default,,0,0,0,,(东京 伦敦 巴黎 北京 莫斯科 纽约)
Dialogue: 0,3:04:02.45,3:04:04.39,Default,,0,0,0,,(纽约)
Dialogue: 0,3:04:15.45,3:04:20.95,Default,,0,0,0,,最终 我来到了一片阴沉的黑色海洋 在我面前无尽延伸\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}MARINER: Eventually, I came to a dismal black ocean stretching endlessly before me.
Dialogue: 0,3:04:21.62,3:04:25.14,Default,,0,0,0,,我怎么会落到如此骇人的地步 还是以爱…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}How had I reached this appalling position with love...
Dialogue: 0,3:04:25.14,3:04:28.18,Default,,0,0,0,,…我唯一的爱 作为我的指引\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}... only love, as my guide?
Dialogue: 0,3:04:29.80,3:04:32.40,Default,,0,0,0,,那个放债人漂到了我的脚边\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}The moneylender floated at my feet.
Dialogue: 0,3:04:32.97,3:04:36.02,Default,,0,0,0,,高贵的意图将我引向暴行\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Noble intentions had led me to atrocity.
Dialogue: 0,3:04:36.02,3:04:42.31,Default,,0,0,0,,正义之怒助燃了我的遐想 那可怕的图谋不过是错觉\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}The righteous anger fueling my ingenious, awful scheme was but delusion.
Dialogue: 0,3:04:42.31,3:04:44.13,Default,,0,0,0,,我错在哪里?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Where was my error?
Dialogue: 0,3:04:44.69,3:04:49.88,Default,,0,0,0,,正要重新开始回想时 我抬起了头看到了她\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Planning to resume my flight, I raised my head and saw her.
Dialogue: 0,3:04:52.15,3:04:56.74,Default,,0,0,0,,那艘船看起来正在等待 不是在伺机进攻\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}The vessel seemed to be waiting, not hovering to strike.
Dialogue: 0,3:04:56.74,3:05:00.99,Default,,0,0,0,,然而逐渐地 我明白了单纯的动机把我带向了什么\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}And, gradually, I understood what innocent intent had brought me to...
Dialogue: 0,3:05:01.83,3:05:04.56,Default,,0,0,0,,我涉水前往那最深处\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}... and waded out beyond my depth.
Dialogue: 0,3:05:05.58,3:05:08.88,Default,,0,0,0,,当我游向下锚的黑货船时\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}The unspeakable truth loomed unavoidably before me...
Dialogue: 0,3:05:08.88,3:05:11.92,Default,,0,0,0,,那说不出口的事实无可避免地显现在我面前\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}... as I swam towards the anchored Freighter.
Dialogue: 0,3:05:11.92,3:05:16.42,Default,,0,0,0,,它那黑暗、摇摆不定的桅杆充满我的视线\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Its dark and lurching mast filled all my vision.
Dialogue: 0,3:05:16.42,3:05:19.56,Default,,0,0,0,,我所有善意的计划全都终结于此\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}All my well-meaning plans had come to this.
Dialogue: 0,3:05:19.56,3:05:23.52,Default,,0,0,0,,那个我想要拯救的世界 在回忆中失落\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}The world I tried to save was lost beyond recall.
Dialogue: 0,3:05:24.25,3:05:26.23,Default,,0,0,0,,一条绳索垂了下来\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}A rope snaked down.
Dialogue: 0,3:05:26.23,3:05:28.48,Default,,0,0,0,,急切中 我抓住了它\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Sputtering, I grabbed it.
Dialogue: 0,3:05:28.48,3:05:31.37,Default,,0,0,0,,然后从上面的甲板上 欢呼声骤起\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}And from the decks above, a cheer went up...
Dialogue: 0,3:05:31.37,3:05:35.79,Default,,0,0,0,,二者都粗劣和黑暗 它的恶臭亵渎着上天\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}... both gross and black, its stench affronting heaven.
Dialogue: 0,3:05:38.60,3:05:41.03,Default,,0,0,0,,根本就没有要攻占戴维斯城的计划\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}There had been no plan to capture Davidstown.
Dialogue: 0,3:05:41.80,3:05:45.91,Default,,0,0,0,,他们是来等待的 等到可以收取他们唯一珍视的奖赏\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}They'd come to wait until they could collect the only prize they valued.
Dialogue: 0,3:05:47.04,3:05:50.25,Default,,0,0,0,,他们真正想要的唯一一个灵魂\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Claim the only soul they truly wanted.
Dialogue: 0,3:05:56.18,3:05:58.28,Default,,0,0,0,,我就是恐怖\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I was a horror.
Dialogue: 0,3:05:59.12,3:06:02.26,Default,,0,0,0,,我必在恐怖中容身\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Amongst horrors must I dwell.
Dialogue: 0,3:06:03.12,3:06:05.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\a5}(剧终)
Dialogue: 0,3:06:08.12,3:06:11.15,Default,,0,0,0,,(《黑货船》)
Dialogue: 0,3:06:11.93,3:06:16.03,Default,,0,0,0,,- 老兄 这破玩意儿毫无道理  - 可不是吗\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}- Man, this shit don't make no sense. - You're telling me.
Dialogue: 0,3:06:17.30,3:06:19.47,Default,,0,0,0,,抱歉 你留着这本垃圾吧\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Sorry, but you can keep this garbage.
Dialogue: 0,3:06:19.47,3:06:20.66,Default,,0,0,0,,浪费我他妈的时间\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Wasting all my damn time.
Dialogue: 0,3:06:21.75,3:06:24.09,Default,,0,0,0,,知道吗 这段时间你总是到这儿来\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You know, all this time you've been coming here...
Dialogue: 0,3:06:24.09,3:06:25.66,Default,,0,0,0,,我从不知道你的名字\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...I never caught your name.
Dialogue: 0,3:06:27.35,3:06:28.46,Default,,0,0,0,,伯纳德\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Bernard.
Dialogue: 0,3:06:28.75,3:06:30.50,Default,,0,0,0,,伯纳德? 你开玩笑吧\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Bernard? You're kidding.
Dialogue: 0,3:06:30.50,3:06:34.63,Default,,0,0,0,,那…那也是我的名字\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}That's... Heh. That's my name too.
Dialogue: 0,3:06:35.22,3:06:38.45,Default,,0,0,0,,没什么大不了的 很多人都叫伯纳德\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Not that big a deal. There's lots of people called Bernard.
Dialogue: 0,3:07:13.86,3:07:15.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}(纽约邮报：战争? )
Dialogue: 0,3:08:03.68,3:08:06.83,Default,,0,0,0,,老天爷 亨利\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Jesus Christ, Henry.
Dialogue: 0,3:08:06.83,3:08:09.10,Default,,0,0,0,,搞什么鬼我们没侦测到发射?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Why the hell didn't we get a launch detection?
Dialogue: 0,3:08:10.95,3:08:15.39,Default,,0,0,0,,这不是苏联 先生\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}It's not the Soviets, sir.
Dialogue: 0,3:08:15.96,3:08:21.72,Default,,0,0,0,,情报显示这个能量特征的引发者是…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Intel indicates the energy signature was generated by...
Dialogue: 0,3:08:22.70,3:08:25.16,Default,,0,0,0,,曼哈顿博士\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...Dr. Manhattan.
Dialogue: 0,3:08:27.97,3:08:29.53,Default,,0,0,0,,乔恩\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Jon.
Dialogue: 0,3:08:32.54,3:08:33.71,Default,,0,0,0,,干扰\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Interference.
Dialogue: 0,3:08:34.27,3:08:36.21,Default,,0,0,0,,灾难性的干扰\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Cataclysmic interference.
Dialogue: 0,3:08:45.89,3:08:48.65,Default,,0,0,0,,我不敢相信这件事发生了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}LAURIE: I can't believe it happened.
Dialogue: 0,3:08:49.66,3:08:53.15,Default,,0,0,0,,这不是由核弹头引起的\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}This wasn't caused by nuclear warheads.
Dialogue: 0,3:08:57.23,3:08:58.57,Default,,0,0,0,,是我\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}It was me.
Dialogue: 0,3:09:00.57,3:09:02.16,Default,,0,0,0,,我…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I...
Dialogue: 0,3:09:02.74,3:09:03.82,Default,,0,0,0,,造成的\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...did this.
Dialogue: 0,3:09:04.40,3:09:06.43,Default,,0,0,0,,你什么意思? 是你造成的?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}What do you mean, you did this?
Dialogue: 0,3:09:06.43,3:09:07.44,Default,,0,0,0,,不是直接的\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Not directly.
Dialogue: 0,3:09:08.84,3:09:11.54,Default,,0,0,0,,它做成像是我造成的\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}It was made to look like I did it.
Dialogue: 0,3:09:14.58,3:09:16.04,Default,,0,0,0,,阿德里安\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Adrian.
Dialogue: 0,3:09:22.17,3:09:24.28,Default,,0,0,0,,说到就到\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Speak of the devil.
Dialogue: 0,3:09:27.43,3:09:28.61,Default,,0,0,0,,- 乔恩  - 我知道\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}DAN: Jon... JON: I know.
Dialogue: 0,3:09:28.61,3:09:30.94,Default,,0,0,0,,必须阻止他 他杀了布雷克 杀了上百万人\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}RORSCHACH: Must stop him. Killed Blake, killed millions.
Dialogue: 0,3:09:30.94,3:09:32.35,Default,,0,0,0,,在这等着\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Wait here.
Dialogue: 0,3:09:43.44,3:09:45.81,Default,,0,0,0,,阿德里安 收手吧\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Adrian, stop this.
Dialogue: 0,3:09:47.28,3:09:49.20,Default,,0,0,0,,超光速粒子那招很聪明\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}The tachyons were clever...
Dialogue: 0,3:09:50.28,3:09:54.66,Default,,0,0,0,,但即便我无法预测你在哪 我也能把这些墙变成玻璃\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...but even if I can't predict where you are, I can turn the walls to glass.
Dialogue: 0,3:09:55.96,3:09:58.42,Default,,0,0,0,,我该谢谢你\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I should thank you.
Dialogue: 0,3:09:59.59,3:10:02.84,Default,,0,0,0,,我几乎忘了"不知道"的兴奋感\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I'd almost forgotten the excitement of not knowing...
Dialogue: 0,3:10:03.80,3:10:06.84,Default,,0,0,0,,不确定带来的快乐\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}... the delights of uncertainty.
Dialogue: 0,3:10:10.97,3:10:12.68,Default,,0,0,0,,原谅我 姑娘\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Forgive me, girl.
Dialogue: 0,3:10:35.60,3:10:37.33,Default,,0,0,0,,你就是个混蛋\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You're such an asshole.
Dialogue: 0,3:11:11.23,3:11:13.20,Default,,0,0,0,,维特 你这杂种\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}DAN: Veidt, you bastard.
Dialogue: 0,3:11:13.20,3:11:15.80,Default,,0,0,0,,- 你要敢伤害她 我就…  - 丹\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}- If you've hurt her, I'Il... - Dan...
Dialogue: 0,3:11:17.54,3:11:22.17,Default,,0,0,0,,长大点吧 我的新世界需要少一些英雄行为\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...grow up. My new world demands less obvious heroism.
Dialogue: 0,3:11:22.17,3:11:24.46,Default,,0,0,0,,你的…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Your...
Dialogue: 0,3:11:24.46,3:11:26.65,Default,,0,0,0,,小男生似的英雄行为是多余的\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...schoolboy heroics are redundant.
Dialogue: 0,3:11:27.34,3:11:28.94,Default,,0,0,0,,它成就过什么吗?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}What have they achieved?
Dialogue: 0,3:11:31.05,3:11:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,失败于避免地球被拯救\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Failing to prevent Earth's salvation...
Dialogue: 0,3:11:34.89,3:11:37.47,Default,,0,0,0,,就是你们唯一的功绩\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...is your only triumph.
Dialogue: 0,3:11:37.47,3:11:39.43,Default,,0,0,0,,我对你失望了 阿德里安\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}JON: I'm disappointed in you, Adrian.
Dialogue: 0,3:11:40.19,3:11:43.69,Default,,0,0,0,,我非常失望\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I'm very disappointed.
Dialogue: 0,3:11:56.08,3:11:59.29,Default,,0,0,0,,重组我自己是我学到的第一招\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Reassembling myself was the first trick I learned.
Dialogue: 0,3:11:59.91,3:12:02.31,Default,,0,0,0,,它没能杀死奥斯特曼{\fs33.333} 曼哈顿博士的本名{\r}\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}It didn't kill Osterman.
Dialogue: 0,3:12:04.92,3:12:07.34,Default,,0,0,0,,你真的以为它能杀死我吗?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Did you really think it would kill me?
Dialogue: 0,3:12:08.59,3:12:11.75,Default,,0,0,0,,我在太阳表面行走过\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I have walked across the surface of the sun.
Dialogue: 0,3:12:12.26,3:12:15.78,Default,,0,0,0,,我见证过许多微小而又快速的事情\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I have witnessed events so tiny and so fast...
Dialogue: 0,3:12:15.78,3:12:18.81,Default,,0,0,0,,它们甚至很难说发生过\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...they can hardly be said to have occurred at all...
Dialogue: 0,3:12:18.81,3:12:22.52,Default,,0,0,0,,而你 阿德里安 只是个凡人而已\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...but you, Adrian, you're just a man.
Dialogue: 0,3:12:23.60,3:12:26.15,Default,,0,0,0,,世上最聪明的人\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}The world's smartest man...
Dialogue: 0,3:12:26.15,3:12:28.99,Default,,0,0,0,,对我构成的威胁\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...poses no more threat to me...
Dialogue: 0,3:12:28.99,3:12:32.20,Default,,0,0,0,,不会超过最聪明的白蚁\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...than does its smartest termite.
Dialogue: 0,3:12:34.41,3:12:35.91,Default,,0,0,0,,这是什么?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}What's that?
Dialogue: 0,3:12:36.28,3:12:38.20,Default,,0,0,0,,又一个终极武器?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Another ultimate weapon?
Dialogue: 0,3:12:38.79,3:12:40.51,Default,,0,0,0,,是的\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,3:12:42.12,3:12:43.62,Default,,0,0,0,,可以这么说\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You could say that.
Dialogue: 0,3:12:47.13,3:12:49.06,Default,,0,0,0,,遭受攻击\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}- came under attack.
Dialogue: 0,3:12:49.90,3:12:53.33,Default,,0,0,0,,数以万计的人死于非命\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Millions of lives were suddenly ended...
Dialogue: 0,3:12:53.80,3:12:58.77,Default,,0,0,0,,这是曼哈顿博士本人的邪恶罪行\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}... in an act of evil perpetrated by Dr. Manhattan himself.
Dialogue: 0,3:13:00.57,3:13:07.67,Default,,0,0,0,,自从攻击开始 我就持续与苏联的首脑保持联系\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Since the attacks, I have been in constant contact with the premier of the U.S.S.R.
Dialogue: 0,3:13:08.08,3:13:10.91,Default,,0,0,0,,放下我们过去的分歧\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Putting aside our past differences...
Dialogue: 0,3:13:11.25,3:13:13.41,Default,,0,0,0,,我们两人都承诺联合起来…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}... we have both pledged to unite...
Dialogue: 0,3:13:13.75,3:13:17.09,Default,,0,0,0,,对付这个共同的敌人\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}... against this common enemy.
Dialogue: 0,3:13:17.59,3:13:19.58,Default,,0,0,0,,同世界其余的人一起\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}With the rest of the world...
Dialogue: 0,3:13:20.03,3:13:22.05,Default,,0,0,0,,我们将会胜利\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}... we will prevail.
Dialogue: 0,3:13:24.60,3:13:27.75,Default,,0,0,0,,这是我们永远不应忘记的一天\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}This is a day we shall never forget.
Dialogue: 0,3:13:27.75,3:13:32.12,Default,,0,0,0,,而我们会前行保卫人类\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}And yet we go forward to defend the human race...
Dialogue: 0,3:13:32.12,3:13:36.77,Default,,0,0,0,,以及我们这世界的所有美好和正义\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}... and all that is good and just in our world.
Dialogue: 0,3:13:38.11,3:13:42.34,Default,,0,0,0,,谢谢 愿上帝保佑我们\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Thank you. God bless us all.
Dialogue: 0,3:13:42.72,3:13:44.51,Default,,0,0,0,,看见没?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}ADRIAN: Do you see?
Dialogue: 0,3:13:46.72,3:13:49.23,Default,,0,0,0,,两个超级大国 放弃了战争\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Two superpowers retreating from war.
Dialogue: 0,3:13:50.79,3:13:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,我把地球从地狱中救了出来\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I've saved the earth from hell.
Dialogue: 0,3:13:53.28,3:13:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,我们俩一起\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}We both have.
Dialogue: 0,3:13:55.70,3:13:58.07,Default,,0,0,0,,这是我的胜利 同样是你的\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}This is as much your victory as it is mine.
Dialogue: 0,3:13:58.07,3:14:00.43,Default,,0,0,0,,(紧急会议在华盛顿特区召开)
Dialogue: 0,3:14:00.43,3:14:02.52,Default,,0,0,0,,(曼哈顿博士攻击纽约)
Dialogue: 0,3:14:02.84,3:14:04.37,Default,,0,0,0,,现在我们能回去…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Now we can return...
Dialogue: 0,3:14:05.77,3:14:07.37,Default,,0,0,0,,干我们该干的事了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...do what we were meant to.
Dialogue: 0,3:14:07.37,3:14:10.02,Default,,0,0,0,,我们该要的是严格的正义\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}We were meant to exact justice.
Dialogue: 0,3:14:10.81,3:14:12.67,Default,,0,0,0,,人人都会知道你做了什么\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Everyone's gonna know what you've done.
Dialogue: 0,3:14:13.14,3:14:14.47,Default,,0,0,0,,是吗?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Will they?
Dialogue: 0,3:14:14.47,3:14:19.28,Default,,0,0,0,,揭发我 你就会葬送今天这么多死者换来的和平\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}By exposing me, you would sacrifice the peace so many died for today.
Dialogue: 0,3:14:19.28,3:14:20.72,Default,,0,0,0,,基于谎言的和平\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Peace based on a lie.
Dialogue: 0,3:14:20.72,3:14:22.76,Default,,0,0,0,,也是和平\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}But peace...
Dialogue: 0,3:14:22.76,3:14:24.12,Default,,0,0,0,,…无论如何\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...nonetheless.
Dialogue: 0,3:14:24.12,3:14:25.14,Default,,0,0,0,,他说得对\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}He's right.
Dialogue: 0,3:14:25.66,3:14:29.80,Default,,0,0,0,,揭发阿德里安只会让世界重新陷入核毁灭的厄运\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Exposing Adrian would only doom the world to nuclear destruction again.
Dialogue: 0,3:14:29.80,3:14:30.52,Default,,0,0,0,,不\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}No.
Dialogue: 0,3:14:31.38,3:14:32.81,Default,,0,0,0,,我们不能这样做\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}We can't do this.
Dialogue: 0,3:14:32.81,3:14:34.60,Default,,0,0,0,,在火星上\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}On Mars...
Dialogue: 0,3:14:36.10,3:14:37.99,Default,,0,0,0,,你教会了我生命的价值\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...you taught me the value of life.
Dialogue: 0,3:14:38.91,3:14:41.37,Default,,0,0,0,,如果我们希望它在这里维系\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}If we hope to preserve it here...
Dialogue: 0,3:14:42.14,3:14:44.20,Default,,0,0,0,,我们必须保持沉默\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...we must remain silent.
Dialogue: 0,3:14:47.87,3:14:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,你们保守秘密吧\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Keep your own secrets.
Dialogue: 0,3:14:56.82,3:14:58.02,Default,,0,0,0,,想都不要想\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Don't even think about it.
Dialogue: 0,3:15:00.63,3:15:02.02,Default,,0,0,0,,罗夏\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Rorschach.
Dialogue: 0,3:15:04.13,3:15:05.65,Default,,0,0,0,,等等\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Wait.
Dialogue: 0,3:15:06.70,3:15:08.79,Default,,0,0,0,,永不妥协\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Never compromise.
Dialogue: 0,3:15:09.17,3:15:12.04,Default,,0,0,0,,即便面临世界末日\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Not even in the face of armageddon.
Dialogue: 0,3:15:12.40,3:15:15.48,Default,,0,0,0,,这一直是我们俩之间的分别 丹尼尔\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}That's always been the difference between us, Daniel.
Dialogue: 0,3:15:26.49,3:15:30.01,Default,,0,0,0,,我让自己去感受每一个死亡\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I've made myself feel every death...
Dialogue: 0,3:15:31.49,3:15:37.40,Default,,0,0,0,,去看每一张我为拯救人类而谋杀的无辜的脸\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...see every innocent face I've murdered to save humanity.
Dialogue: 0,3:15:42.97,3:15:45.15,Default,,0,0,0,,你能理解 不是吗?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You understand, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,3:15:45.15,3:15:46.67,Default,,0,0,0,,既不纵容…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}JON: Without condoning...
Dialogue: 0,3:15:48.34,3:15:50.24,Default,,0,0,0,,也不谴责…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...or condemning...
Dialogue: 0,3:15:54.65,3:15:56.58,Default,,0,0,0,,我理解\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...I understand.
Dialogue: 0,3:16:03.99,3:16:07.16,Default,,0,0,0,,让开我的路 人们必须被告知\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Out of my way. People have to be told.
Dialogue: 0,3:16:07.99,3:16:09.95,Default,,0,0,0,,你知道我不能让你这么做\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You know I can't let you do that.
Dialogue: 0,3:16:11.16,3:16:14.16,Default,,0,0,0,,突然间你开发出了人性?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Suddenly you discover humanity?
Dialogue: 0,3:16:15.60,3:16:17.46,Default,,0,0,0,,真是方便\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Convenient.
Dialogue: 0,3:16:26.15,3:16:27.91,Default,,0,0,0,,如果你一开始就关心\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}If you'd cared from the start
Dialogue: 0,3:16:28.71,3:16:30.77,Default,,0,0,0,,这些事情没有一件会发生\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}none of this would have happened.
Dialogue: 0,3:16:34.49,3:16:37.46,Default,,0,0,0,,我能改变几乎任何东西\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I can change almost anything...
Dialogue: 0,3:16:42.03,3:16:44.41,Default,,0,0,0,,但我不能改变人的本性\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...but I can't change human nature.
Dialogue: 0,3:16:45.70,3:16:49.10,Default,,0,0,0,,当然 你必须保护维特的新乌托邦\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Of course you must protect Veidt's new utopia.
Dialogue: 0,3:16:50.37,3:16:53.75,Default,,0,0,0,,地基里再加上一具尸首又如何?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}What's one more body amongst foundations?
Dialogue: 0,3:17:00.15,3:17:01.80,Default,,0,0,0,,那你还等什么?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Well, what are you waiting for?
Dialogue: 0,3:17:05.22,3:17:07.05,Default,,0,0,0,,动手吧！\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Do it.
Dialogue: 0,3:17:13.16,3:17:14.23,Default,,0,0,0,,动手啊！\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Do it!
Dialogue: 0,3:17:16.77,3:17:20.26,Default,,0,0,0,,不！！！\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}No!
Dialogue: 0,3:17:37.75,3:17:43.67,Default,,0,0,0,,我要离开这个星系 去一个没这么复杂的地方\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}JON: I'm leaving this galaxy for one a little less complicated.
Dialogue: 0,3:17:43.67,3:17:46.34,Default,,0,0,0,,我以为你又开始在意生命了呢\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}LAURIE: I thought you said you cared about life again.
Dialogue: 0,3:17:46.34,3:17:47.80,Default,,0,0,0,,我是的\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}JON: I do.
Dialogue: 0,3:17:49.10,3:17:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,我想也许我要创造一些生命\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I think maybe I'll create some.
Dialogue: 0,3:17:56.10,3:17:58.43,Default,,0,0,0,,再见 劳瑞\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Goodbye, Laurie.
Dialogue: 0,3:18:33.56,3:18:34.83,Default,,0,0,0,,来啊\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Come on.
Dialogue: 0,3:18:37.31,3:18:38.90,Default,,0,0,0,,来啊\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Come on!
Dialogue: 0,3:18:43.32,3:18:44.65,Default,,0,0,0,,丹\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Dan...
Dialogue: 0,3:18:45.12,3:18:47.88,Default,,0,0,0,,一个团结又和平的世界\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...a world united and at peace.
Dialogue: 0,3:18:48.91,3:18:49.99,Default,,0,0,0,,必须有牺牲\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}There had to be sacrifice.
Dialogue: 0,3:18:49.99,3:18:51.03,Default,,0,0,0,,不！\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}No!
Dialogue: 0,3:18:51.03,3:18:54.54,Default,,0,0,0,,你没有理想化人类 你扭曲了人性\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You haven't idealized mankind, you've deformed it.
Dialogue: 0,3:18:54.54,3:18:56.45,Default,,0,0,0,,你残损了人心\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You've mutilated it.
Dialogue: 0,3:18:56.80,3:18:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,那就是你的遗产\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}That's your legacy.
Dialogue: 0,3:19:07.51,3:19:10.30,Default,,0,0,0,,那才是真正的恶作剧\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}That's the real practical joke.
Dialogue: 0,3:20:02.90,3:20:07.05,Default,,0,0,0,,重复一遍 您的电视机没有任何问题\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}MAN [ON TV]: We repeat, there is nothing wrong with your television set.
Dialogue: 0,3:20:07.05,3:20:10.68,Default,,0,0,0,,您即将参与一次伟大的冒险\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You are about to participate in a great adventure.
Dialogue: 0,3:20:10.68,3:20:14.02,Default,,0,0,0,,您即将体验恐惧和神秘\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You are about to experience the awe and mystery...
Dialogue: 0,3:20:14.02,3:20:19.44,Default,,0,0,0,,从心灵的最深处一直到外界限\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}... which reaches from the inner mind to the outer limits.
Dialogue: 0,3:20:21.05,3:20:23.24,Default,,0,0,0,,你确定不来一杯吗?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}SALLY: Sure you don't want a drink?
Dialogue: 0,3:20:24.25,3:20:25.27,Default,,0,0,0,,我没事\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I'm okay.
Dialogue: 0,3:20:26.35,3:20:27.63,Default,,0,0,0,,干杯\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Cheers.
Dialogue: 0,3:20:29.02,3:20:32.15,Default,,0,0,0,,有些事情我需要说出来\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}There's something I need to get off my chest.
Dialogue: 0,3:20:33.43,3:20:35.97,Default,,0,0,0,,我知道艾迪·布雷克是我的父亲\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I know that Eddie Blake was my father.
Dialogue: 0,3:20:38.93,3:20:40.33,Default,,0,0,0,,劳瑞\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Laurel.
Dialogue: 0,3:20:41.90,3:20:44.03,Default,,0,0,0,,你肯定对我有看法\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}What you must think of me.
Dialogue: 0,3:20:44.73,3:20:47.55,Default,,0,0,0,,对不起我从未告诉过你\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I'm sorry I never told you.
Dialogue: 0,3:20:47.55,3:20:49.52,Default,,0,0,0,,我本来应该说的\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I should have...
Dialogue: 0,3:20:49.52,3:20:53.83,Default,,0,0,0,,我不知道 我觉得丢人 我觉得很傻\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...but I don't know, I just felt ashamed. I felt stupid.
Dialogue: 0,3:20:53.83,3:20:55.78,Default,,0,0,0,,没关系的\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}It doesn't matter.
Dialogue: 0,3:20:56.62,3:21:01.88,Default,,0,0,0,,生命会带人去奇怪的地方 做奇怪的事情\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}People's lives take them strange places. They do strange things...
Dialogue: 0,3:21:02.45,3:21:05.54,Default,,0,0,0,,而且 有时候也不能说出来\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...and, well, sometimes they can't talk about them.
Dialogue: 0,3:21:05.54,3:21:07.89,Default,,0,0,0,,我知道那是怎么回事\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I know how that is...
Dialogue: 0,3:21:08.63,3:21:11.22,Default,,0,0,0,,但我只想让你知道\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...but I just want you to know that...
Dialogue: 0,3:21:11.80,3:21:14.68,Default,,0,0,0,,你对我从来没有做错过什么\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...you never did anything wrong by me.
Dialogue: 0,3:21:18.80,3:21:22.78,Default,,0,0,0,,你问过我 为什么我不生他的气\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}You asked me why I wasn't mad at him.
Dialogue: 0,3:21:24.69,3:21:27.13,Default,,0,0,0,,因为他把你给了我\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Because he gave me you.
Dialogue: 0,3:21:32.15,3:21:33.28,Default,,0,0,0,,谢谢你 妈妈\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Thanks, Mom.
Dialogue: 0,3:21:35.99,3:21:37.82,Default,,0,0,0,,我爱你\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I love you.
Dialogue: 0,3:21:45.33,3:21:46.25,Default,,0,0,0,,你好 朱庇特小姐\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Hello, Miss Jupiter.
Dialogue: 0,3:21:46.25,3:21:49.23,Default,,0,0,0,,哦 请叫莎莉\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Oh, Sally, please.
Dialogue: 0,3:21:51.17,3:21:54.05,Default,,0,0,0,,抱歉 我得去梳洗了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Excuse me. Gotta go freshen up.
Dialogue: 0,3:21:54.60,3:21:55.80,Default,,0,0,0,,一会儿就回来\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I'll be right back.
Dialogue: 0,3:22:06.29,3:22:10.45,Default,,0,0,0,,- 你在这里怎么样了?   - 不错 你那边呢?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}- So how's it going up here? - Good. How's it going down there?
Dialogue: 0,3:22:10.80,3:22:14.27,Default,,0,0,0,,不错 我想我把事情都理顺了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Good. I think I've got everything working.
Dialogue: 0,3:22:14.27,3:22:19.08,Default,,0,0,0,,阿基米德的所有系统升级了 暂时完成了熔补\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}All of Archie's systems are upgraded. Finished the tinkering for now...
Dialogue: 0,3:22:19.08,3:22:21.49,Default,,0,0,0,,我们要做的是开它出去兜风\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...so all we gotta do is take her out.
Dialogue: 0,3:22:21.49,3:22:24.56,Default,,0,0,0,,哇哦 听着像是个约会\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Well, that sounds like a date.
Dialogue: 0,3:22:35.88,3:22:38.15,Default,,0,0,0,,我们会没事吗?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Are we gonna be all right?
Dialogue: 0,3:22:40.22,3:22:44.70,Default,,0,0,0,,只要大家认为乔恩还在盯着我们 我们就会没事\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Long as people think Jon's still watching us, we'll be all right...
Dialogue: 0,3:22:44.70,3:22:46.59,Default,,0,0,0,,…到最后\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...in the end.
Dialogue: 0,3:22:48.23,3:22:50.54,Default,,0,0,0,,我知道乔恩会说什么\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I know what Jon would say:
Dialogue: 0,3:22:50.54,3:22:52.59,Default,,0,0,0,,世事无尽头\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Nothing ends.
Dialogue: 0,3:22:54.50,3:22:57.09,Default,,0,0,0,,世事从无尽头\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Nothing ever ends.
Dialogue: 0,3:23:20.65,3:23:25.22,Default,,0,0,0,,(新边疆人报)
Dialogue: 0,3:23:44.45,3:23:45.52,Default,,0,0,0,,西摩尔\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Seymour
Dialogue: 0,3:23:46.45,3:23:48.49,Default,,0,0,0,,我们再没有什么可写的了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}we got nothing to write about anymore.
Dialogue: 0,3:23:48.49,3:23:49.90,Default,,0,0,0,,国家里的每个人\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Everyone in the country...
Dialogue: 0,3:23:49.90,3:23:52.34,Default,,0,0,0,,世界上的每个国家都拉着手\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...every country in the world are holding hands...
Dialogue: 0,3:23:52.34,3:23:55.62,Default,,0,0,0,,唱着和平与爱的欢歌\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}...and singing songs about peace and love.
Dialogue: 0,3:23:56.13,3:23:59.27,Default,,0,0,0,,就像是住在一个该死的嬉皮社区里\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}It's like living in a goddamn global hippie commune.
Dialogue: 0,3:23:59.27,3:24:00.57,Default,,0,0,0,,哦…那个…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Well...
Dialogue: 0,3:24:00.57,3:24:03.30,Default,,0,0,0,,罗纳德·里根说他要在88年竞选总统\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Ronald Reagan says he's gonna be running for president in '88.
Dialogue: 0,3:24:03.30,3:24:05.34,Default,,0,0,0,,我们可以写一篇这个\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}We could run a piece on that.
Dialogue: 0,3:24:05.34,3:24:08.69,Default,,0,0,0,,西摩尔 我们不会用新闻报道来美化荒谬\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Seymour, we don't dignify absurdities with coverage.
Dialogue: 0,3:24:08.69,3:24:10.52,Default,,0,0,0,,这里仍然是美国 该死的\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}This is still America, damn it.
Dialogue: 0,3:24:10.52,3:24:12.48,Default,,0,0,0,,谁会想要一个牛仔入主白宫?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Who wants a cowboy in the White House?
Dialogue: 0,3:24:13.18,3:24:14.41,Default,,0,0,0,,好吧 呃…\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Okay....
Dialogue: 0,3:24:15.36,3:24:17.65,Default,,0,0,0,,我可以去轶闻档案里找点东西\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}I could look for something in the crank file.
Dialogue: 0,3:24:17.65,3:24:19.33,Default,,0,0,0,,轶闻档案?\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Crank file.
Dialogue: 0,3:24:19.33,3:24:21.51,Default,,0,0,0,,随便吧 找点积极的\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Whatever. Take some initiative.
Dialogue: 0,3:24:21.51,3:24:24.20,Default,,0,0,0,,想写什么就写什么 全交给你了\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Run whatever you like. I leave it entirely in your hands.
Dialogue: 0,3:24:30.66,3:24:35.51,Default,,0,0,0,,罗夏日记 1985年10月12号\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Rorschach's journal, October 12th, 1985.
Dialogue: 0,3:24:35.51,3:24:39.99,Default,,0,0,0,,今晚 一个笑匠死于纽约\N{\fs40\1c&HB4DCFC&}Tonight, a comedian died in New York.
